59 """
60 Important note on ids
61 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
62  
63 Multiple id generation schemes are used due to backwards compatibility.
64 - v1: 1.2.3 <= version < 1.3
65 The style used before the rewrite.
66 It is not the actual old code, but a replication of the behaviour.
67 - v2: 1.3 <= version < now
68 Standardised mangling scheme from
69 https://itanium-cxx-abi.github.io/cxx-abi/abi.html#mangling
70 though not completely implemented.
71 All versions are generated and attached to elements. The newest is used for
72 the index. All of the versions should work as permalinks.
73  
74  
75 Signature Nodes and Tagnames
76 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
77  
78 Each signature is in a desc_signature node, where all children are
79 desc_signature_line nodes. Each of these lines will have the attribute
80 'sphinx_line_type' set to one of the following (prioritized):
81 - 'declarator', if the line contains the name of the declared object.
82 - 'templateParams', if the line starts a template parameter list,
83 - 'templateParams', if the line has template parameters
84 Note: such lines might get a new tag in the future.
85 - 'templateIntroduction, if the line is on the form 'conceptName{...}'
86 No other desc_signature nodes should exist (so far).
87  
88  
89 Grammar
90 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
91  
92 See https://www.nongnu.org/hcb/ for the grammar,
93 and https://github.com/cplusplus/draft/blob/master/source/grammar.tex,
94 and https://github.com/cplusplus/concepts-ts
95 for the newest grammar.
96  
97 common grammar things:
98 template-declaration ->
99 "template" "<" template-parameter-list ">" declaration
100 template-parameter-list ->
101 template-parameter
102 | template-parameter-list "," template-parameter
103 template-parameter ->
104 type-parameter
105 | parameter-declaration # i.e., same as a function argument
106  
107 type-parameter ->
108 "class" "..."[opt] identifier[opt]
109 | "class" identifier[opt] "=" type-id
110 | "typename" "..."[opt] identifier[opt]
111 | "typename" identifier[opt] "=" type-id
112 | "template" "<" template-parameter-list ">"
113 "class" "..."[opt] identifier[opt]
114 | "template" "<" template-parameter-list ">"
115 "class" identifier[opt] "=" id-expression
116 # also, from C++17 we can have "typename" in template templates
117 templateDeclPrefix ->
118 "template" "<" template-parameter-list ">"
119  
120 simple-declaration ->
121 attribute-specifier-seq[opt] decl-specifier-seq[opt]
122 init-declarator-list[opt] ;
123 # Make the semicolon optional.
124 # For now: drop the attributes (TODO).
125 # Use at most 1 init-declarator.
126 -> decl-specifier-seq init-declarator
127 -> decl-specifier-seq declarator initializer
128  
129 decl-specifier ->
130 storage-class-specifier ->
131 ( "static" (only for member_object and function_object)
132 | "extern" (only for member_object and function_object)
133 | "register"
134 )
135 thread_local[opt] (only for member_object)
136 (it can also appear before the others)
137  
138 | type-specifier -> trailing-type-specifier
139 | function-specifier -> "inline" | "virtual" | "explicit" (only
140 for function_object)
141 | "friend" (only for function_object)
142 | "constexpr" (only for member_object and function_object)
143 trailing-type-specifier ->
144 simple-type-specifier
145 | elaborated-type-specifier
146 | typename-specifier
147 | cv-qualifier -> "const" | "volatile"
148 stricter grammar for decl-specifier-seq (with everything, each object
149 uses a subset):
150 visibility storage-class-specifier function-specifier "friend"
151 "constexpr" "volatile" "const" trailing-type-specifier
152 # where trailing-type-specifier can no be cv-qualifier
153 # Inside e.g., template parameters a strict subset is used
154 # (see type-specifier-seq)
155 trailing-type-specifier ->
156 simple-type-specifier ->
157 ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] type-name
158 | ::[opt] nested-name-specifier "template" simple-template-id
159 | "char" | "bool" | etc.
160 | decltype-specifier
161 | elaborated-type-specifier ->
162 class-key attribute-specifier-seq[opt] ::[opt]
163 nested-name-specifier[opt] identifier
164 | class-key ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] template[opt]
165 simple-template-id
166 | "enum" ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] identifier
167 | typename-specifier ->
168 "typename" ::[opt] nested-name-specifier identifier
169 | "typename" ::[opt] nested-name-specifier template[opt]
170 simple-template-id
171 class-key -> "class" | "struct" | "union"
172 type-name ->* identifier | simple-template-id
173 # ignoring attributes and decltype, and then some left-factoring
174 trailing-type-specifier ->
175 rest-of-trailing
176 ("class" | "struct" | "union" | "typename") rest-of-trailing
177 built-in -> "char" | "bool" | etc.
178 decltype-specifier
179 rest-of-trailing -> (with some simplification)
180 "::"[opt] list-of-elements-separated-by-::
181 element ->
182 "template"[opt] identifier ("<" template-argument-list ">")[opt]
183 template-argument-list ->
184 template-argument "..."[opt]
185 | template-argument-list "," template-argument "..."[opt]
186 template-argument ->
187 constant-expression
188 | type-specifier-seq abstract-declarator
189 | id-expression
190  
191  
192 declarator ->
193 ptr-declarator
194 | noptr-declarator parameters-and-qualifiers trailing-return-type
195 ptr-declarator ->
196 noptr-declarator
197 | ptr-operator ptr-declarator
198 noptr-declarator ->
199 declarator-id attribute-specifier-seq[opt] ->
200 "..."[opt] id-expression
201 | rest-of-trailing
202 | noptr-declarator parameters-and-qualifiers
203 | noptr-declarator "[" constant-expression[opt] "]"
204 attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
205 | "(" ptr-declarator ")"
206 ptr-operator ->
207 "*" attribute-specifier-seq[opt] cv-qualifier-seq[opt]
208 | "& attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
209 | "&&" attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
210 | "::"[opt] nested-name-specifier "*" attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
211 cv-qualifier-seq[opt]
212 # function_object must use a parameters-and-qualifiers, the others may
213 # use it (e.g., function pointers)
214 parameters-and-qualifiers ->
215 "(" parameter-clause ")" attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
216 cv-qualifier-seq[opt] ref-qualifier[opt]
217 exception-specification[opt]
218 ref-qualifier -> "&" | "&&"
219 exception-specification ->
220 "noexcept" ("(" constant-expression ")")[opt]
221 "throw" ("(" type-id-list ")")[opt]
222 # TODO: we don't implement attributes
223 # member functions can have initializers, but we fold them into here
224 memberFunctionInit -> "=" "0"
225 # (note: only "0" is allowed as the value, according to the standard,
226 # right?)
227  
228 enum-head ->
229 enum-key attribute-specifier-seq[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt]
230 identifier enum-base[opt]
231 enum-key -> "enum" | "enum struct" | "enum class"
232 enum-base ->
233 ":" type
234 enumerator-definition ->
235 identifier
236 | identifier "=" constant-expression
237  
238 We additionally add the possibility for specifying the visibility as the
239 first thing.
240  
241 concept_object:
242 goal:
243 just a declaration of the name (for now)
244  
245 grammar: only a single template parameter list, and the nested name
246 may not have any template argument lists
247  
248 "template" "<" template-parameter-list ">"
249 nested-name-specifier
250  
251 type_object:
252 goal:
253 either a single type (e.g., "MyClass:Something_T" or a typedef-like
254 thing (e.g. "Something Something_T" or "int I_arr[]"
255 grammar, single type: based on a type in a function parameter, but
256 without a name:
257 parameter-declaration
258 -> attribute-specifier-seq[opt] decl-specifier-seq
259 abstract-declarator[opt]
260 # Drop the attributes
261 -> decl-specifier-seq abstract-declarator[opt]
262 grammar, typedef-like: no initilizer
263 decl-specifier-seq declarator
264 Can start with a templateDeclPrefix.
265  
266 member_object:
267 goal: as a type_object which must have a declarator, and optionally
268 with a initializer
269 grammar:
270 decl-specifier-seq declarator initializer
271 Can start with a templateDeclPrefix.
272  
273 function_object:
274 goal: a function declaration, TODO: what about templates? for now: skip
275 grammar: no initializer
276 decl-specifier-seq declarator
277 Can start with a templateDeclPrefix.
278  
279 class_object:
280 goal: a class declaration, but with specification of a base class
281 grammar:
282 attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
283 nested-name "final"[opt] (":" base-specifier-list)[opt]
284 base-specifier-list ->
285 base-specifier "..."[opt]
286 | base-specifier-list, base-specifier "..."[opt]
287 base-specifier ->
288 base-type-specifier
289 | "virtual" access-spe"cifier[opt] base-type-specifier
290 | access-specifier[opt] "virtual"[opt] base-type-specifier
291 Can start with a templateDeclPrefix.
292  
293 enum_object:
294 goal: an unscoped enum or a scoped enum, optionally with the underlying
295 type specified
296 grammar:
297 ("class" | "struct")[opt] visibility[opt]
298 attribute-specifier-seq[opt] nested-name (":" type)[opt]
299 enumerator_object:
300 goal: an element in a scoped or unscoped enum. The name should be
301 injected according to the scopedness.
302 grammar:
303 nested-name ("=" constant-expression)
304  
305 namespace_object:
306 goal: a directive to put all following declarations in a specific scope
307 grammar:
308 nested-name
309 """
310  
311 udl_identifier_re = re.compile(r'''
312 [a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\b # note, no word boundary in the beginning
313 ''', re.VERBOSE)
314 _string_re = re.compile(r"[LuU8]?('([^'\\]*(?:\\.[^'\\]*)*)'"
315 r'|"([^"\\]*(?:\\.[^"\\]*)*)")', re.S)
316 _visibility_re = re.compile(r'\b(public|private|protected)\b')
317 _operator_re = re.compile(r'''
318 \[\s*\]
319 | \(\s*\)
320 | \+\+ | --
321 | ->\*? | \,
322 | (<<|>>)=? | && | \|\|
323 | <=>
324 | [!<>=/*%+|&^~-]=?
325 | (\b(and|and_eq|bitand|bitor|compl|not|not_eq|or|or_eq|xor|xor_eq)\b)
326 ''', re.VERBOSE)
327 _fold_operator_re = re.compile(r'''
328 ->\* | \.\* | \,
329 | (<<|>>)=? | && | \|\|
330 | !=
331 | [<>=/*%+|&^~-]=?
332 ''', re.VERBOSE)

594 class _DuplicateSymbolError(Exception):
595 def __init__(self, symbol: Symbol, declaration: ASTDeclaration) -> None:
596 assert symbol
597 assert declaration
598 self.symbol = symbol
599 self.declaration = declaration
600  
601 def __str__(self) -> str:
602 return "Internal C++ duplicate symbol error:\n%s" % self.symbol.dump(0)
603  
604  
605 class ASTBase(ASTBaseBase):
606 pass
607  
608  
609 # Names
610 ################################################################################
611  
612 class ASTIdentifier(ASTBase):
613 def __init__(self, identifier: str) -> None:
614 assert identifier is not None
615 assert len(identifier) != 0
616 self.identifier = identifier
617  
618 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
619 return transform(self.identifier)
620  
621 def is_anon(self) -> bool:
622 return self.identifier[0] == '@'
623  
624 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
625 if self.is_anon() and version < 3:
626 raise NoOldIdError
627 if version == 1:
628 if self.identifier == 'size_t':
629 return 's'
630 else:
631 return self.identifier
632 if self.identifier == "std":
633 return 'St'
634 elif self.identifier[0] == "~":
635 # a destructor, just use an arbitrary version of dtors
636 return 'D0'
637 else:
638 if self.is_anon():
639 return 'Ut%d_%s' % (len(self.identifier) - 1, self.identifier[1:])
640 else:
641 return str(len(self.identifier)) + self.identifier
642  
643 # and this is where we finally make a difference between __str__ and the display string
644  
645 def __str__(self) -> str:
646 return self.identifier
647  
648 def get_display_string(self) -> str:
649 return "[anonymous]" if self.is_anon() else self.identifier
650  
651 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str, env: BuildEnvironment,
652 prefix: str, templateArgs: str, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
653 verify_description_mode(mode)
654 if self.is_anon():
655 node = addnodes.desc_sig_name(text="[anonymous]")
656 else:
657 node = addnodes.desc_sig_name(self.identifier, self.identifier)
658 if mode == 'markType':
659 targetText = prefix + self.identifier + templateArgs
660 pnode = addnodes.pending_xref('', refdomain='cpp',
661 reftype='identifier',
662 reftarget=targetText, modname=None,
663 classname=None)
664 pnode['cpp:parent_key'] = symbol.get_lookup_key()
665 pnode += node
666 signode += pnode
667 elif mode == 'lastIsName':
668 nameNode = addnodes.desc_name()
669 nameNode += node
670 signode += nameNode
671 elif mode == 'noneIsName':
672 signode += node
673 elif mode == 'param':
674 node['classes'].append('sig-param')
675 signode += node
676 elif mode == 'udl':
677 # the target is 'operator""id' instead of just 'id'
678 assert len(prefix) == 0
679 assert len(templateArgs) == 0
680 assert not self.is_anon()
681 targetText = 'operator""' + self.identifier
682 pnode = addnodes.pending_xref('', refdomain='cpp',
683 reftype='identifier',
684 reftarget=targetText, modname=None,
685 classname=None)
686 pnode['cpp:parent_key'] = symbol.get_lookup_key()
687 pnode += node
688 signode += pnode
689 else:
690 raise Exception('Unknown description mode: %s' % mode)
691  
692  
693 class ASTNestedNameElement(ASTBase):
694 def __init__(self, identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
695 templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs) -> None:
696 self.identOrOp = identOrOp
697 self.templateArgs = templateArgs
698  
699 def is_operator(self) -> bool:
700 return False
701  
702 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
703 res = self.identOrOp.get_id(version)
704 if self.templateArgs:
705 res += self.templateArgs.get_id(version)
706 return res
707  
708 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
709 res = transform(self.identOrOp)
710 if self.templateArgs:
711 res += transform(self.templateArgs)
712 return res
713  
714 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
715 env: BuildEnvironment, prefix: str, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
716 tArgs = str(self.templateArgs) if self.templateArgs is not None else ''
717 self.identOrOp.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, prefix, tArgs, symbol)
718 if self.templateArgs is not None:
719 self.templateArgs.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol)
720  
721  
722 class ASTNestedName(ASTBase):
723 def __init__(self, names: list[ASTNestedNameElement],
724 templates: list[bool], rooted: bool) -> None:
725 assert len(names) > 0
726 self.names = names
727 self.templates = templates
728 assert len(self.names) == len(self.templates)
729 self.rooted = rooted
730  
731 @property
732 def name(self) -> ASTNestedName:
733 return self
734  
735 def num_templates(self) -> int:
736 count = 0
737 for n in self.names:
738 if n.is_operator():
739 continue
740 if n.templateArgs:
741 count += 1
742 return count
743  
744 def get_id(self, version: int, modifiers: str = '') -> str:
745 if version == 1:
746 tt = str(self)
747 if tt in _id_shorthands_v1:
748 return _id_shorthands_v1[tt]
749 else:
750 return '::'.join(n.get_id(version) for n in self.names)
751  
752 res = []
753 if len(self.names) > 1 or len(modifiers) > 0:
754 res.append('N')
755 res.append(modifiers)
756 for n in self.names:
757 res.append(n.get_id(version))
758 if len(self.names) > 1 or len(modifiers) > 0:
759 res.append('E')
760 return ''.join(res)
761  
762 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
763 res = []
764 if self.rooted:
765 res.append('')
766 for i in range(len(self.names)):
767 n = self.names[i]
768 if self.templates[i]:
769 res.append("template " + transform(n))
770 else:
771 res.append(transform(n))
772 return '::'.join(res)
773  
774 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
775 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
776 verify_description_mode(mode)
777 # just print the name part, with template args, not template params
778 if mode == 'noneIsName':
779 if self.rooted:
780 unreachable = "Can this happen?"
781 raise AssertionError(unreachable) # TODO
782 signode += nodes.Text('::')
783 for i in range(len(self.names)):
784 if i != 0:
785 unreachable = "Can this happen?"
786 raise AssertionError(unreachable) # TODO
787 signode += nodes.Text('::blah')
788 n = self.names[i]
789 if self.templates[i]:
790 unreachable = "Can this happen?"
791 raise AssertionError(unreachable) # TODO
792 signode += nodes.Text("template")
793 signode += nodes.Text(" ")
794 n.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, '', symbol)
795 elif mode == 'param':
796 assert not self.rooted, str(self)
797 assert len(self.names) == 1
798 assert not self.templates[0]
799 self.names[0].describe_signature(signode, 'param', env, '', symbol)
800 elif mode in ('markType', 'lastIsName', 'markName'):
801 # Each element should be a pending xref targeting the complete
802 # prefix. however, only the identifier part should be a link, such
803 # that template args can be a link as well.
804 # For 'lastIsName' we should also prepend template parameter lists.
805 templateParams: list[Any] = []
806 if mode == 'lastIsName':
807 assert symbol is not None
808 if symbol.declaration.templatePrefix is not None:
809 templateParams = symbol.declaration.templatePrefix.templates
810 iTemplateParams = 0
811 templateParamsPrefix = ''
812 prefix = ''
813 first = True
814 names = self.names[:-1] if mode == 'lastIsName' else self.names
815 # If lastIsName, then wrap all of the prefix in a desc_addname,
816 # else append directly to signode.
817 # NOTE: Breathe previously relied on the prefix being in the desc_addname node,
818 # so it can remove it in inner declarations.
819 dest = signode
820 if mode == 'lastIsName':
821 dest = addnodes.desc_addname()
822 if self.rooted:
823 prefix += '::'
824 if mode == 'lastIsName' and len(names) == 0:
825 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('::', '::')
826 else:
827 dest += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('::', '::')
828 for i in range(len(names)):
829 nne = names[i]
830 template = self.templates[i]
831 if not first:
832 dest += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('::', '::')
833 prefix += '::'
834 if template:
835 dest += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('template', 'template')
836 dest += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
837 first = False
838 txt_nne = str(nne)
839 if txt_nne != '':
840 if nne.templateArgs and iTemplateParams < len(templateParams):
841 templateParamsPrefix += str(templateParams[iTemplateParams])
842 iTemplateParams += 1
843 nne.describe_signature(dest, 'markType',
844 env, templateParamsPrefix + prefix, symbol)
845 prefix += txt_nne
846 if mode == 'lastIsName':
847 if len(self.names) > 1:
848 dest += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('::', '::')
849 signode += dest
850 if self.templates[-1]:
851 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('template', 'template')
852 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
853 self.names[-1].describe_signature(signode, mode, env, '', symbol)
854 else:
855 raise Exception('Unknown description mode: %s' % mode)
856

862 class ASTExpression(ASTBase):
863 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
864 raise NotImplementedError(repr(self))
865  
866 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
867 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
868 raise NotImplementedError(repr(self))

871 # Primary expressions
872 ################################################################################
873  
874 class ASTLiteral(ASTExpression):
875 pass
876  
877  
878 class ASTPointerLiteral(ASTLiteral):
879 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
880 return 'nullptr'
881  
882 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
883 return 'LDnE'
884  
885 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
886 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
887 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('nullptr', 'nullptr')

889  
890 class ASTBooleanLiteral(ASTLiteral):
891 def __init__(self, value: bool) -> None:
892 self.value = value
893  
894 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
895 if self.value:
896 return 'true'
897 else:
898 return 'false'
899  
900 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
901 if self.value:
902 return 'L1E'
903 else:
904 return 'L0E'
905  
906 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
907 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
908 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(str(self), str(self))
909  
910  
911 class ASTNumberLiteral(ASTLiteral):
912 def __init__(self, data: str) -> None:
913 self.data = data
914  
915 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
916 return self.data
917  
918 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
919 # TODO: floats should be mangled by writing the hex of the binary representation
920 return "L%sE" % self.data.replace("'", "")
921  
922 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
923 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
924 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_literal_number(self.data, self.data)
925  
926  
927 class ASTStringLiteral(ASTLiteral):
928 def __init__(self, data: str) -> None:
929 self.data = data
930  
931 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
932 return self.data
933  
934 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
935 # note: the length is not really correct with escaping
936 return "LA%d_KcE" % (len(self.data) - 2)
937  
938 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
939 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
940 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_literal_string(self.data, self.data)
941  
942  
943 class ASTCharLiteral(ASTLiteral):
944 def __init__(self, prefix: str, data: str) -> None:
945 self.prefix = prefix # may be None when no prefix
946 self.data = data
947 assert prefix in _id_char_from_prefix
948 self.type = _id_char_from_prefix[prefix]
949 decoded = data.encode().decode('unicode-escape')
950 if len(decoded) == 1:
951 self.value = ord(decoded)
952 else:
953 raise UnsupportedMultiCharacterCharLiteral(decoded)
954  
955 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
956 if self.prefix is None:
957 return "'" + self.data + "'"
958 else:
959 return self.prefix + "'" + self.data + "'"
960  
961 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
962 # TODO: the ID should be have L E around it
963 return self.type + str(self.value)
964  
965 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
966 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
967 if self.prefix is not None:
968 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.prefix, self.prefix)
969 txt = "'" + self.data + "'"
970 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_literal_char(txt, txt)
971  
972  
973 class ASTUserDefinedLiteral(ASTLiteral):
974 def __init__(self, literal: ASTLiteral, ident: ASTIdentifier):
975 self.literal = literal
976 self.ident = ident
977  
978 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
979 return transform(self.literal) + transform(self.ident)
980  
981 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
982 # mangle as if it was a function call: ident(literal)
983 return f'clL_Zli{self.ident.get_id(version)}E{self.literal.get_id(version)}E'
984  
985 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
986 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
987 self.literal.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
988 self.ident.describe_signature(signode, "udl", env, "", "", symbol)

993 class ASTThisLiteral(ASTExpression):
994 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
995 return "this"
996  
997 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
998 return "fpT"
999  
1000 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1001 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1002 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('this', 'this')

1004  
1005 class ASTFoldExpr(ASTExpression):
1006 def __init__(self, leftExpr: ASTExpression,
1007 op: str, rightExpr: ASTExpression) -> None:
1008 assert leftExpr is not None or rightExpr is not None
1009 self.leftExpr = leftExpr
1010 self.op = op
1011 self.rightExpr = rightExpr
1012  
1013 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1014 res = ['(']
1015 if self.leftExpr:
1016 res.append(transform(self.leftExpr))
1017 res.append(' ')
1018 res.append(self.op)
1019 res.append(' ')
1020 res.append('...')
1021 if self.rightExpr:
1022 res.append(' ')
1023 res.append(self.op)
1024 res.append(' ')
1025 res.append(transform(self.rightExpr))
1026 res.append(')')
1027 return ''.join(res)
1028  
1029 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1030 assert version >= 3
1031 if version == 3:
1032 return str(self)
1033 # https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/pull/67
1034 res = []
1035 if self.leftExpr is None: # (... op expr)
1036 res.append('fl')
1037 elif self.rightExpr is None: # (expr op ...)
1038 res.append('fr')
1039 else: # (expr op ... op expr)
1040 # we don't check where the parameter pack is,
1041 # we just always call this a binary left fold
1042 res.append('fL')
1043 res.append(_id_operator_v2[self.op])
1044 if self.leftExpr:
1045 res.append(self.leftExpr.get_id(version))
1046 if self.rightExpr:
1047 res.append(self.rightExpr.get_id(version))
1048 return ''.join(res)
1049  
1050 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1051 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1052 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('(', '(')
1053 if self.leftExpr:
1054 self.leftExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1055 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1056 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(self.op, self.op)
1057 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1058 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('...', '...')
1059 if self.rightExpr:
1060 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1061 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(self.op, self.op)
1062 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1063 self.rightExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1064 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(')', ')')
1065  
1066

1079 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('(', '(')
1080 self.expr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1081 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(')', ')')

1204 class ASTPostfixExpr(ASTExpression):
1205 def __init__(self, prefix: ASTType, postFixes: list[ASTPostfixOp]):
1206 self.prefix = prefix
1207 self.postFixes = postFixes
1208  
1209 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1210 res = [transform(self.prefix)]
1211 for p in self.postFixes:
1212 res.append(transform(p))
1213 return ''.join(res)
1214  
1215 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1216 id = self.prefix.get_id(version)
1217 for p in self.postFixes:
1218 id = p.get_id(id, version)
1219 return id
1220  
1221 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1222 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1223 self.prefix.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1224 for p in self.postFixes:
1225 p.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)

1228 class ASTExplicitCast(ASTExpression):
1229 def __init__(self, cast: str, typ: ASTType, expr: ASTExpression):
1230 assert cast in _id_explicit_cast
1231 self.cast = cast
1232 self.typ = typ
1233 self.expr = expr
1234  
1235 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1236 res = [self.cast]
1237 res.append('<')
1238 res.append(transform(self.typ))
1239 res.append('>(')
1240 res.append(transform(self.expr))
1241 res.append(')')
1242 return ''.join(res)
1243  
1244 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1245 return (_id_explicit_cast[self.cast] +
1246 self.typ.get_id(version) +
1247 self.expr.get_id(version))
1248  
1249 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1250 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1251 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.cast, self.cast)
1252 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('<', '<')
1253 self.typ.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1254 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('>', '>')
1255 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('(', '(')
1256 self.expr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1257 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(')', ')')

1280 # Unary expressions

1283 class ASTUnaryOpExpr(ASTExpression):
1284 def __init__(self, op: str, expr: ASTExpression):
1285 self.op = op
1286 self.expr = expr
1287  
1288 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1289 if self.op[0] in 'cn':
1290 return self.op + " " + transform(self.expr)
1291 else:
1292 return self.op + transform(self.expr)
1293  
1294 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1295 return _id_operator_unary_v2[self.op] + self.expr.get_id(version)
1296  
1297 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1298 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1299 if self.op[0] in 'cn':
1300 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.op, self.op)
1301 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1302 else:
1303 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(self.op, self.op)
1304 self.expr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)

1323 symbol=symbol, prefix="", templateArgs="")
1324 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(')', ')')

1398 class ASTNewExpr(ASTExpression):
1399 def __init__(self, rooted: bool, isNewTypeId: bool, typ: ASTType,
1400 initList: ASTParenExprList | ASTBracedInitList) -> None:
1401 self.rooted = rooted
1402 self.isNewTypeId = isNewTypeId
1403 self.typ = typ
1404 self.initList = initList
1405  
1406 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1407 res = []
1408 if self.rooted:
1409 res.append('::')
1410 res.append('new ')
1411 # TODO: placement
1412 if self.isNewTypeId:
1413 res.append(transform(self.typ))
1414 else:
1415 raise AssertionError
1416 if self.initList is not None:
1417 res.append(transform(self.initList))
1418 return ''.join(res)
1419  
1420 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1421 # the array part will be in the type mangling, so na is not used
1422 res = ['nw']
1423 # TODO: placement
1424 res.append('_')
1425 res.append(self.typ.get_id(version))
1426 if self.initList is not None:
1427 res.append(self.initList.get_id(version))
1428 else:
1429 res.append('E')
1430 return ''.join(res)
1431  
1432 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1433 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1434 if self.rooted:
1435 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('::', '::')
1436 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('new', 'new')
1437 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1438 # TODO: placement
1439 if self.isNewTypeId:
1440 self.typ.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1441 else:
1442 raise AssertionError
1443 if self.initList is not None:
1444 self.initList.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1445  
1446  
1447 class ASTDeleteExpr(ASTExpression):
1448 def __init__(self, rooted: bool, array: bool, expr: ASTExpression):
1449 self.rooted = rooted
1450 self.array = array
1451 self.expr = expr
1452  
1453 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1454 res = []
1455 if self.rooted:
1456 res.append('::')
1457 res.append('delete ')
1458 if self.array:
1459 res.append('[] ')
1460 res.append(transform(self.expr))
1461 return ''.join(res)
1462  
1463 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1464 if self.array:
1465 id = "da"
1466 else:
1467 id = "dl"
1468 return id + self.expr.get_id(version)
1469  
1470 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1471 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1472 if self.rooted:
1473 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('::', '::')
1474 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('delete', 'delete')
1475 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1476 if self.array:
1477 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('[]', '[]')
1478 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1479 self.expr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)

1488 self.expr = expr

1491 res = ['(']
1492 res.append(transform(self.typ))
1493 res.append(')')
1494 res.append(transform(self.expr))
1495 return ''.join(res)

1497 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1498 return 'cv' + self.typ.get_id(version) + self.expr.get_id(version)

1501 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1502 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('(', '(')

1508 class ASTBinOpExpr(ASTExpression):
1509 def __init__(self, exprs: list[ASTExpression], ops: list[str]):
1510 assert len(exprs) > 0
1511 assert len(exprs) == len(ops) + 1
1512 self.exprs = exprs
1513 self.ops = ops
1514  
1515 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1516 res = []
1517 res.append(transform(self.exprs[0]))
1518 for i in range(1, len(self.exprs)):
1519 res.append(' ')
1520 res.append(self.ops[i - 1])
1521 res.append(' ')
1522 res.append(transform(self.exprs[i]))
1523 return ''.join(res)
1524  
1525 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1526 assert version >= 2
1527 res = []
1528 for i in range(len(self.ops)):
1529 res.append(_id_operator_v2[self.ops[i]])
1530 res.append(self.exprs[i].get_id(version))
1531 res.append(self.exprs[-1].get_id(version))
1532 return ''.join(res)
1533  
1534 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1535 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1536 self.exprs[0].describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1537 for i in range(1, len(self.exprs)):
1538 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1539 op = self.ops[i - 1]
1540 if ord(op[0]) >= ord('a') and ord(op[0]) <= ord('z'):
1541 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(op, op)
1542 else:
1543 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(op, op)
1544 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1545 self.exprs[i].describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1546  
1547  
1548 class ASTConditionalExpr(ASTExpression):
1549 def __init__(self, ifExpr: ASTExpression, thenExpr: ASTExpression,
1550 elseExpr: ASTExpression):
1551 self.ifExpr = ifExpr
1552 self.thenExpr = thenExpr
1553 self.elseExpr = elseExpr
1554  
1555 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1556 res = []
1557 res.append(transform(self.ifExpr))
1558 res.append(' ? ')
1559 res.append(transform(self.thenExpr))
1560 res.append(' : ')
1561 res.append(transform(self.elseExpr))
1562 return ''.join(res)
1563  
1564 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1565 assert version >= 2
1566 res = []
1567 res.append(_id_operator_v2['?'])
1568 res.append(self.ifExpr.get_id(version))
1569 res.append(self.thenExpr.get_id(version))
1570 res.append(self.elseExpr.get_id(version))
1571 return ''.join(res)
1572  
1573 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1574 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1575 self.ifExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1576 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1577 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator('?', '?')
1578 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1579 self.thenExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1580 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1581 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(':', ':')
1582 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1583 self.elseExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1584

1586 class ASTBracedInitList(ASTBase):
1587 def __init__(self, exprs: list[ASTExpression | ASTBracedInitList],
1588 trailingComma: bool) -> None:
1589 self.exprs = exprs
1590 self.trailingComma = trailingComma
1591  
1592 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1593 return "il%sE" % ''.join(e.get_id(version) for e in self.exprs)
1594  
1595 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1596 exprs = ', '.join(transform(e) for e in self.exprs)
1597 trailingComma = ',' if self.trailingComma else ''
1598 return f'{{{exprs}{trailingComma}}}'
1599  
1600 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1601 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1602 verify_description_mode(mode)
1603 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('{', '{')
1604 first = True
1605 for e in self.exprs:
1606 if not first:
1607 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
1608 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1609 else:
1610 first = False
1611 e.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1612 if self.trailingComma:
1613 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
1614 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('}', '}')
1615  
1616  
1617 class ASTAssignmentExpr(ASTExpression):
1618 def __init__(self, leftExpr: ASTExpression, op: str,
1619 rightExpr: ASTExpression | ASTBracedInitList):
1620 self.leftExpr = leftExpr
1621 self.op = op
1622 self.rightExpr = rightExpr
1623  
1624 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1625 res = []
1626 res.append(transform(self.leftExpr))
1627 res.append(' ')
1628 res.append(self.op)
1629 res.append(' ')
1630 res.append(transform(self.rightExpr))
1631 return ''.join(res)
1632  
1633 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1634 # we end up generating the ID from left to right, instead of right to left
1635 res = []
1636 res.append(_id_operator_v2[self.op])
1637 res.append(self.leftExpr.get_id(version))
1638 res.append(self.rightExpr.get_id(version))
1639 return ''.join(res)
1640  
1641 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1642 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1643 self.leftExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1644 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1645 if ord(self.op[0]) >= ord('a') and ord(self.op[0]) <= ord('z'):
1646 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.op, self.op)
1647 else:
1648 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(self.op, self.op)
1649 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1650 self.rightExpr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1651  
1652  
1653 class ASTCommaExpr(ASTExpression):
1654 def __init__(self, exprs: list[ASTExpression]):
1655 assert len(exprs) > 0
1656 self.exprs = exprs
1657  
1658 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1659 return ', '.join(transform(e) for e in self.exprs)
1660  
1661 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1662 id_ = _id_operator_v2[',']
1663 res = []
1664 for i in range(len(self.exprs) - 1):
1665 res.append(id_)
1666 res.append(self.exprs[i].get_id(version))
1667 res.append(self.exprs[-1].get_id(version))
1668 return ''.join(res)
1669  
1670 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1671 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1672 self.exprs[0].describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1673 for i in range(1, len(self.exprs)):
1674 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
1675 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1676 self.exprs[i].describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1677

1700  
1701 class ASTOperator(ASTBase):
1702 def is_anon(self) -> bool:
1703 return False
1704  
1705 def is_operator(self) -> bool:
1706 return True
1707  
1708 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1709 raise NotImplementedError
1710  
1711 def _describe_identifier(self, signode: TextElement, identnode: TextElement,
1712 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1713 """Render the prefix into signode, and the last part into identnode."""
1714 raise NotImplementedError
1715  
1716 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1717 env: BuildEnvironment, prefix: str, templateArgs: str,
1718 symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1719 verify_description_mode(mode)
1720 if mode == 'lastIsName':
1721 mainName = addnodes.desc_name()
1722 self._describe_identifier(mainName, mainName, env, symbol)
1723 signode += mainName
1724 elif mode == 'markType':
1725 targetText = prefix + str(self) + templateArgs
1726 pnode = addnodes.pending_xref('', refdomain='cpp',
1727 reftype='identifier',
1728 reftarget=targetText, modname=None,
1729 classname=None)
1730 pnode['cpp:parent_key'] = symbol.get_lookup_key()
1731 # Render the identifier part, but collapse it into a string
1732 # and make that the a link to this operator.
1733 # E.g., if it is 'operator SomeType', then 'SomeType' becomes
1734 # a link to the operator, not to 'SomeType'.
1735 container = nodes.literal()
1736 self._describe_identifier(signode, container, env, symbol)
1737 txt = container.astext()
1738 pnode += addnodes.desc_name(txt, txt)
1739 signode += pnode
1740 else:
1741 addName = addnodes.desc_addname()
1742 self._describe_identifier(addName, addName, env, symbol)
1743 signode += addName
1744  
1745  
1746 class ASTOperatorBuildIn(ASTOperator):
1747 def __init__(self, op: str) -> None:
1748 self.op = op
1749  
1750 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1751 if version == 1:
1752 ids = _id_operator_v1
1753 if self.op not in ids:
1754 raise NoOldIdError
1755 else:
1756 ids = _id_operator_v2
1757 if self.op not in ids:
1758 raise Exception('Internal error: Built-in operator "%s" can not '
1759 'be mapped to an id.' % self.op)
1760 return ids[self.op]
1761  
1762 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1763 if self.op in ('new', 'new[]', 'delete', 'delete[]') or self.op[0] in "abcnox":
1764 return 'operator ' + self.op
1765 else:
1766 return 'operator' + self.op
1767  
1768 def _describe_identifier(self, signode: TextElement, identnode: TextElement,
1769 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1770 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('operator', 'operator')
1771 if self.op in ('new', 'new[]', 'delete', 'delete[]') or self.op[0] in "abcnox":
1772 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1773 identnode += addnodes.desc_sig_operator(self.op, self.op)
1774  
1775  
1776 class ASTOperatorLiteral(ASTOperator):
1777 def __init__(self, identifier: ASTIdentifier) -> None:
1778 self.identifier = identifier
1779  
1780 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1781 if version == 1:
1782 raise NoOldIdError
1783 return 'li' + self.identifier.get_id(version)
1784  
1785 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1786 return 'operator""' + transform(self.identifier)
1787  
1788 def _describe_identifier(self, signode: TextElement, identnode: TextElement,
1789 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1790 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('operator', 'operator')
1791 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_literal_string('""', '""')
1792 self.identifier.describe_signature(identnode, 'markType', env, '', '', symbol)
1793  
1794  
1795 class ASTOperatorType(ASTOperator):
1796 def __init__(self, type: ASTType) -> None:
1797 self.type = type
1798  
1799 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1800 if version == 1:
1801 return 'castto-%s-operator' % self.type.get_id(version)
1802 else:
1803 return 'cv' + self.type.get_id(version)
1804  
1805 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1806 return ''.join(['operator ', transform(self.type)])
1807  
1808 def get_name_no_template(self) -> str:
1809 return str(self)
1810  
1811 def _describe_identifier(self, signode: TextElement, identnode: TextElement,
1812 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1813 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('operator', 'operator')
1814 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1815 self.type.describe_signature(identnode, 'markType', env, symbol)

1818 class ASTTemplateArgConstant(ASTBase):
1819 def __init__(self, value: ASTExpression) -> None:
1820 self.value = value
1821  
1822 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1823 return transform(self.value)
1824  
1825 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1826 if version == 1:
1827 return str(self).replace(' ', '-')
1828 if version == 2:
1829 return 'X' + str(self) + 'E'
1830 return 'X' + self.value.get_id(version) + 'E'
1831  
1832 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1833 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1834 verify_description_mode(mode)
1835 self.value.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
1836  
1837  
1838 class ASTTemplateArgs(ASTBase):
1839 def __init__(self, args: list[ASTType | ASTTemplateArgConstant],
1840 packExpansion: bool) -> None:
1841 assert args is not None
1842 self.args = args
1843 self.packExpansion = packExpansion
1844  
1845 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1846 if version == 1:
1847 res = []
1848 res.append(':')
1849 res.append('.'.join(a.get_id(version) for a in self.args))
1850 res.append(':')
1851 return ''.join(res)
1852  
1853 res = []
1854 res.append('I')
1855 if len(self.args) > 0:
1856 for a in self.args[:-1]:
1857 res.append(a.get_id(version))
1858 if self.packExpansion:
1859 res.append('J')
1860 res.append(self.args[-1].get_id(version))
1861 if self.packExpansion:
1862 res.append('E')
1863 res.append('E')
1864 return ''.join(res)
1865  
1866 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1867 res = ', '.join(transform(a) for a in self.args)
1868 if self.packExpansion:
1869 res += '...'
1870 return '<' + res + '>'
1871  
1872 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1873 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1874 verify_description_mode(mode)
1875 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('<', '<')
1876 first = True
1877 for a in self.args:
1878 if not first:
1879 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
1880 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
1881 first = False
1882 a.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol=symbol)
1883 if self.packExpansion:
1884 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('...', '...')
1885 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('>', '>')
1886  
1887

1891 class ASTTrailingTypeSpec(ASTBase):
1892 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1893 raise NotImplementedError(repr(self))
1894  
1895 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1896 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1897 raise NotImplementedError(repr(self))
1898  
1899  
1900 class ASTTrailingTypeSpecFundamental(ASTTrailingTypeSpec):
1901 def __init__(self, names: list[str], canonNames: list[str]) -> None:
1902 assert len(names) != 0
1903 assert len(names) == len(canonNames), (names, canonNames)
1904 self.names = names
1905 # the canonical name list is for ID lookup
1906 self.canonNames = canonNames
1907  
1908 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
1909 return ' '.join(self.names)
1910  
1911 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
1912 if version == 1:
1913 res = []
1914 for a in self.canonNames:
1915 if a in _id_fundamental_v1:
1916 res.append(_id_fundamental_v1[a])
1917 else:
1918 res.append(a)
1919 return '-'.join(res)
1920  
1921 txt = ' '.join(self.canonNames)
1922 if txt not in _id_fundamental_v2:
1923 raise Exception(
1924 'Semi-internal error: Fundamental type "%s" can not be mapped '
1925 'to an ID. Is it a true fundamental type? If not so, the '
1926 'parser should have rejected it.' % txt)
1927 return _id_fundamental_v2[txt]
1928  
1929 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
1930 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
1931 first = True
1932 for n in self.names:
1933 if not first:
1934 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()

2021 class ASTFunctionParameter(ASTBase):
2022 def __init__(self, arg: ASTTypeWithInit | ASTTemplateParamConstrainedTypeWithInit,
2023 ellipsis: bool = False) -> None:
2024 self.arg = arg
2025 self.ellipsis = ellipsis
2026  
2027 def get_id(
2028 self, version: int, objectType: str | None = None, symbol: Symbol | None = None,
2029 ) -> str:
2030 # this is not part of the normal name mangling in C++
2031 if symbol:
2032 # the anchor will be our parent
2033 return symbol.parent.declaration.get_id(version, prefixed=False)
2034 # else, do the usual
2035 if self.ellipsis:
2036 return 'z'
2037 else:
2038 return self.arg.get_id(version)

2041 if self.ellipsis:
2042 return '...'
2043 else:
2044 return transform(self.arg)

2049 if self.ellipsis:
2050 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('...', '...')
2051 else:
2052 self.arg.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol=symbol)

2094 def get_modifiers_id(self, version: int) -> str:
2095 res = []
2096 if self.volatile:
2097 res.append('V')
2098 if self.const:
2099 if version == 1:
2100 res.append('C')
2101 else:
2102 res.append('K')

2109 def get_param_id(self, version: int) -> str:
2110 if version == 1:
2111 if len(self.args) == 0:
2112 return ''
2113 else:
2114 return '__' + '.'.join(a.get_id(version) for a in self.args)
2115 if len(self.args) == 0:
2116 return 'v'
2117 else:
2118 return ''.join(a.get_id(version) for a in self.args)

2120 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
2121 res = []

2123 first = True
2124 for a in self.args:

2131 res.append(' volatile')
2132 if self.const:
2133 res.append(' const')

2135 res.append(' ')

2140 if self.trailingReturn:

2145 if self.override:
2146 res.append(' override')
2147 if len(self.attrs) != 0:
2148 res.append(' ')

2150 if self.initializer:
2151 res.append(' = ')

2346 class ASTDeclSpecs(ASTBase):
2347 def __init__(self, outer: str,
2348 leftSpecs: ASTDeclSpecsSimple, rightSpecs: ASTDeclSpecsSimple,
2349 trailing: ASTTrailingTypeSpec) -> None:
2350 # leftSpecs and rightSpecs are used for output
2351 # allSpecs are used for id generation
2352 self.outer = outer
2353 self.leftSpecs = leftSpecs
2354 self.rightSpecs = rightSpecs
2355 self.allSpecs = self.leftSpecs.mergeWith(self.rightSpecs)
2356 self.trailingTypeSpec = trailing
2357  
2358 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
2359 if version == 1:
2360 res = []
2361 res.append(self.trailingTypeSpec.get_id(version))
2362 if self.allSpecs.volatile:
2363 res.append('V')
2364 if self.allSpecs.const:
2365 res.append('C')
2366 return ''.join(res)
2367 res = []
2368 if self.allSpecs.volatile:
2369 res.append('V')
2370 if self.allSpecs.const:
2371 res.append('K')
2372 if self.trailingTypeSpec is not None:
2373 res.append(self.trailingTypeSpec.get_id(version))
2374 return ''.join(res)
2375  
2376 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
2377 res: list[str] = []
  • E741 Ambiguous variable name 'l'
2378 l = transform(self.leftSpecs)
2379 if len(l) > 0:
2380 res.append(l)
2381 if self.trailingTypeSpec:
2382 if len(res) > 0:
2383 res.append(" ")
2384 res.append(transform(self.trailingTypeSpec))
2385 r = str(self.rightSpecs)
2386 if len(r) > 0:
2387 if len(res) > 0:
2388 res.append(" ")
2389 res.append(r)
2390 return "".join(res)
2391  
2392 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
2393 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
2394 verify_description_mode(mode)
2395 numChildren = len(signode)
2396 self.leftSpecs.describe_signature(signode, env, symbol)
2397 addSpace = len(signode) != numChildren
2398  
2399 if self.trailingTypeSpec:
2400 if addSpace:
2401 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
2402 numChildren = len(signode)
2403 self.trailingTypeSpec.describe_signature(signode, mode, env,
2404 symbol=symbol)
2405 addSpace = len(signode) != numChildren
2406  
2407 if len(str(self.rightSpecs)) > 0:
2408 if addSpace:
2409 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
2410 self.rightSpecs.describe_signature(signode, env, symbol)

2416 class ASTArray(ASTBase):
2417 def __init__(self, size: ASTExpression):
2418 self.size = size
2419  
2420 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
2421 if self.size:
2422 return '[' + transform(self.size) + ']'
2423 else:
2424 return '[]'
2425  
2426 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
2427 if version == 1:
2428 return 'A'
2429 if version == 2:
2430 if self.size:
2431 return 'A' + str(self.size) + '_'
2432 else:
2433 return 'A_'
2434 if self.size:
2435 return 'A' + self.size.get_id(version) + '_'
2436 else:
2437 return 'A_'
2438  
2439 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
2440 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
2441 verify_description_mode(mode)
2442 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('[', '[')
2443 if self.size:
2444 self.size.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol)
2445 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(']', ']')

2492 class ASTDeclaratorNameParamQual(ASTDeclarator):
2493 def __init__(self, declId: ASTNestedName,
2494 arrayOps: list[ASTArray],
2495 paramQual: ASTParametersQualifiers) -> None:
2496 self.declId = declId
2497 self.arrayOps = arrayOps
2498 self.paramQual = paramQual
2499  
2500 @property
2501 def name(self) -> ASTNestedName:
2502 return self.declId
2503  
2504 @name.setter
2505 def name(self, name: ASTNestedName) -> None:
2506 self.declId = name
2507  
2508 @property
2509 def isPack(self) -> bool:
2510 return False
2511  
2512 @property
2513 def function_params(self) -> list[ASTFunctionParameter]:
2514 return self.paramQual.function_params
2515  
2516 @property
2517 def trailingReturn(self) -> ASTType:
2518 return self.paramQual.trailingReturn
2519  
2520 # only the modifiers for a function, e.g.,
2521 def get_modifiers_id(self, version: int) -> str:
2522 # cv-qualifiers
2523 if self.paramQual:
2524 return self.paramQual.get_modifiers_id(version)
2525 raise Exception("This should only be called on a function: %s" % self)
2526  
2527 def get_param_id(self, version: int) -> str: # only the parameters (if any)
2528 if self.paramQual:
2529 return self.paramQual.get_param_id(version)
2530 else:
2531 return ''
2532  
2533 def get_ptr_suffix_id(self, version: int) -> str: # only the array specifiers
2534 return ''.join(a.get_id(version) for a in self.arrayOps)
2535  
2536 def get_type_id(self, version: int, returnTypeId: str) -> str:
2537 assert version >= 2
2538 res = []
2539 # TODO: can we actually have both array ops and paramQual?
2540 res.append(self.get_ptr_suffix_id(version))
2541 if self.paramQual:
2542 res.append(self.get_modifiers_id(version))
2543 res.append('F')
2544 res.append(returnTypeId)
2545 res.append(self.get_param_id(version))
2546 res.append('E')
2547 else:
2548 res.append(returnTypeId)
2549 return ''.join(res)
2550

2552  
2553 def require_space_after_declSpecs(self) -> bool:
2554 return self.declId is not None
2555  
2556 def is_function_type(self) -> bool:
2557 return self.paramQual is not None
2558  
2559 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
2560 res = []
2561 if self.declId:
2562 res.append(transform(self.declId))
2563 for op in self.arrayOps:
2564 res.append(transform(op))
2565 if self.paramQual:
2566 res.append(transform(self.paramQual))
2567 return ''.join(res)
2568  
2569 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
2570 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
2571 verify_description_mode(mode)
2572 if self.declId:
2573 self.declId.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
2574 for op in self.arrayOps:
2575 op.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
2576 if self.paramQual:
2577 self.paramQual.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)

2593 def get_param_id(self, version: int) -> str: # only the parameters (if any)
2594 return ''
2595  
2596 def get_ptr_suffix_id(self, version: int) -> str: # only the array specifiers
2597 return ''
2598

2600  
2601 def require_space_after_declSpecs(self) -> bool:
2602 return self.declId is not None
2603  
2604 def is_function_type(self) -> bool:
2605 return False
2606

2608 res = []
2609 if self.declId:
2610 res.append(transform(self.declId))
2611 res.append(" : ")
2612 res.append(transform(self.size))
2613 return ''.join(res)
2614

2616 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
2617 verify_description_mode(mode)
2618 if self.declId:
2619 self.declId.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
2620 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
2621 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(':', ':')
2622 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
2623 self.size.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)

2626 class ASTDeclaratorPtr(ASTDeclarator):
2627 def __init__(self, next: ASTDeclarator, volatile: bool, const: bool,

2631 self.volatile = volatile
2632 self.const = const

2637 return self.next.name

2641 self.next.name = name

2649 return self.next.function_params

2658 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
2659 res = ['*']
2660 res.append(transform(self.attrs))
2661 if len(self.attrs) != 0 and (self.volatile or self.const):
2662 res.append(' ')
2663 if self.volatile:
2664 res.append('volatile')
2665 if self.const:
2666 if self.volatile:
2667 res.append(' ')
2668 res.append('const')
2669 if self.const or self.volatile or len(self.attrs) > 0:
2670 if self.next.require_space_after_declSpecs():
2671 res.append(' ')
2672 res.append(transform(self.next))

2682 if version == 1:
2683 res = ['P']

2685 res.append('V')
2686 if self.const:
2687 res.append('C')
2688 res.append(self.next.get_ptr_suffix_id(version))
2689 return ''.join(res)
2690  
2691 res = [self.next.get_ptr_suffix_id(version)]
2692 res.append('P')
2693 if self.volatile:
2694 res.append('V')
2695 if self.const:
2696 res.append('C')
2697 return ''.join(res)

2699 def get_type_id(self, version: int, returnTypeId: str) -> str:
2700 # ReturnType *next, so we are part of the return type of 'next
2701 res = ['P']
2702 if self.volatile:
2703 res.append('V')
2704 if self.const:
2705 res.append('C')
2706 res.append(returnTypeId)
2707 return self.next.get_type_id(version, returnTypeId=''.join(res))

2716 self.attrs.describe_signature(signode)
2717 if len(self.attrs) != 0 and (self.volatile or self.const):
2718 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
2719

2723 _add_anno(signode, 'volatile')

2727 _add_anno(signode, 'const')
2728 if self.const or self.volatile or len(self.attrs) > 0:
2729 if self.next.require_space_after_declSpecs():

3054 class ASTParenExprList(ASTBaseParenExprList):
3055 def __init__(self, exprs: list[ASTExpression | ASTBracedInitList]) -> None:
3056 self.exprs = exprs

3059 return "pi%sE" % ''.join(e.get_id(version) for e in self.exprs)
3060  
3061 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3062 exprs = [transform(e) for e in self.exprs]
3063 return '(%s)' % ', '.join(exprs)

3066 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3067 verify_description_mode(mode)
3068 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('(', '(')
3069 first = True
3070 for e in self.exprs:
3071 if not first:
3072 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
3073 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3074 else:
3075 first = False
3076 e.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
3077 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(')', ')')

3103 class ASTType(ASTBase):
3104 def __init__(self, declSpecs: ASTDeclSpecs, decl: ASTDeclarator) -> None:
3105 assert declSpecs
3106 assert decl
3107 self.declSpecs = declSpecs
3108 self.decl = decl
3109  
3110 @property
3111 def name(self) -> ASTNestedName:
3112 return self.decl.name
3113  
3114 @name.setter
3115 def name(self, name: ASTNestedName) -> None:
3116 self.decl.name = name
3117  
3118 @property
3119 def isPack(self) -> bool:
3120 return self.decl.isPack
3121  
3122 @property
3123 def function_params(self) -> list[ASTFunctionParameter]:
3124 return self.decl.function_params
3125  
3126 @property
3127 def trailingReturn(self) -> ASTType:
3128 return self.decl.trailingReturn
3129  
3130 def get_id(self, version: int, objectType: str | None = None,
3131 symbol: Symbol | None = None) -> str:
3132 if version == 1:
3133 res = []
3134 if objectType: # needs the name
3135 if objectType == 'function': # also modifiers
3136 res.append(symbol.get_full_nested_name().get_id(version))
3137 res.append(self.decl.get_param_id(version))
3138 res.append(self.decl.get_modifiers_id(version))
3139 if (self.declSpecs.leftSpecs.constexpr or
3140 (self.declSpecs.rightSpecs and
3141 self.declSpecs.rightSpecs.constexpr)):
3142 res.append('CE')
3143 elif objectType == 'type': # just the name
3144 res.append(symbol.get_full_nested_name().get_id(version))
3145 else:
3146 raise AssertionError(objectType)
3147 else: # only type encoding
3148 if self.decl.is_function_type():
3149 raise NoOldIdError
3150 res.append(self.declSpecs.get_id(version))
3151 res.append(self.decl.get_ptr_suffix_id(version))
3152 res.append(self.decl.get_param_id(version))
3153 return ''.join(res)
3154 # other versions
3155 res = []
3156 if objectType: # needs the name
3157 if objectType == 'function': # also modifiers
3158 modifiers = self.decl.get_modifiers_id(version)
3159 res.append(symbol.get_full_nested_name().get_id(version, modifiers))
3160 if version >= 4:
3161 # with templates we need to mangle the return type in as well
3162 templ = symbol.declaration.templatePrefix
3163 if templ is not None:
3164 typeId = self.decl.get_ptr_suffix_id(version)
3165 if self.trailingReturn:
3166 returnTypeId = self.trailingReturn.get_id(version)
3167 else:
3168 returnTypeId = self.declSpecs.get_id(version)
3169 res.append(typeId)
3170 res.append(returnTypeId)
3171 res.append(self.decl.get_param_id(version))
3172 elif objectType == 'type': # just the name
3173 res.append(symbol.get_full_nested_name().get_id(version))
3174 else:
3175 raise AssertionError(objectType)
3176 else: # only type encoding
3177 # the 'returnType' of a non-function type is simply just the last
3178 # type, i.e., for 'int*' it is 'int'
3179 returnTypeId = self.declSpecs.get_id(version)
3180 typeId = self.decl.get_type_id(version, returnTypeId)
3181 res.append(typeId)
3182 return ''.join(res)
3183  
3184 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3185 res = []
3186 declSpecs = transform(self.declSpecs)
3187 res.append(declSpecs)
3188 if self.decl.require_space_after_declSpecs() and len(declSpecs) > 0:
3189 res.append(' ')
3190 res.append(transform(self.decl))
3191 return ''.join(res)
3192  
3193 def get_type_declaration_prefix(self) -> str:
3194 if self.declSpecs.trailingTypeSpec:
3195 return 'typedef'
3196 else:
3197 return 'type'
3198  
3199 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3200 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3201 verify_description_mode(mode)
3202 self.declSpecs.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol)
3203 if (self.decl.require_space_after_declSpecs() and
3204 len(str(self.declSpecs)) > 0):
3205 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3206 # for parameters that don't really declare new names we get 'markType',
3207 # this should not be propagated, but be 'noneIsName'.
3208 if mode == 'markType':
3209 mode = 'noneIsName'
3210 self.decl.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
3211  
3212  
3213 class ASTTemplateParamConstrainedTypeWithInit(ASTBase):
3214 def __init__(self, type: ASTType, init: ASTType) -> None:
3215 assert type
3216 self.type = type
3217 self.init = init
3218  
3219 @property
3220 def name(self) -> ASTNestedName:
3221 return self.type.name
3222  
3223 @property
3224 def isPack(self) -> bool:
3225 return self.type.isPack
3226  
3227 def get_id(
3228 self, version: int, objectType: str | None = None, symbol: Symbol | None = None,
3229 ) -> str:
3230 # this is not part of the normal name mangling in C++
3231 assert version >= 2
3232 if symbol:
3233 # the anchor will be our parent
3234 return symbol.parent.declaration.get_id(version, prefixed=False)
3235 else:
3236 return self.type.get_id(version)
3237  
3238 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3239 res = transform(self.type)
3240 if self.init:
3241 res += " = "
3242 res += transform(self.init)
3243 return res
3244  
3245 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3246 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3247 self.type.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
3248 if self.init:
3249 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3250 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('=', '=')
3251 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3252 self.init.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)

3356 class ASTBaseClass(ASTBase):

3359 self.name = name
3360 self.visibility = visibility
3361 self.virtual = virtual
3362 self.pack = pack
3363  
3364 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3365 res = []
3366 if self.visibility is not None:
3367 res.append(self.visibility)
3368 res.append(' ')
3369 if self.virtual:
3370 res.append('virtual ')
3371 res.append(transform(self.name))
3372 if self.pack:
3373 res.append('...')
3374 return ''.join(res)
3375  
3376 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3377 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3378 verify_description_mode(mode)
3379 if self.visibility is not None:
3380 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.visibility,
3381 self.visibility)
3382 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3383 if self.virtual:
3384 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('virtual', 'virtual')
3385 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3386 self.name.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol=symbol)
3387 if self.pack:
3388 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('...', '...')

3391 class ASTClass(ASTBase):
3392 def __init__(self, name: ASTNestedName, final: bool, bases: list[ASTBaseClass],
3393 attrs: ASTAttributeList) -> None:
3394 self.name = name
3395 self.final = final
3396 self.bases = bases
3397 self.attrs = attrs
3398  
3399 def get_id(self, version: int, objectType: str, symbol: Symbol) -> str:
3400 return symbol.get_full_nested_name().get_id(version)
3401  
3402 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3403 res = []
3404 res.append(transform(self.attrs))
3405 if len(self.attrs) != 0:
3406 res.append(' ')
3407 res.append(transform(self.name))
3408 if self.final:
3409 res.append(' final')
3410 if len(self.bases) > 0:
3411 res.append(' : ')
3412 first = True
3413 for b in self.bases:
3414 if not first:
3415 res.append(', ')
3416 first = False
3417 res.append(transform(b))
3418 return ''.join(res)
3419  
3420 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3421 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3422 verify_description_mode(mode)
3423 self.attrs.describe_signature(signode)
3424 if len(self.attrs) != 0:
3425 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3426 self.name.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol=symbol)
3427 if self.final:
3428 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3429 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('final', 'final')
3430 if len(self.bases) > 0:
3431 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3432 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(':', ':')
3433 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3434 for b in self.bases:
3435 b.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol=symbol)
3436 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
3437 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3438 signode.pop()
3439 signode.pop()

3572 class ASTTemplateKeyParamPackIdDefault(ASTTemplateParam):
3573 def __init__(self, key: str, identifier: ASTIdentifier,
3574 parameterPack: bool, default: ASTType) -> None:
3575 assert key
3576 if parameterPack:
3577 assert default is None
3578 self.key = key
3579 self.identifier = identifier
3580 self.parameterPack = parameterPack
3581 self.default = default
3582  
3583 def get_identifier(self) -> ASTIdentifier:
3584 return self.identifier
3585  
3586 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
3587 assert version >= 2
3588 # this is not part of the normal name mangling in C++
3589 res = []
3590 if self.parameterPack:
3591 res.append('Dp')
3592 else:
3593 res.append('0') # we need to put something
3594 return ''.join(res)
3595  
3596 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3597 res = [self.key]
3598 if self.parameterPack:
3599 if self.identifier:
3600 res.append(' ')
3601 res.append('...')
3602 if self.identifier:
3603 if not self.parameterPack:
3604 res.append(' ')
3605 res.append(transform(self.identifier))
3606 if self.default:
3607 res.append(' = ')
3608 res.append(transform(self.default))
3609 return ''.join(res)
3610  
3611 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3612 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3613 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.key, self.key)
3614 if self.parameterPack:
3615 if self.identifier:
3616 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3617 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('...', '...')
3618 if self.identifier:
3619 if not self.parameterPack:
3620 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3621 self.identifier.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, '', '', symbol)
3622 if self.default:
3623 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3624 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('=', '=')
3625 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3626 self.default.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol)

3706 class ASTTemplateParamNonType(ASTTemplateParam):

3721 return self.param.isPack or self.parameterPack
3722  
3723 def get_identifier(self) -> ASTIdentifier:
3724 name = self.param.name
3725 if name:
3726 assert len(name.names) == 1
3727 assert name.names[0].identOrOp
3728 assert not name.names[0].templateArgs
3729 res = name.names[0].identOrOp
3730 assert isinstance(res, ASTIdentifier)
3731 return res
3732 else:
3733 return None
3734  
3735 def get_id(
3736 self, version: int, objectType: str | None = None, symbol: Symbol | None = None,
3737 ) -> str:
3738 assert version >= 2

3741 # the anchor will be our parent
3742 return symbol.parent.declaration.get_id(version, prefixed=None)
3743 else:
3744 res = '_'

3746 res += 'Dp'

3761  
3762 class ASTTemplateParams(ASTBase):
3763 def __init__(self, params: list[ASTTemplateParam],
3764 requiresClause: ASTRequiresClause | None) -> None:
3765 assert params is not None
3766 self.params = params
3767 self.requiresClause = requiresClause
3768  
3769 def get_id(self, version: int, excludeRequires: bool = False) -> str:
3770 assert version >= 2
3771 res = []
3772 res.append("I")
3773 for param in self.params:
3774 res.append(param.get_id(version))
3775 res.append("E")
3776 if not excludeRequires and self.requiresClause:
3777 res.append('IQ')
3778 res.append(self.requiresClause.expr.get_id(version))
3779 res.append('E')
3780 return ''.join(res)
3781  
3782 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3783 res = []
3784 res.append("template<")
3785 res.append(", ".join(transform(a) for a in self.params))
3786 res.append("> ")
3787 if self.requiresClause is not None:
3788 res.append(transform(self.requiresClause))
3789 res.append(" ")
3790 return ''.join(res)
3791  
3792 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3793 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3794 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('template', 'template')
3795 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('<', '<')
3796 first = True
3797 for param in self.params:
3798 if not first:
3799 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
3800 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3801 first = False
3802 param.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
3803 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('>', '>')
3804 if self.requiresClause is not None:
3805 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3806 self.requiresClause.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
3807  
3808 def describe_signature_as_introducer(
3809 self, parentNode: desc_signature, mode: str, env: BuildEnvironment,
3810 symbol: Symbol, lineSpec: bool) -> None:
3811 def makeLine(parentNode: desc_signature) -> addnodes.desc_signature_line:
3812 signode = addnodes.desc_signature_line()
3813 parentNode += signode
3814 signode.sphinx_line_type = 'templateParams'
3815 return signode
3816 lineNode = makeLine(parentNode)
3817 lineNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('template', 'template')
3818 lineNode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('<', '<')
3819 first = True
3820 for param in self.params:
3821 if not first:
3822 lineNode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
3823 lineNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3824 first = False
3825 if lineSpec:
3826 lineNode = makeLine(parentNode)
3827 param.describe_signature(lineNode, mode, env, symbol)
3828 if lineSpec and not first:
3829 lineNode = makeLine(parentNode)
3830 lineNode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('>', '>')
3831 if self.requiresClause:
3832 reqNode = addnodes.desc_signature_line()
3833 reqNode.sphinx_line_type = 'requiresClause'
3834 parentNode += reqNode
3835 self.requiresClause.describe_signature(reqNode, 'markType', env, symbol)

3883 if self.parameterPack:
3884 res.append('...')
3885 res.append(transform(self.identifier))
3886 return ''.join(res)
3887  
3888 def describe_signature(self, signode: TextElement, mode: str,
3889 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3890 if self.parameterPack:
3891 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('...', '...')
3892 self.identifier.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, '', '', symbol)
3893  
3894  
3895 class ASTTemplateIntroduction(ASTBase):
3896 def __init__(self, concept: ASTNestedName,
3897 params: list[ASTTemplateIntroductionParameter]) -> None:
3898 assert len(params) > 0
3899 self.concept = concept
3900 self.params = params
3901  
3902 def get_id(self, version: int) -> str:
3903 assert version >= 2
3904 # first do the same as a normal template parameter list
3905 res = []
3906 res.append("I")
3907 for param in self.params:
3908 res.append(param.get_id(version))
3909 res.append("E")
3910 # let's use X expr E, which is otherwise for constant template args
3911 res.append("X")
3912 res.append(self.concept.get_id(version))
3913 res.append("I")
3914 for param in self.params:
3915 res.append(param.get_id_as_arg(version))
3916 res.append("E")
3917 res.append("E")
3918 return ''.join(res)
3919  
3920 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3921 res = []
3922 res.append(transform(self.concept))
3923 res.append('{')
3924 res.append(', '.join(transform(param) for param in self.params))
3925 res.append('} ')
3926 return ''.join(res)
3927  
3928 def describe_signature_as_introducer(
3929 self, parentNode: desc_signature, mode: str,
3930 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol, lineSpec: bool) -> None:
3931 # Note: 'lineSpec' has no effect on template introductions.
3932 signode = addnodes.desc_signature_line()
3933 parentNode += signode
3934 signode.sphinx_line_type = 'templateIntroduction'
3935 self.concept.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', env, symbol)
3936 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('{', '{')
3937 first = True
3938 for param in self.params:
3939 if not first:
3940 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(',', ',')
3941 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3942 first = False
3943 param.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
3944 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation('}', '}')
3945

3949 class ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix(ASTBase):
3950 def __init__(self,
3951 templates: list[ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction]) -> None:
3952 # templates is None means it's an explicit instantiation of a variable
3953 self.templates = templates
3954  
3955 def get_requires_clause_in_last(self) -> ASTRequiresClause | None:
3956 if self.templates is None:
3957 return None
3958 lastList = self.templates[-1]
3959 if not isinstance(lastList, ASTTemplateParams):
3960 return None
3961 return lastList.requiresClause # which may be None
3962  
3963 def get_id_except_requires_clause_in_last(self, version: int) -> str:
3964 assert version >= 2
3965 # This is not part of the Itanium ABI mangling system.
3966 res = []
3967 lastIndex = len(self.templates) - 1
3968 for i, t in enumerate(self.templates):
3969 if isinstance(t, ASTTemplateParams):
3970 res.append(t.get_id(version, excludeRequires=(i == lastIndex)))
3971 else:
3972 res.append(t.get_id(version))
3973 return ''.join(res)
3974  
3975 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3976 res = []
3977 for t in self.templates:
3978 res.append(transform(t))
3979 return ''.join(res)
3980  
3981 def describe_signature(self, signode: desc_signature, mode: str,
3982 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol, lineSpec: bool) -> None:
3983 verify_description_mode(mode)
3984 for t in self.templates:
3985 t.describe_signature_as_introducer(signode, 'lastIsName', env, symbol, lineSpec)
3986

3990 self.expr = expr
3991  
3992 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
3993 return 'requires ' + transform(self.expr)
3994  
3995 def describe_signature(self, signode: nodes.TextElement, mode: str,
3996 env: BuildEnvironment, symbol: Symbol) -> None:
3997 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('requires', 'requires')
3998 signode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
3999 self.expr.describe_signature(signode, mode, env, symbol)
