4005 class ASTDeclaration(ASTBase):
4006 def __init__(self, objectType: str, directiveType: str | None = None,
4007 visibility: str | None = None,
4008 templatePrefix: ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix | None = None,
4009 declaration: Any = None,
4010 trailingRequiresClause: ASTRequiresClause | None = None,
4011 semicolon: bool = False) -> None:
4012 self.objectType = objectType
4013 self.directiveType = directiveType
4014 self.visibility = visibility
4015 self.templatePrefix = templatePrefix
4016 self.declaration = declaration
4017 self.trailingRequiresClause = trailingRequiresClause
4018 self.semicolon = semicolon
4019  
4020 self.symbol: Symbol = None
4021 # set by CPPObject._add_enumerator_to_parent
4022 self.enumeratorScopedSymbol: Symbol = None
4023  
4024 def clone(self) -> ASTDeclaration:
4025 templatePrefixClone = self.templatePrefix.clone() if self.templatePrefix else None
4026 trailingRequiresClasueClone = self.trailingRequiresClause.clone() \
4027 if self.trailingRequiresClause else None
4028 return ASTDeclaration(self.objectType, self.directiveType, self.visibility,
4029 templatePrefixClone,
4030 self.declaration.clone(), trailingRequiresClasueClone,
4031 self.semicolon)
4032  
4033 @property
4034 def name(self) -> ASTNestedName:
4035 return self.declaration.name
4036  
4037 @property
4038 def function_params(self) -> list[ASTFunctionParameter]:
4039 if self.objectType != 'function':
4040 return None
4041 return self.declaration.function_params
4042  
4043 def get_id(self, version: int, prefixed: bool = True) -> str:
4044 if version == 1:
4045 if self.templatePrefix or self.trailingRequiresClause:
4046 raise NoOldIdError
4047 if self.objectType == 'enumerator' and self.enumeratorScopedSymbol:
4048 return self.enumeratorScopedSymbol.declaration.get_id(version)
4049 return self.declaration.get_id(version, self.objectType, self.symbol)
4050 # version >= 2
4051 if self.objectType == 'enumerator' and self.enumeratorScopedSymbol:
4052 return self.enumeratorScopedSymbol.declaration.get_id(version, prefixed)
4053 if prefixed:
4054 res = [_id_prefix[version]]
4055 else:
4056 res = []
4057 # (See also https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/pull/10286#issuecomment-1168102147)
4058 # The first implementation of requires clauses only supported a single clause after the
4059 # template prefix, and no trailing clause. It put the ID after the template parameter
4060 # list, i.e.,
4061 # "I" + template_parameter_list_id + "E" + "IQ" + requires_clause_id + "E"
4062 # but the second implementation associates the requires clause with each list, i.e.,
4063 # "I" + template_parameter_list_id + "IQ" + requires_clause_id + "E" + "E"
4064 # To avoid making a new ID version, we make an exception for the last requires clause
4065 # in the template prefix, and still put it in the end.
4066 # As we now support trailing requires clauses we add that as if it was a conjunction.
4067 if self.templatePrefix is not None:
4068 res.append(self.templatePrefix.get_id_except_requires_clause_in_last(version))
4069 requiresClauseInLast = self.templatePrefix.get_requires_clause_in_last()
4070 else:
4071 requiresClauseInLast = None
4072  
4073 if requiresClauseInLast or self.trailingRequiresClause:
4074 if version < 4:
4075 raise NoOldIdError
4076 res.append('IQ')
4077 if requiresClauseInLast and self.trailingRequiresClause:
4078 # make a conjunction of them
4079 res.append('aa')
4080 if requiresClauseInLast:
4081 res.append(requiresClauseInLast.expr.get_id(version))
4082 if self.trailingRequiresClause:
4083 res.append(self.trailingRequiresClause.expr.get_id(version))
4084 res.append('E')
4085 res.append(self.declaration.get_id(version, self.objectType, self.symbol))
4086 return ''.join(res)
4087  
4088 def get_newest_id(self) -> str:
4089 return self.get_id(_max_id, True)
4090  
4091 def _stringify(self, transform: StringifyTransform) -> str:
4092 res = []
4093 if self.visibility and self.visibility != "public":
4094 res.append(self.visibility)
4095 res.append(' ')
4096 if self.templatePrefix:
4097 res.append(transform(self.templatePrefix))
4098 res.append(transform(self.declaration))
4099 if self.trailingRequiresClause:
4100 res.append(' ')
4101 res.append(transform(self.trailingRequiresClause))
4102 if self.semicolon:
4103 res.append(';')
4104 return ''.join(res)
4105  
4106 def describe_signature(self, signode: desc_signature, mode: str,
4107 env: BuildEnvironment, options: dict) -> None:
4108 verify_description_mode(mode)
4109 assert self.symbol
4110 # The caller of the domain added a desc_signature node.
4111 # Always enable multiline:
4112 signode['is_multiline'] = True
4113 # Put each line in a desc_signature_line node.
4114 mainDeclNode = addnodes.desc_signature_line()
4115 mainDeclNode.sphinx_line_type = 'declarator'
4116 mainDeclNode['add_permalink'] = not self.symbol.isRedeclaration
4117  
4118 if self.templatePrefix:
4119 self.templatePrefix.describe_signature(signode, mode, env,
4120 symbol=self.symbol,
4121 lineSpec=options.get('tparam-line-spec'))
4122 signode += mainDeclNode
4123 if self.visibility and self.visibility != "public":
4124 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.visibility, self.visibility)
4125 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4126 if self.objectType == 'type':
4127 prefix = self.declaration.get_type_declaration_prefix()
4128 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(prefix, prefix)
4129 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4130 elif self.objectType == 'concept':
4131 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('concept', 'concept')
4132 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4133 elif self.objectType in {'member', 'function'}:
4134 pass
4135 elif self.objectType == 'class':
4136 assert self.directiveType in ('class', 'struct')
4137 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword(self.directiveType, self.directiveType)
4138 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4139 elif self.objectType == 'union':
4140 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('union', 'union')
4141 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4142 elif self.objectType == 'enum':
4143 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('enum', 'enum')
4144 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4145 if self.directiveType == 'enum-class':
4146 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('class', 'class')
4147 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4148 elif self.directiveType == 'enum-struct':
4149 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('struct', 'struct')
4150 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4151 else:
4152 assert self.directiveType == 'enum', self.directiveType
4153 elif self.objectType == 'enumerator':
4154 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_keyword('enumerator', 'enumerator')
4155 mainDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_space()
4156 else:
4157 raise AssertionError(self.objectType)
4158 self.declaration.describe_signature(mainDeclNode, mode, env, self.symbol)
4159 lastDeclNode = mainDeclNode
4160 if self.trailingRequiresClause:
4161 trailingReqNode = addnodes.desc_signature_line()
4162 trailingReqNode.sphinx_line_type = 'trailingRequiresClause'
4163 signode.append(trailingReqNode)
4164 lastDeclNode = trailingReqNode
4165 self.trailingRequiresClause.describe_signature(
4166 trailingReqNode, 'markType', env, self.symbol)
4167 if self.semicolon:
4168 lastDeclNode += addnodes.desc_sig_punctuation(';', ';')
4169

4196 class LookupKey:
4197 def __init__(self, data: list[tuple[ASTNestedNameElement,
4198 ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction,
4199 str]]) -> None:
4200 self.data = data
4201  
4202  
4203 def _is_specialization(templateParams: ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction,
4204 templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs) -> bool:
4205 # Checks if `templateArgs` does not exactly match `templateParams`.
4206 # the names of the template parameters must be given exactly as args
4207 # and params that are packs must in the args be the name expanded
4208 if len(templateParams.params) != len(templateArgs.args):
4209 return True
4210 # having no template params and no arguments is also a specialization
4211 if len(templateParams.params) == 0:
4212 return True
4213 for i in range(len(templateParams.params)):
4214 param = templateParams.params[i]
4215 arg = templateArgs.args[i]
4216 # TODO: doing this by string manipulation is probably not the most efficient
4217 paramName = str(param.name)
4218 argTxt = str(arg)
4219 isArgPackExpansion = argTxt.endswith('...')
4220 if param.isPack != isArgPackExpansion:
4221 return True
4222 argName = argTxt[:-3] if isArgPackExpansion else argTxt
4223 if paramName != argName:
4224 return True
4225 return False

4228 class Symbol:
4229 debug_indent = 0
4230 debug_indent_string = " "
4231 debug_lookup = False # overridden by the corresponding config value
4232 debug_show_tree = False # overridden by the corresponding config value
4233  
4234 def __copy__(self):
4235 raise AssertionError # shouldn't happen
4236  
4237 def __deepcopy__(self, memo):
4238 if self.parent:
4239 raise AssertionError # shouldn't happen
4240 # the domain base class makes a copy of the initial data, which is fine
4241 return Symbol(None, None, None, None, None, None, None)
4242  
4243 @staticmethod
4244 def debug_print(*args: Any) -> None:
4245 logger.debug(Symbol.debug_indent_string * Symbol.debug_indent, end="")
4246 logger.debug(*args)
4247  
4248 def _assert_invariants(self) -> None:
4249 if not self.parent:
4250 # parent == None means global scope, so declaration means a parent
4251 assert not self.identOrOp
4252 assert not self.templateParams
4253 assert not self.templateArgs
4254 assert not self.declaration
4255 assert not self.docname
4256 else:
4257 if self.declaration:
4258 assert self.docname
4259  
4260 def __setattr__(self, key: str, value: Any) -> None:
4261 if key == "children":
4262 raise AssertionError
4263 return super().__setattr__(key, value)
4264  
4265 def __init__(self, parent: Symbol | None,
4266 identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator | None,
4267 templateParams: ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction | None,
4268 templateArgs: Any, declaration: ASTDeclaration | None,
4269 docname: str | None, line: int | None) -> None:
4270 self.parent = parent
4271 # declarations in a single directive are linked together
4272 self.siblingAbove: Symbol | None = None
4273 self.siblingBelow: Symbol | None = None
4274 self.identOrOp = identOrOp
4275 # Ensure the same symbol for `A` is created for:
4276 #
4277 # .. cpp:class:: template <typename T> class A
4278 #
4279 # and
4280 #
4281 # .. cpp:function:: template <typename T> int A<T>::foo()
4282 if (templateArgs is not None and
4283 not _is_specialization(templateParams, templateArgs)):
4284 templateArgs = None
4285 self.templateParams = templateParams # template<templateParams>
4286 self.templateArgs = templateArgs # identifier<templateArgs>
4287 self.declaration = declaration
4288 self.docname = docname
4289 self.line = line
4290 self.isRedeclaration = False
4291 self._assert_invariants()
4292  
4293 # Remember to modify Symbol.remove if modifications to the parent change.
4294 self._children: list[Symbol] = []
4295 self._anonChildren: list[Symbol] = []
4296 # note: _children includes _anonChildren
4297 if self.parent:
4298 self.parent._children.append(self)
4299 if self.declaration:
4300 self.declaration.symbol = self
4301  
4302 # Do symbol addition after self._children has been initialised.
4303 self._add_template_and_function_params()
4304  
4305 def _fill_empty(self, declaration: ASTDeclaration, docname: str, line: int) -> None:
4306 self._assert_invariants()
4307 assert self.declaration is None
4308 assert self.docname is None
4309 assert self.line is None
4310 assert declaration is not None
4311 assert docname is not None
4312 assert line is not None
4313 self.declaration = declaration
4314 self.declaration.symbol = self
4315 self.docname = docname
4316 self.line = line
4317 self._assert_invariants()
4318 # and symbol addition should be done as well
4319 self._add_template_and_function_params()
4320  
4321 def _add_template_and_function_params(self) -> None:
4322 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4323 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4324 Symbol.debug_print("_add_template_and_function_params:")
4325 # Note: we may be called from _fill_empty, so the symbols we want
4326 # to add may actually already be present (as empty symbols).
4327  
4328 # add symbols for the template params
4329 if self.templateParams:
4330 for tp in self.templateParams.params:
4331 if not tp.get_identifier():
4332 continue
4333 # only add a declaration if we our self are from a declaration
4334 if self.declaration:
4335 decl = ASTDeclaration(objectType='templateParam', declaration=tp)
4336 else:
4337 decl = None
4338 nne = ASTNestedNameElement(tp.get_identifier(), None)
4339 nn = ASTNestedName([nne], [False], rooted=False)
4340 self._add_symbols(nn, [], decl, self.docname, self.line)
4341 # add symbols for function parameters, if any
4342 if self.declaration is not None and self.declaration.function_params is not None:
4343 for fp in self.declaration.function_params:
4344 if fp.arg is None:
4345 continue
4346 nn = fp.arg.name
4347 if nn is None:
4348 continue
4349 # (comparing to the template params: we have checked that we are a declaration)
4350 decl = ASTDeclaration(objectType='functionParam', declaration=fp)
4351 assert not nn.rooted
4352 assert len(nn.names) == 1
4353 self._add_symbols(nn, [], decl, self.docname, self.line)
4354 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4355 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4356  
4357 def remove(self) -> None:
4358 if self.parent is None:
4359 return
4360 assert self in self.parent._children
4361 self.parent._children.remove(self)
4362 self.parent = None
4363  
4364 def clear_doc(self, docname: str) -> None:
4365 newChildren: list[Symbol] = []
4366 for sChild in self._children:
4367 sChild.clear_doc(docname)
4368 if sChild.declaration and sChild.docname == docname:
4369 sChild.declaration = None
4370 sChild.docname = None
4371 sChild.line = None
4372 if sChild.siblingAbove is not None:
4373 sChild.siblingAbove.siblingBelow = sChild.siblingBelow
4374 if sChild.siblingBelow is not None:
4375 sChild.siblingBelow.siblingAbove = sChild.siblingAbove
4376 sChild.siblingAbove = None
4377 sChild.siblingBelow = None
4378 newChildren.append(sChild)
4379 self._children = newChildren
4380  
4381 def get_all_symbols(self) -> Iterator[Any]:
4382 yield self
4383 for sChild in self._children:
4384 yield from sChild.get_all_symbols()
4385  
4386 @property
4387 def children_recurse_anon(self) -> Generator[Symbol, None, None]:
4388 for c in self._children:
4389 yield c
4390 if not c.identOrOp.is_anon():
4391 continue
4392  
4393 yield from c.children_recurse_anon
4394  
4395 def get_lookup_key(self) -> LookupKey:
4396 # The pickle files for the environment and for each document are distinct.
4397 # The environment has all the symbols, but the documents has xrefs that
4398 # must know their scope. A lookup key is essentially a specification of
4399 # how to find a specific symbol.
4400 symbols = []
4401 s = self
4402 while s.parent:
4403 symbols.append(s)
4404 s = s.parent
4405 symbols.reverse()
4406 key = []
4407 for s in symbols:
4408 nne = ASTNestedNameElement(s.identOrOp, s.templateArgs)
4409 if s.declaration is not None:
4410 key.append((nne, s.templateParams, s.declaration.get_newest_id()))
4411 else:
4412 key.append((nne, s.templateParams, None))
4413 return LookupKey(key)
4414  
4415 def get_full_nested_name(self) -> ASTNestedName:
4416 symbols = []
4417 s = self
4418 while s.parent:
4419 symbols.append(s)
4420 s = s.parent
4421 symbols.reverse()
4422 names = []
4423 templates = []
4424 for s in symbols:
4425 names.append(ASTNestedNameElement(s.identOrOp, s.templateArgs))
4426 templates.append(False)
4427 return ASTNestedName(names, templates, rooted=False)
4428  
4429 def _find_first_named_symbol(self, identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
4430 templateParams: Any, templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs,
4431 templateShorthand: bool, matchSelf: bool,
4432 recurseInAnon: bool, correctPrimaryTemplateArgs: bool,
4433 ) -> Symbol:
4434 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4435 Symbol.debug_print("_find_first_named_symbol ->")
4436 res = self._find_named_symbols(identOrOp, templateParams, templateArgs,
4437 templateShorthand, matchSelf, recurseInAnon,
4438 correctPrimaryTemplateArgs,
4439 searchInSiblings=False)
4440 try:
4441 return next(res)
4442 except StopIteration:
4443 return None
4444  
4445 def _find_named_symbols(self, identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
4446 templateParams: Any, templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs,
4447 templateShorthand: bool, matchSelf: bool,
4448 recurseInAnon: bool, correctPrimaryTemplateArgs: bool,
4449 searchInSiblings: bool) -> Iterator[Symbol]:
4450 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4451 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4452 Symbol.debug_print("_find_named_symbols:")
4453 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4454 Symbol.debug_print("self:")
4455 logger.debug(self.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4456 Symbol.debug_print("identOrOp: ", identOrOp)
4457 Symbol.debug_print("templateParams: ", templateParams)
4458 Symbol.debug_print("templateArgs: ", templateArgs)
4459 Symbol.debug_print("templateShorthand: ", templateShorthand)
4460 Symbol.debug_print("matchSelf: ", matchSelf)
4461 Symbol.debug_print("recurseInAnon: ", recurseInAnon)
4462 Symbol.debug_print("correctPrimaryTemplateAargs:", correctPrimaryTemplateArgs)
4463 Symbol.debug_print("searchInSiblings: ", searchInSiblings)
4464  
4465 if correctPrimaryTemplateArgs:
4466 if templateParams is not None and templateArgs is not None:
4467 # If both are given, but it's not a specialization, then do lookup as if
4468 # there is no argument list.
4469 # For example: template<typename T> int A<T>::var;
4470 if not _is_specialization(templateParams, templateArgs):
4471 templateArgs = None
4472  
4473 def matches(s: Symbol) -> bool:
4474 if s.identOrOp != identOrOp:
4475 return False
4476 if (s.templateParams is None) != (templateParams is None):
4477 if templateParams is not None:
4478 # we query with params, they must match params
4479 return False
4480 if not templateShorthand:
4481 # we don't query with params, and we do care about them
4482 return False
4483 if templateParams:
4484 # TODO: do better comparison
4485 if str(s.templateParams) != str(templateParams):
4486 return False
4487 if (s.templateArgs is None) != (templateArgs is None):
4488 return False
4489 if s.templateArgs:
4490 # TODO: do better comparison
4491 if str(s.templateArgs) != str(templateArgs):
4492 return False
4493 return True
4494  
4495 def candidates() -> Generator[Symbol, None, None]:
4496 s = self
4497 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4498 Symbol.debug_print("searching in self:")
4499 logger.debug(s.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4500 while True:
4501 if matchSelf:
4502 yield s
4503 if recurseInAnon:
4504 yield from s.children_recurse_anon
4505 else:
4506 yield from s._children
4507  
4508 if s.siblingAbove is None:
4509 break
4510 s = s.siblingAbove
4511 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4512 Symbol.debug_print("searching in sibling:")
4513 logger.debug(s.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4514  
4515 for s in candidates():
4516 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4517 Symbol.debug_print("candidate:")
4518 logger.debug(s.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4519 if matches(s):
4520 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4521 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4522 Symbol.debug_print("matches")
4523 Symbol.debug_indent -= 3
4524 yield s
4525 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4526 Symbol.debug_indent += 2
4527 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4528 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4529  
4530 def _symbol_lookup(
4531 self,
4532 nestedName: ASTNestedName,
4533 templateDecls: list[Any],
4534 onMissingQualifiedSymbol: Callable[
4535 [Symbol, ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator, Any, ASTTemplateArgs], Symbol | None,
4536 ],
4537 strictTemplateParamArgLists: bool, ancestorLookupType: str,
4538 templateShorthand: bool, matchSelf: bool,
4539 recurseInAnon: bool, correctPrimaryTemplateArgs: bool,
4540 searchInSiblings: bool,
4541 ) -> SymbolLookupResult:
4542 # ancestorLookupType: if not None, specifies the target type of the lookup
4543 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4544 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4545 Symbol.debug_print("_symbol_lookup:")
4546 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4547 Symbol.debug_print("self:")
4548 logger.debug(self.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4549 Symbol.debug_print("nestedName: ", nestedName)
4550 Symbol.debug_print("templateDecls: ", ",".join(str(t) for t in templateDecls))
4551 Symbol.debug_print("strictTemplateParamArgLists:", strictTemplateParamArgLists)
4552 Symbol.debug_print("ancestorLookupType:", ancestorLookupType)
4553 Symbol.debug_print("templateShorthand: ", templateShorthand)
4554 Symbol.debug_print("matchSelf: ", matchSelf)
4555 Symbol.debug_print("recurseInAnon: ", recurseInAnon)
4556 Symbol.debug_print("correctPrimaryTemplateArgs: ", correctPrimaryTemplateArgs)
4557 Symbol.debug_print("searchInSiblings: ", searchInSiblings)
4558  
4559 if strictTemplateParamArgLists:
4560 # Each template argument list must have a template parameter list.
4561 # But to declare a template there must be an additional template parameter list.
4562 assert (nestedName.num_templates() == len(templateDecls) or
4563 nestedName.num_templates() + 1 == len(templateDecls))
4564 else:
4565 assert len(templateDecls) <= nestedName.num_templates() + 1
4566  
4567 names = nestedName.names
4568  
4569 # find the right starting point for lookup
4570 parentSymbol = self
4571 if nestedName.rooted:
4572 while parentSymbol.parent:
4573 parentSymbol = parentSymbol.parent
4574 if ancestorLookupType is not None:
4575 # walk up until we find the first identifier
4576 firstName = names[0]
4577 if not firstName.is_operator():
4578 while parentSymbol.parent:
4579 if parentSymbol.find_identifier(firstName.identOrOp,
4580 matchSelf=matchSelf,
4581 recurseInAnon=recurseInAnon,
4582 searchInSiblings=searchInSiblings):
4583 # if we are in the scope of a constructor but wants to
4584 # reference the class we need to walk one extra up
4585 if (len(names) == 1 and ancestorLookupType == 'class' and matchSelf and
4586 parentSymbol.parent and
4587 parentSymbol.parent.identOrOp == firstName.identOrOp):
4588 pass
4589 else:
4590 break
4591 parentSymbol = parentSymbol.parent
4592  
4593 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4594 Symbol.debug_print("starting point:")
4595 logger.debug(parentSymbol.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4596  
4597 # and now the actual lookup
4598 iTemplateDecl = 0
4599 for name in names[:-1]:
4600 identOrOp = name.identOrOp
4601 templateArgs = name.templateArgs
4602 if strictTemplateParamArgLists:
4603 # there must be a parameter list
4604 if templateArgs:
4605 assert iTemplateDecl < len(templateDecls)
4606 templateParams = templateDecls[iTemplateDecl]
4607 iTemplateDecl += 1
4608 else:
4609 templateParams = None
4610 else:
4611 # take the next template parameter list if there is one
4612 # otherwise it's ok
4613 if templateArgs and iTemplateDecl < len(templateDecls):
4614 templateParams = templateDecls[iTemplateDecl]
4615 iTemplateDecl += 1
4616 else:
4617 templateParams = None
4618  
4619 symbol = parentSymbol._find_first_named_symbol(
4620 identOrOp,
4621 templateParams, templateArgs,
4622 templateShorthand=templateShorthand,
4623 matchSelf=matchSelf,
4624 recurseInAnon=recurseInAnon,
4625 correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=correctPrimaryTemplateArgs)
4626 if symbol is None:
4627 symbol = onMissingQualifiedSymbol(parentSymbol, identOrOp,
4628 templateParams, templateArgs)
4629 if symbol is None:
4630 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4631 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4632 return None
4633 # We have now matched part of a nested name, and need to match more
4634 # so even if we should matchSelf before, we definitely shouldn't
4635 # even more. (see also issue #2666)
4636 matchSelf = False
4637 parentSymbol = symbol
4638  
4639 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4640 Symbol.debug_print("handle last name from:")
4641 logger.debug(parentSymbol.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
4642  
4643 # handle the last name
4644 name = names[-1]
4645 identOrOp = name.identOrOp
4646 templateArgs = name.templateArgs
4647 if iTemplateDecl < len(templateDecls):
4648 assert iTemplateDecl + 1 == len(templateDecls)
4649 templateParams = templateDecls[iTemplateDecl]
4650 else:
4651 assert iTemplateDecl == len(templateDecls)
4652 templateParams = None
4653  
4654 symbols = parentSymbol._find_named_symbols(
4655 identOrOp, templateParams, templateArgs,
4656 templateShorthand=templateShorthand, matchSelf=matchSelf,
4657 recurseInAnon=recurseInAnon, correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=False,
4658 searchInSiblings=searchInSiblings)
4659 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4660 symbols = list(symbols) # type: ignore[assignment]
4661 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4662 return SymbolLookupResult(symbols, parentSymbol,
4663 identOrOp, templateParams, templateArgs)
4664  
4665 def _add_symbols(self, nestedName: ASTNestedName, templateDecls: list[Any],
4666 declaration: ASTDeclaration, docname: str, line: int) -> Symbol:
4667 # Used for adding a whole path of symbols, where the last may or may not
4668 # be an actual declaration.
4669  
4670 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4671 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4672 Symbol.debug_print("_add_symbols:")
4673 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4674 Symbol.debug_print("tdecls:", ",".join(str(t) for t in templateDecls))
4675 Symbol.debug_print("nn: ", nestedName)
4676 Symbol.debug_print("decl: ", declaration)
4677 Symbol.debug_print(f"location: {docname}:{line}")
4678  
4679 def onMissingQualifiedSymbol(parentSymbol: Symbol,
4680 identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
4681 templateParams: Any, templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs,
4682 ) -> Symbol | None:
4683 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4684 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4685 Symbol.debug_print("_add_symbols, onMissingQualifiedSymbol:")
4686 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4687 Symbol.debug_print("templateParams:", templateParams)
4688 Symbol.debug_print("identOrOp: ", identOrOp)
4689 Symbol.debug_print("templateARgs: ", templateArgs)
4690 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4691 return Symbol(parent=parentSymbol, identOrOp=identOrOp,
4692 templateParams=templateParams,
4693 templateArgs=templateArgs, declaration=None,
4694 docname=None, line=None)
4695  
4696 lookupResult = self._symbol_lookup(nestedName, templateDecls,
4697 onMissingQualifiedSymbol,
4698 strictTemplateParamArgLists=True,
4699 ancestorLookupType=None,
4700 templateShorthand=False,
4701 matchSelf=False,
4702 recurseInAnon=False,
4703 correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=True,
4704 searchInSiblings=False)
4705 assert lookupResult is not None # we create symbols all the way, so that can't happen
4706 symbols = list(lookupResult.symbols)
4707 if len(symbols) == 0:
4708 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4709 Symbol.debug_print("_add_symbols, result, no symbol:")
4710 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4711 Symbol.debug_print("templateParams:", lookupResult.templateParams)
4712 Symbol.debug_print("identOrOp: ", lookupResult.identOrOp)
4713 Symbol.debug_print("templateArgs: ", lookupResult.templateArgs)
4714 Symbol.debug_print("declaration: ", declaration)
4715 Symbol.debug_print(f"location: {docname}:{line}")
4716 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4717 symbol = Symbol(parent=lookupResult.parentSymbol,
4718 identOrOp=lookupResult.identOrOp,
4719 templateParams=lookupResult.templateParams,
4720 templateArgs=lookupResult.templateArgs,
4721 declaration=declaration,
4722 docname=docname, line=line)
4723 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4724 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4725 return symbol
4726  
4727 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4728 Symbol.debug_print("_add_symbols, result, symbols:")
4729 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4730 Symbol.debug_print("number symbols:", len(symbols))
4731 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4732  
4733 if not declaration:
4734 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4735 Symbol.debug_print("no declaration")
4736 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4737 # good, just a scope creation
4738 # TODO: what if we have more than one symbol?
4739 return symbols[0]
4740  
4741 noDecl = []
4742 withDecl = []
4743 dupDecl = []
4744 for s in symbols:
4745 if s.declaration is None:
4746 noDecl.append(s)
4747 elif s.isRedeclaration:
4748 dupDecl.append(s)
4749 else:
4750 withDecl.append(s)
4751 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4752 Symbol.debug_print("#noDecl: ", len(noDecl))
4753 Symbol.debug_print("#withDecl:", len(withDecl))
4754 Symbol.debug_print("#dupDecl: ", len(dupDecl))
4755 # With partial builds we may start with a large symbol tree stripped of declarations.
4756 # Essentially any combination of noDecl, withDecl, and dupDecls seems possible.
4757 # TODO: make partial builds fully work. What should happen when the primary symbol gets
4758 # deleted, and other duplicates exist? The full document should probably be rebuild.
4759  
4760 # First check if one of those with a declaration matches.
4761 # If it's a function, we need to compare IDs,
4762 # otherwise there should be only one symbol with a declaration.
4763 def makeCandSymbol() -> Symbol:
4764 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4765 Symbol.debug_print("begin: creating candidate symbol")
4766 symbol = Symbol(parent=lookupResult.parentSymbol,
4767 identOrOp=lookupResult.identOrOp,
4768 templateParams=lookupResult.templateParams,
4769 templateArgs=lookupResult.templateArgs,
4770 declaration=declaration,
4771 docname=docname, line=line)
4772 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4773 Symbol.debug_print("end: creating candidate symbol")
4774 return symbol
4775 if len(withDecl) == 0:
4776 candSymbol = None
4777 else:
4778 candSymbol = makeCandSymbol()
4779  
4780 def handleDuplicateDeclaration(symbol: Symbol, candSymbol: Symbol) -> None:
4781 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4782 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4783 Symbol.debug_print("redeclaration")
4784 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4785 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4786 # Redeclaration of the same symbol.
4787 # Let the new one be there, but raise an error to the client
4788 # so it can use the real symbol as subscope.
4789 # This will probably result in a duplicate id warning.
4790 candSymbol.isRedeclaration = True
4791 raise _DuplicateSymbolError(symbol, declaration)
4792  
4793 if declaration.objectType != "function":
4794 assert len(withDecl) <= 1
4795 handleDuplicateDeclaration(withDecl[0], candSymbol)
4796 # (not reachable)
4797  
4798 # a function, so compare IDs
4799 candId = declaration.get_newest_id()
4800 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4801 Symbol.debug_print("candId:", candId)
4802 for symbol in withDecl:
4803 # but all existing must be functions as well,
4804 # otherwise we declare it to be a duplicate
4805 if symbol.declaration.objectType != 'function':
4806 handleDuplicateDeclaration(symbol, candSymbol)
4807 # (not reachable)
4808 oldId = symbol.declaration.get_newest_id()
4809 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4810 Symbol.debug_print("oldId: ", oldId)
4811 if candId == oldId:
4812 handleDuplicateDeclaration(symbol, candSymbol)
4813 # (not reachable)
4814 # no candidate symbol found with matching ID
4815 # if there is an empty symbol, fill that one
4816 if len(noDecl) == 0:
4817 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4818 Symbol.debug_print("no match, no empty")
4819 if candSymbol is not None:
4820 Symbol.debug_print("result is already created candSymbol")
4821 else:
4822 Symbol.debug_print("result is makeCandSymbol()")
4823 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4824 if candSymbol is not None:
4825 return candSymbol
4826 else:
4827 return makeCandSymbol()
4828 else:
4829 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4830 Symbol.debug_print(
4831 "no match, but fill an empty declaration, candSybmol is not None?:",
4832 candSymbol is not None,
4833 )
4834 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
4835 if candSymbol is not None:
4836 candSymbol.remove()
4837 # assert len(noDecl) == 1
4838 # TODO: enable assertion when we at some point find out how to do cleanup
4839 # for now, just take the first one, it should work fine ... right?
4840 symbol = noDecl[0]
4841 # If someone first opened the scope, and then later
4842 # declares it, e.g,
4843 # .. namespace:: Test
4844 # .. namespace:: nullptr
4845 # .. class:: Test
4846 symbol._fill_empty(declaration, docname, line)
4847 return symbol
4848  
4849 def merge_with(self, other: Symbol, docnames: list[str],
4850 env: BuildEnvironment) -> None:
4851 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4852 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4853 Symbol.debug_print("merge_with:")
4854 assert other is not None
4855  
4856 def unconditionalAdd(self, otherChild):
4857 # TODO: hmm, should we prune by docnames?
4858 self._children.append(otherChild)
4859 otherChild.parent = self
4860 otherChild._assert_invariants()
4861  
4862 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4863 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4864 for otherChild in other._children:
4865 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4866 Symbol.debug_print("otherChild:\n", otherChild.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent))
4867 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4868 if otherChild.isRedeclaration:
4869 unconditionalAdd(self, otherChild)
4870 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4871 Symbol.debug_print("isRedeclaration")
4872 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4873 continue
4874 candiateIter = self._find_named_symbols(
4875 identOrOp=otherChild.identOrOp,
4876 templateParams=otherChild.templateParams,
4877 templateArgs=otherChild.templateArgs,
4878 templateShorthand=False, matchSelf=False,
4879 recurseInAnon=False, correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=False,
4880 searchInSiblings=False)
4881 candidates = list(candiateIter)
4882  
4883 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4884 Symbol.debug_print("raw candidate symbols:", len(candidates))
4885 symbols = [s for s in candidates if not s.isRedeclaration]
4886 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4887 Symbol.debug_print("non-duplicate candidate symbols:", len(symbols))
4888  
4889 if len(symbols) == 0:
4890 unconditionalAdd(self, otherChild)
4891 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4892 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4893 continue
4894  
4895 ourChild = None
4896 if otherChild.declaration is None:
4897 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4898 Symbol.debug_print("no declaration in other child")
4899 ourChild = symbols[0]
4900 else:
4901 queryId = otherChild.declaration.get_newest_id()
4902 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4903 Symbol.debug_print("queryId: ", queryId)
4904 for symbol in symbols:
4905 if symbol.declaration is None:
4906 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4907 Symbol.debug_print("empty candidate")
4908 # if in the end we have non-matching, but have an empty one,
4909 # then just continue with that
4910 ourChild = symbol
4911 continue
4912 candId = symbol.declaration.get_newest_id()
4913 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4914 Symbol.debug_print("candidate:", candId)
4915 if candId == queryId:
4916 ourChild = symbol
4917 break
4918 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4919 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
4920 if ourChild is None:
4921 unconditionalAdd(self, otherChild)
4922 continue
4923 if otherChild.declaration and otherChild.docname in docnames:
4924 if not ourChild.declaration:
4925 ourChild._fill_empty(otherChild.declaration,
4926 otherChild.docname, otherChild.line)
4927 elif ourChild.docname != otherChild.docname:
4928 name = str(ourChild.declaration)
4929 msg = __("Duplicate C++ declaration, also defined at %s:%s.\n"
4930 "Declaration is '.. cpp:%s:: %s'.")
4931 msg = msg % (ourChild.docname, ourChild.line,
4932 ourChild.declaration.directiveType, name)
4933 logger.warning(msg, location=(otherChild.docname, otherChild.line))
4934 else:
4935 if (otherChild.declaration.objectType ==
4936 ourChild.declaration.objectType and
4937 otherChild.declaration.objectType in
4938 ('templateParam', 'functionParam') and
4939 ourChild.parent.declaration == otherChild.parent.declaration):
4940 # `ourChild` was just created during merging by the call
4941 # to `_fill_empty` on the parent and can be ignored.
4942 pass
4943 else:
4944 # Both have declarations, and in the same docname.
4945 # This can apparently happen, it should be safe to
4946 # just ignore it, right?
4947 # Hmm, only on duplicate declarations, right?
4948 msg = "Internal C++ domain error during symbol merging.\n"
4949 msg += "ourChild:\n" + ourChild.to_string(1)
4950 msg += "\notherChild:\n" + otherChild.to_string(1)
4951 logger.warning(msg, location=otherChild.docname)
4952 ourChild.merge_with(otherChild, docnames, env)
4953 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4954 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2

4989 def find_identifier(self, identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
4990 matchSelf: bool, recurseInAnon: bool, searchInSiblings: bool,
4991 ) -> Symbol:
4992 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
4993 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4994 Symbol.debug_print("find_identifier:")
4995 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
4996 Symbol.debug_print("identOrOp: ", identOrOp)
4997 Symbol.debug_print("matchSelf: ", matchSelf)
4998 Symbol.debug_print("recurseInAnon: ", recurseInAnon)
4999 Symbol.debug_print("searchInSiblings:", searchInSiblings)
5000 logger.debug(self.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
5001 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5002 current = self
5003 while current is not None:
5004 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5005 Symbol.debug_indent += 2
5006 Symbol.debug_print("trying:")
5007 logger.debug(current.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
5008 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5009 if matchSelf and current.identOrOp == identOrOp:
5010 return current
5011 children = current.children_recurse_anon if recurseInAnon else current._children
5012 for s in children:
5013 if s.identOrOp == identOrOp:
5014 return s
5015 if not searchInSiblings:
5016 break
5017 current = current.siblingAbove
5018 return None

5020 def direct_lookup(self, key: LookupKey) -> Symbol:
5021 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5022 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
5023 Symbol.debug_print("direct_lookup:")
5024 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
5025 s = self
5026 for name, templateParams, id_ in key.data:
5027 if id_ is not None:
5028 res = None
5029 for cand in s._children:
5030 if cand.declaration is None:
5031 continue
5032 if cand.declaration.get_newest_id() == id_:
5033 res = cand
5034 break
5035 s = res
5036 else:
5037 identOrOp = name.identOrOp
5038 templateArgs = name.templateArgs
5039 s = s._find_first_named_symbol(identOrOp,
5040 templateParams, templateArgs,
5041 templateShorthand=False,
5042 matchSelf=False,
5043 recurseInAnon=False,
5044 correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=False)
5045 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5046 Symbol.debug_print("name: ", name)
5047 Symbol.debug_print("templateParams:", templateParams)
5048 Symbol.debug_print("id: ", id_)
5049 if s is not None:
5050 logger.debug(s.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
5051 else:
5052 Symbol.debug_print("not found")
5053 if s is None:
5054 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5055 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5056 return None
5057 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5058 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5059 return s

5061 def find_name(self, nestedName: ASTNestedName, templateDecls: list[Any],
5062 typ: str, templateShorthand: bool, matchSelf: bool,
5063 recurseInAnon: bool, searchInSiblings: bool) -> tuple[list[Symbol], str]:
5064 # templateShorthand: missing template parameter lists for templates is ok
5065 # If the first component is None,
5066 # then the second component _may_ be a string explaining why.
5067 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5068 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
5069 Symbol.debug_print("find_name:")
5070 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
5071 Symbol.debug_print("self:")
5072 logger.debug(self.to_string(Symbol.debug_indent + 1), end="")
5073 Symbol.debug_print("nestedName: ", nestedName)
5074 Symbol.debug_print("templateDecls: ", templateDecls)
5075 Symbol.debug_print("typ: ", typ)
5076 Symbol.debug_print("templateShorthand:", templateShorthand)
5077 Symbol.debug_print("matchSelf: ", matchSelf)
5078 Symbol.debug_print("recurseInAnon: ", recurseInAnon)
5079 Symbol.debug_print("searchInSiblings: ", searchInSiblings)
5080  
5081 class QualifiedSymbolIsTemplateParam(Exception):
5082 pass
5083  
5084 def onMissingQualifiedSymbol(parentSymbol: Symbol,
5085 identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
5086 templateParams: Any,
5087 templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs) -> Symbol | None:
5088 # TODO: Maybe search without template args?
5089 # Though, the correctPrimaryTemplateArgs does
5090 # that for primary templates.
5091 # Is there another case where it would be good?
5092 if parentSymbol.declaration is not None:
5093 if parentSymbol.declaration.objectType == 'templateParam':
5094 raise QualifiedSymbolIsTemplateParam
5095 return None
5096  
5097 try:
5098 lookupResult = self._symbol_lookup(nestedName, templateDecls,
5099 onMissingQualifiedSymbol,
5100 strictTemplateParamArgLists=False,
5101 ancestorLookupType=typ,
5102 templateShorthand=templateShorthand,
5103 matchSelf=matchSelf,
5104 recurseInAnon=recurseInAnon,
5105 correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=False,
5106 searchInSiblings=searchInSiblings)
5107 except QualifiedSymbolIsTemplateParam:
5108 return None, "templateParamInQualified"
5109  
5110 if lookupResult is None:
5111 # if it was a part of the qualification that could not be found
5112 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5113 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5114 return None, None
5115  
5116 res = list(lookupResult.symbols)
5117 if len(res) != 0:
5118 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5119 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5120 return res, None
5121  
5122 if lookupResult.parentSymbol.declaration is not None:
5123 if lookupResult.parentSymbol.declaration.objectType == 'templateParam':
5124 return None, "templateParamInQualified"
5125  
5126 # try without template params and args
5127 symbol = lookupResult.parentSymbol._find_first_named_symbol(
5128 lookupResult.identOrOp, None, None,
5129 templateShorthand=templateShorthand, matchSelf=matchSelf,
5130 recurseInAnon=recurseInAnon, correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=False)
5131 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5132 Symbol.debug_indent -= 2
5133 if symbol is not None:
5134 return [symbol], None
5135 else:
5136 return None, None
5137  
5138 def find_declaration(self, declaration: ASTDeclaration, typ: str, templateShorthand: bool,
5139 matchSelf: bool, recurseInAnon: bool) -> Symbol:
5140 # templateShorthand: missing template parameter lists for templates is ok
5141 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5142 Symbol.debug_indent += 1
5143 Symbol.debug_print("find_declaration:")
5144 nestedName = declaration.name
5145 if declaration.templatePrefix:
5146 templateDecls = declaration.templatePrefix.templates
5147 else:
5148 templateDecls = []
5149  
5150 def onMissingQualifiedSymbol(parentSymbol: Symbol,
5151 identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator,
5152 templateParams: Any,
5153 templateArgs: ASTTemplateArgs) -> Symbol | None:
5154 return None
5155  
5156 lookupResult = self._symbol_lookup(nestedName, templateDecls,
5157 onMissingQualifiedSymbol,
5158 strictTemplateParamArgLists=False,
5159 ancestorLookupType=typ,
5160 templateShorthand=templateShorthand,
5161 matchSelf=matchSelf,
5162 recurseInAnon=recurseInAnon,
5163 correctPrimaryTemplateArgs=False,
5164 searchInSiblings=False)
5165 if Symbol.debug_lookup:
5166 Symbol.debug_indent -= 1
5167 if lookupResult is None:
5168 return None
5169  
5170 symbols = list(lookupResult.symbols)
5171 if len(symbols) == 0:
5172 return None
5173  
5174 querySymbol = Symbol(parent=lookupResult.parentSymbol,
5175 identOrOp=lookupResult.identOrOp,
5176 templateParams=lookupResult.templateParams,
5177 templateArgs=lookupResult.templateArgs,
5178 declaration=declaration,
5179 docname='fakeDocnameForQuery',
5180 line=42)
5181 queryId = declaration.get_newest_id()
5182 for symbol in symbols:
5183 if symbol.declaration is None:
5184 continue
5185 candId = symbol.declaration.get_newest_id()
5186 if candId == queryId:
5187 querySymbol.remove()
5188 return symbol
5189 querySymbol.remove()
5190 return None
5191  
5192 def to_string(self, indent: int) -> str:
5193 res = [Symbol.debug_indent_string * indent]
5194 if not self.parent:
5195 res.append('::')
5196 else:
5197 if self.templateParams:
5198 res.append(str(self.templateParams))
5199 res.append('\n')
5200 res.append(Symbol.debug_indent_string * indent)
5201 if self.identOrOp:
5202 res.append(str(self.identOrOp))
5203 else:
5204 res.append(str(self.declaration))
5205 if self.templateArgs:
5206 res.append(str(self.templateArgs))
5207 if self.declaration:
5208 res.append(": ")
5209 if self.isRedeclaration:
5210 res.append('!!duplicate!! ')
5211 res.append("{" + self.declaration.objectType + "} ")
5212 res.append(str(self.declaration))
5213 if self.docname:
5214 res.append('\t(')
5215 res.append(self.docname)
5216 res.append(')')
5217 res.append('\n')
5218 return ''.join(res)
5219  
5220 def dump(self, indent: int) -> str:
5221 res = [self.to_string(indent)]
5222 for c in self._children:
5223 res.append(c.dump(indent + 1))
5224 return ''.join(res)
