5226  
5227 class DefinitionParser(BaseParser):
5228 @property
5229 def language(self) -> str:
5230 return 'C++'
5231  
5232 @property
5233 def id_attributes(self):
5234 return self.config.cpp_id_attributes
5235  
5236 @property
5237 def paren_attributes(self):
5238 return self.config.cpp_paren_attributes
5239  
5240 def _parse_string(self) -> str:
5241 if self.current_char != '"':
5242 return None
5243 startPos = self.pos
5244 self.pos += 1
5245 escape = False
5246 while True:
5247 if self.eof:
5248 self.fail("Unexpected end during inside string.")
5249 elif self.current_char == '"' and not escape:
5250 self.pos += 1
5251 break
5252 elif self.current_char == '\\':
5253 escape = True
5254 else:
5255 escape = False
5256 self.pos += 1
5257 return self.definition[startPos:self.pos]
5258  
5259 def _parse_literal(self) -> ASTLiteral:
5260 # -> integer-literal
5261 # | character-literal
5262 # | floating-literal
5263 # | string-literal
5264 # | boolean-literal -> "false" | "true"
5265 # | pointer-literal -> "nullptr"
5266 # | user-defined-literal
5267  
5268 def _udl(literal: ASTLiteral) -> ASTLiteral:
5269 if not self.match(udl_identifier_re):
5270 return literal
5271 # hmm, should we care if it's a keyword?
5272 # it looks like GCC does not disallow keywords
5273 ident = ASTIdentifier(self.matched_text)
5274 return ASTUserDefinedLiteral(literal, ident)
5275  
5276 self.skip_ws()
5277 if self.skip_word('nullptr'):
5278 return ASTPointerLiteral()
5279 if self.skip_word('true'):
5280 return ASTBooleanLiteral(True)
5281 if self.skip_word('false'):
5282 return ASTBooleanLiteral(False)
5283 pos = self.pos
5284 if self.match(float_literal_re):
5285 hasSuffix = self.match(float_literal_suffix_re)
5286 floatLit = ASTNumberLiteral(self.definition[pos:self.pos])
5287 if hasSuffix:
5288 return floatLit
5289 else:
5290 return _udl(floatLit)
5291 for regex in [binary_literal_re, hex_literal_re,
5292 integer_literal_re, octal_literal_re]:
5293 if self.match(regex):
5294 hasSuffix = self.match(integers_literal_suffix_re)
5295 intLit = ASTNumberLiteral(self.definition[pos:self.pos])
5296 if hasSuffix:
5297 return intLit
5298 else:
5299 return _udl(intLit)
5300  
5301 string = self._parse_string()
5302 if string is not None:
5303 return _udl(ASTStringLiteral(string))
5304  
5305 # character-literal
5306 if self.match(char_literal_re):
5307 prefix = self.last_match.group(1) # may be None when no prefix
5308 data = self.last_match.group(2)
5309 try:
5310 charLit = ASTCharLiteral(prefix, data)
5311 except UnicodeDecodeError as e:
5312 self.fail("Can not handle character literal. Internal error was: %s" % e)
5313 except UnsupportedMultiCharacterCharLiteral:
5314 self.fail("Can not handle character literal"
5315 " resulting in multiple decoded characters.")
5316 return _udl(charLit)
5317 return None
5318  
5319 def _parse_fold_or_paren_expression(self) -> ASTExpression:
5320 # "(" expression ")"
5321 # fold-expression
5322 # -> ( cast-expression fold-operator ... )
5323 # | ( ... fold-operator cast-expression )
5324 # | ( cast-expression fold-operator ... fold-operator cast-expression
5325 if self.current_char != '(':
5326 return None
5327 self.pos += 1
5328 self.skip_ws()
5329 if self.skip_string_and_ws("..."):
5330 # ( ... fold-operator cast-expression )
5331 if not self.match(_fold_operator_re):
5332 self.fail("Expected fold operator after '...' in fold expression.")
5333 op = self.matched_text
5334 rightExpr = self._parse_cast_expression()
5335 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5336 self.fail("Expected ')' in end of fold expression.")
5337 return ASTFoldExpr(None, op, rightExpr)
5338 # try first parsing a unary right fold, or a binary fold
5339 pos = self.pos
5340 try:
5341 self.skip_ws()
5342 leftExpr = self._parse_cast_expression()
5343 self.skip_ws()
5344 if not self.match(_fold_operator_re):
5345 self.fail("Expected fold operator after left expression in fold expression.")
5346 op = self.matched_text
5347 self.skip_ws()
5348 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('...'):
5349 self.fail("Expected '...' after fold operator in fold expression.")
5350 except DefinitionError as eFold:
5351 self.pos = pos
5352 # fall back to a paren expression
5353 try:
5354 res = self._parse_expression()
5355 self.skip_ws()
5356 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5357 self.fail("Expected ')' in end of parenthesized expression.")
5358 except DefinitionError as eExpr:
5359 raise self._make_multi_error([
5360 (eFold, "If fold expression"),
5361 (eExpr, "If parenthesized expression"),
5362 ], "Error in fold expression or parenthesized expression.") from eExpr
5363 return ASTParenExpr(res)
5364 # now it definitely is a fold expression
5365 if self.skip_string(')'):
5366 return ASTFoldExpr(leftExpr, op, None)
5367 if not self.match(_fold_operator_re):
5368 self.fail("Expected fold operator or ')' after '...' in fold expression.")
5369 if op != self.matched_text:
5370 self.fail("Operators are different in binary fold: '%s' and '%s'."
5371 % (op, self.matched_text))
5372 rightExpr = self._parse_cast_expression()
5373 self.skip_ws()
5374 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5375 self.fail("Expected ')' to end binary fold expression.")
5376 return ASTFoldExpr(leftExpr, op, rightExpr)
5377  
5378 def _parse_primary_expression(self) -> ASTExpression:
5379 # literal
5380 # "this"
5381 # lambda-expression
5382 # "(" expression ")"
5383 # fold-expression
5384 # id-expression -> we parse this with _parse_nested_name
5385 self.skip_ws()
5386 res: ASTExpression = self._parse_literal()
5387 if res is not None:
5388 return res
5389 self.skip_ws()
5390 if self.skip_word("this"):
5391 return ASTThisLiteral()
5392 # TODO: try lambda expression
5393 res = self._parse_fold_or_paren_expression()
5394 if res is not None:
5395 return res
5396 nn = self._parse_nested_name()
5397 if nn is not None:
5398 return ASTIdExpression(nn)
5399 return None
5400  
5401 def _parse_initializer_list(self, name: str, open: str, close: str,
5402 ) -> tuple[list[ASTExpression | ASTBracedInitList],
5403 bool]:
5404 # Parse open and close with the actual initializer-list in between
5405 # -> initializer-clause '...'[opt]
5406 # | initializer-list ',' initializer-clause '...'[opt]
5407 self.skip_ws()
5408 if not self.skip_string_and_ws(open):
5409 return None, None
5410 if self.skip_string(close):
5411 return [], False
5412  
5413 exprs: list[ASTExpression | ASTBracedInitList] = []
5414 trailingComma = False
5415 while True:
5416 self.skip_ws()
5417 expr = self._parse_initializer_clause()
5418 self.skip_ws()
5419 if self.skip_string('...'):
5420 exprs.append(ASTPackExpansionExpr(expr))
5421 else:
5422 exprs.append(expr)
5423 self.skip_ws()
5424 if self.skip_string(close):
5425 break
5426 if not self.skip_string_and_ws(','):
5427 self.fail(f"Error in {name}, expected ',' or '{close}'.")
5428 if self.current_char == close and close == '}':
5429 self.pos += 1
5430 trailingComma = True
5431 break
5432 return exprs, trailingComma
5433  
5434 def _parse_paren_expression_list(self) -> ASTParenExprList:
5435 # -> '(' expression-list ')'
5436 # though, we relax it to also allow empty parens
5437 # as it's needed in some cases
5438 #
5439 # expression-list
5440 # -> initializer-list
5441 exprs, trailingComma = self._parse_initializer_list("parenthesized expression-list",
5442 '(', ')')
5443 if exprs is None:
5444 return None
5445 return ASTParenExprList(exprs)
5446  
5447 def _parse_initializer_clause(self) -> ASTExpression | ASTBracedInitList:
5448 bracedInitList = self._parse_braced_init_list()
5449 if bracedInitList is not None:
5450 return bracedInitList
5451 return self._parse_assignment_expression(inTemplate=False)
5452  
5453 def _parse_braced_init_list(self) -> ASTBracedInitList:
5454 # -> '{' initializer-list ','[opt] '}'
5455 # | '{' '}'
5456 exprs, trailingComma = self._parse_initializer_list("braced-init-list", '{', '}')
5457 if exprs is None:
5458 return None
5459 return ASTBracedInitList(exprs, trailingComma)
5460  
5461 def _parse_expression_list_or_braced_init_list(
5462 self,
5463 ) -> ASTParenExprList | ASTBracedInitList:
5464 paren = self._parse_paren_expression_list()
5465 if paren is not None:
5466 return paren
5467 return self._parse_braced_init_list()
5468  
5469 def _parse_postfix_expression(self) -> ASTPostfixExpr:
5470 # -> primary
5471 # | postfix "[" expression "]"
5472 # | postfix "[" braced-init-list [opt] "]"
5473 # | postfix "(" expression-list [opt] ")"
5474 # | postfix "." "template" [opt] id-expression
5475 # | postfix "->" "template" [opt] id-expression
5476 # | postfix "." pseudo-destructor-name
5477 # | postfix "->" pseudo-destructor-name
5478 # | postfix "++"
5479 # | postfix "--"
5480 # | simple-type-specifier "(" expression-list [opt] ")"
5481 # | simple-type-specifier braced-init-list
5482 # | typename-specifier "(" expression-list [opt] ")"
5483 # | typename-specifier braced-init-list
5484 # | "dynamic_cast" "<" type-id ">" "(" expression ")"
5485 # | "static_cast" "<" type-id ">" "(" expression ")"
5486 # | "reinterpret_cast" "<" type-id ">" "(" expression ")"
5487 # | "const_cast" "<" type-id ">" "(" expression ")"
5488 # | "typeid" "(" expression ")"
5489 # | "typeid" "(" type-id ")"
5490  
5491 prefixType = None
5492 prefix: Any = None
5493 self.skip_ws()
5494  
5495 cast = None
5496 for c in _id_explicit_cast:
5497 if self.skip_word_and_ws(c):
5498 cast = c
5499 break
5500 if cast is not None:
5501 prefixType = "cast"
5502 if not self.skip_string("<"):
5503 self.fail("Expected '<' after '%s'." % cast)
5504 typ = self._parse_type(False)
5505 self.skip_ws()
5506 if not self.skip_string_and_ws(">"):
5507 self.fail("Expected '>' after type in '%s'." % cast)
5508 if not self.skip_string("("):
5509 self.fail("Expected '(' in '%s'." % cast)
5510  
5511 def parser() -> ASTExpression:
5512 return self._parse_expression()
5513 expr = self._parse_expression_fallback([')'], parser)
5514 self.skip_ws()
5515 if not self.skip_string(")"):
5516 self.fail("Expected ')' to end '%s'." % cast)
5517 prefix = ASTExplicitCast(cast, typ, expr)
5518 elif self.skip_word_and_ws("typeid"):
5519 prefixType = "typeid"
5520 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
5521 self.fail("Expected '(' after 'typeid'.")
5522 pos = self.pos
5523 try:
5524 typ = self._parse_type(False)
5525 prefix = ASTTypeId(typ, isType=True)
5526 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5527 self.fail("Expected ')' to end 'typeid' of type.")
5528 except DefinitionError as eType:
5529 self.pos = pos
5530 try:
5531  
5532 def parser() -> ASTExpression:
5533 return self._parse_expression()
5534 expr = self._parse_expression_fallback([')'], parser)
5535 prefix = ASTTypeId(expr, isType=False)
5536 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5537 self.fail("Expected ')' to end 'typeid' of expression.")
5538 except DefinitionError as eExpr:
5539 self.pos = pos
5540 header = "Error in 'typeid(...)'."
5541 header += " Expected type or expression."
5542 errors = []
5543 errors.append((eType, "If type"))
5544 errors.append((eExpr, "If expression"))
5545 raise self._make_multi_error(errors, header) from eExpr
5546 else: # a primary expression or a type
5547 pos = self.pos
5548 try:
5549 prefix = self._parse_primary_expression()
5550 prefixType = 'expr'
5551 except DefinitionError as eOuter:
5552 self.pos = pos
5553 try:
5554 # we are potentially casting, so save parens for us
5555 # TODO: hmm, would we need to try both with operatorCast and with None?
5556 prefix = self._parse_type(False, 'operatorCast')
5557 prefixType = 'typeOperatorCast'
5558 # | simple-type-specifier "(" expression-list [opt] ")"
5559 # | simple-type-specifier braced-init-list
5560 # | typename-specifier "(" expression-list [opt] ")"
5561 # | typename-specifier braced-init-list
5562 self.skip_ws()
5563 if self.current_char != '(' and self.current_char != '{':
5564 self.fail("Expecting '(' or '{' after type in cast expression.")
5565 except DefinitionError as eInner:
5566 self.pos = pos
5567 header = "Error in postfix expression,"
5568 header += " expected primary expression or type."
5569 errors = []
5570 errors.append((eOuter, "If primary expression"))
5571 errors.append((eInner, "If type"))
5572 raise self._make_multi_error(errors, header) from eInner
5573  
5574 # and now parse postfixes
5575 postFixes: list[ASTPostfixOp] = []
5576 while True:
5577 self.skip_ws()
5578 if prefixType in ('expr', 'cast', 'typeid'):
5579 if self.skip_string_and_ws('['):
5580 expr = self._parse_expression()
5581 self.skip_ws()
5582 if not self.skip_string(']'):
5583 self.fail("Expected ']' in end of postfix expression.")
5584 postFixes.append(ASTPostfixArray(expr))
5585 continue
5586 if self.skip_string('.'):
5587 if self.skip_string('*'):
5588 # don't steal the dot
5589 self.pos -= 2
5590 elif self.skip_string('..'):
5591 # don't steal the dot
5592 self.pos -= 3
5593 else:
5594 name = self._parse_nested_name()
5595 postFixes.append(ASTPostfixMember(name))
5596 continue
5597 if self.skip_string('->'):
5598 if self.skip_string('*'):
5599 # don't steal the arrow
5600 self.pos -= 3
5601 else:
5602 name = self._parse_nested_name()
5603 postFixes.append(ASTPostfixMemberOfPointer(name))
5604 continue
5605 if self.skip_string('++'):
5606 postFixes.append(ASTPostfixInc())
5607 continue
5608 if self.skip_string('--'):
5609 postFixes.append(ASTPostfixDec())
5610 continue
5611 lst = self._parse_expression_list_or_braced_init_list()
5612 if lst is not None:
5613 postFixes.append(ASTPostfixCallExpr(lst))
5614 continue
5615 break
5616 return ASTPostfixExpr(prefix, postFixes)
5617  
5618 def _parse_unary_expression(self) -> ASTExpression:
5619 # -> postfix
5620 # | "++" cast
5621 # | "--" cast
5622 # | unary-operator cast -> (* | & | + | - | ! | ~) cast
5623 # The rest:
5624 # | "sizeof" unary
5625 # | "sizeof" "(" type-id ")"
5626 # | "sizeof" "..." "(" identifier ")"
5627 # | "alignof" "(" type-id ")"
5628 # | noexcept-expression -> noexcept "(" expression ")"
5629 # | new-expression
5630 # | delete-expression
5631 self.skip_ws()
5632 for op in _expression_unary_ops:
5633 # TODO: hmm, should we be able to backtrack here?
5634 if op[0] in 'cn':
5635 res = self.skip_word(op)
5636 else:
5637 res = self.skip_string(op)
5638 if res:
5639 expr = self._parse_cast_expression()
5640 return ASTUnaryOpExpr(op, expr)
5641 if self.skip_word_and_ws('sizeof'):
5642 if self.skip_string_and_ws('...'):
5643 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
5644 self.fail("Expecting '(' after 'sizeof...'.")
5645 if not self.match(identifier_re):
5646 self.fail("Expecting identifier for 'sizeof...'.")
5647 ident = ASTIdentifier(self.matched_text)
5648 self.skip_ws()
5649 if not self.skip_string(")"):
5650 self.fail("Expecting ')' to end 'sizeof...'.")
5651 return ASTSizeofParamPack(ident)
5652 if self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
5653 typ = self._parse_type(named=False)
5654 self.skip_ws()
5655 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5656 self.fail("Expecting ')' to end 'sizeof'.")
5657 return ASTSizeofType(typ)
5658 expr = self._parse_unary_expression()
5659 return ASTSizeofExpr(expr)
5660 if self.skip_word_and_ws('alignof'):
5661 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
5662 self.fail("Expecting '(' after 'alignof'.")
5663 typ = self._parse_type(named=False)
5664 self.skip_ws()
5665 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5666 self.fail("Expecting ')' to end 'alignof'.")
5667 return ASTAlignofExpr(typ)
5668 if self.skip_word_and_ws('noexcept'):
5669 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
5670 self.fail("Expecting '(' after 'noexcept'.")
5671 expr = self._parse_expression()
5672 self.skip_ws()
5673 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5674 self.fail("Expecting ')' to end 'noexcept'.")
5675 return ASTNoexceptExpr(expr)
5676 # new-expression
5677 pos = self.pos
5678 rooted = self.skip_string('::')
5679 self.skip_ws()
5680 if not self.skip_word_and_ws('new'):
5681 self.pos = pos
5682 else:
5683 # new-placement[opt] new-type-id new-initializer[opt]
5684 # new-placement[opt] ( type-id ) new-initializer[opt]
5685 isNewTypeId = True
5686 if self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
5687 # either this is a new-placement or it's the second production
5688 # without placement, and it's actually the ( type-id ) part
5689 self.fail("Sorry, neither new-placement nor parenthesised type-id "
5690 "in new-epression is supported yet.")
5691 # set isNewTypeId = False if it's (type-id)
5692 if isNewTypeId:
5693 declSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs(outer=None)
5694 decl = self._parse_declarator(named=False, paramMode="new")
5695 else:
5696 self.fail("Sorry, parenthesised type-id in new expression not yet supported.")
5697 lst = self._parse_expression_list_or_braced_init_list()
5698 return ASTNewExpr(rooted, isNewTypeId, ASTType(declSpecs, decl), lst)
5699 # delete-expression
5700 pos = self.pos
5701 rooted = self.skip_string('::')
5702 self.skip_ws()
5703 if not self.skip_word_and_ws('delete'):
5704 self.pos = pos
5705 else:
5706 array = self.skip_string_and_ws('[')
5707 if array and not self.skip_string_and_ws(']'):
5708 self.fail("Expected ']' in array delete-expression.")
5709 expr = self._parse_cast_expression()
5710 return ASTDeleteExpr(rooted, array, expr)
5711 return self._parse_postfix_expression()
5712  
5713 def _parse_cast_expression(self) -> ASTExpression:
5714 # -> unary | "(" type-id ")" cast
5715 pos = self.pos
5716 self.skip_ws()
5717 if self.skip_string('('):
5718 try:
5719 typ = self._parse_type(False)
5720 if not self.skip_string(')'):
5721 self.fail("Expected ')' in cast expression.")
5722 expr = self._parse_cast_expression()
5723 return ASTCastExpr(typ, expr)
5724 except DefinitionError as exCast:
5725 self.pos = pos
5726 try:
5727 return self._parse_unary_expression()
5728 except DefinitionError as exUnary:
5729 errs = []
5730 errs.append((exCast, "If type cast expression"))
5731 errs.append((exUnary, "If unary expression"))
5732 raise self._make_multi_error(errs,
5733 "Error in cast expression.") from exUnary
5734 else:
5735 return self._parse_unary_expression()
5736  
5737 def _parse_logical_or_expression(self, inTemplate: bool) -> ASTExpression:
5738 # logical-or = logical-and ||
5739 # logical-and = inclusive-or &&
5740 # inclusive-or = exclusive-or |
5741 # exclusive-or = and ^
5742 # and = equality &
5743 # equality = relational ==, !=
5744 # relational = shift <, >, <=, >=, <=>
5745 # shift = additive <<, >>
5746 # additive = multiplicative +, -
5747 # multiplicative = pm *, /, %
5748 # pm = cast .*, ->*
5749 def _parse_bin_op_expr(self: DefinitionParser,
5750 opId: int, inTemplate: bool) -> ASTExpression:
5751 if opId + 1 == len(_expression_bin_ops):
5752 def parser(inTemplate: bool) -> ASTExpression:
5753 return self._parse_cast_expression()
5754 else:
5755 def parser(inTemplate: bool) -> ASTExpression:
5756 return _parse_bin_op_expr(self, opId + 1, inTemplate=inTemplate)
5757 exprs = []
5758 ops = []
5759 exprs.append(parser(inTemplate=inTemplate))
5760 while True:
5761 self.skip_ws()
5762 if inTemplate and self.current_char == '>':
5763 break
5764 pos = self.pos
5765 oneMore = False
5766 for op in _expression_bin_ops[opId]:
5767 if op[0] in 'abcnox':
5768 if not self.skip_word(op):
5769 continue
5770 else:
5771 if not self.skip_string(op):
5772 continue
5773 if op == '&' and self.current_char == '&':
5774 # don't split the && 'token'
5775 self.pos -= 1
5776 # and btw. && has lower precedence, so we are done
5777 break
5778 try:
5779 expr = parser(inTemplate=inTemplate)
5780 exprs.append(expr)
5781 ops.append(op)
5782 oneMore = True
5783 break
5784 except DefinitionError:
5785 self.pos = pos
5786 if not oneMore:
5787 break
5788 return ASTBinOpExpr(exprs, ops)
5789 return _parse_bin_op_expr(self, 0, inTemplate=inTemplate)
5790  
5791 def _parse_conditional_expression_tail(self, orExprHead: ASTExpression,
5792 inTemplate: bool) -> ASTConditionalExpr | None:
5793 # Consumes the orExprHead on success.
5794  
5795 # -> "?" expression ":" assignment-expression
5796 self.skip_ws()
5797 if not self.skip_string("?"):
5798 return None
5799 thenExpr = self._parse_expression()
5800 self.skip_ws()
5801 if not self.skip_string(":"):
5802 self.fail('Expected ":" after then-expression in conditional expression.')
5803 elseExpr = self._parse_assignment_expression(inTemplate)
5804 return ASTConditionalExpr(orExprHead, thenExpr, elseExpr)
5805  
5806 def _parse_assignment_expression(self, inTemplate: bool) -> ASTExpression:
5807 # -> conditional-expression
5808 # | logical-or-expression assignment-operator initializer-clause
5809 # | yield-expression -> "co_yield" assignment-expression
5810 # | "co_yield" braced-init-list
5811 # | throw-expression -> "throw" assignment-expression[opt]
5812 # TODO: yield-expression
5813 # TODO: throw-expression
5814  
5815 # Now we have (after expanding conditional-expression:
5816 # logical-or-expression
5817 # | logical-or-expression "?" expression ":" assignment-expression
5818 # | logical-or-expression assignment-operator initializer-clause
5819 leftExpr = self._parse_logical_or_expression(inTemplate=inTemplate)
5820 # the ternary operator
5821 condExpr = self._parse_conditional_expression_tail(leftExpr, inTemplate)
5822 if condExpr is not None:
5823 return condExpr
5824 # and actual assignment
5825 for op in _expression_assignment_ops:
5826 if op[0] in 'anox':
5827 if not self.skip_word(op):
5828 continue
5829 else:
5830 if not self.skip_string(op):
5831 continue
5832 rightExpr = self._parse_initializer_clause()
5833 return ASTAssignmentExpr(leftExpr, op, rightExpr)
5834 # just a logical-or-expression
5835 return leftExpr
5836  
5837 def _parse_constant_expression(self, inTemplate: bool) -> ASTExpression:
5838 # -> conditional-expression ->
5839 # logical-or-expression
5840 # | logical-or-expression "?" expression ":" assignment-expression
5841 orExpr = self._parse_logical_or_expression(inTemplate=inTemplate)
5842 condExpr = self._parse_conditional_expression_tail(orExpr, inTemplate)
5843 if condExpr is not None:
5844 return condExpr
5845 return orExpr
5846  
5847 def _parse_expression(self) -> ASTExpression:
5848 # -> assignment-expression
5849 # | expression "," assignment-expression
5850 exprs = [self._parse_assignment_expression(inTemplate=False)]
5851 while True:
5852 self.skip_ws()
5853 if not self.skip_string(','):
5854 break
5855 exprs.append(self._parse_assignment_expression(inTemplate=False))
5856 if len(exprs) == 1:
5857 return exprs[0]
5858 else:
5859 return ASTCommaExpr(exprs)
5860  
5861 def _parse_expression_fallback(self, end: list[str],
5862 parser: Callable[[], ASTExpression],
5863 allow: bool = True) -> ASTExpression:
5864 # Stupidly "parse" an expression.
5865 # 'end' should be a list of characters which ends the expression.
5866  
5867 # first try to use the provided parser
5868 prevPos = self.pos
5869 try:
5870 return parser()
5871 except DefinitionError as e:
5872 # some places (e.g., template parameters) we really don't want to use fallback,
5873 # and for testing we may want to globally disable it
5874 if not allow or not self.allowFallbackExpressionParsing:
5875 raise
5876 self.warn("Parsing of expression failed. Using fallback parser."
5877 " Error was:\n%s" % e)
5878 self.pos = prevPos
5879 # and then the fallback scanning
5880 assert end is not None
5881 self.skip_ws()
5882 startPos = self.pos
5883 if self.match(_string_re):
5884 value = self.matched_text
5885 else:
5886 # TODO: add handling of more bracket-like things, and quote handling
5887 brackets = {'(': ')', '{': '}', '[': ']', '<': '>'}
5888 symbols: list[str] = []
5889 while not self.eof:
5890 if (len(symbols) == 0 and self.current_char in end):
5891 break
5892 if self.current_char in brackets:
5893 symbols.append(brackets[self.current_char])
5894 elif len(symbols) > 0 and self.current_char == symbols[-1]:
5895 symbols.pop()
5896 self.pos += 1
5897 if len(end) > 0 and self.eof:
5898 self.fail("Could not find end of expression starting at %d."
5899 % startPos)
5900 value = self.definition[startPos:self.pos].strip()
5901 return ASTFallbackExpr(value.strip())
5902  
5903 # ==========================================================================
5904  
5905 def _parse_operator(self) -> ASTOperator:
5906 self.skip_ws()
5907 # adapted from the old code
5908 # yay, a regular operator definition
5909 if self.match(_operator_re):
5910 return ASTOperatorBuildIn(self.matched_text)
5911  
5912 # new/delete operator?
5913 for op in 'new', 'delete':
5914 if not self.skip_word(op):
5915 continue
5916 self.skip_ws()
5917 if self.skip_string('['):
5918 self.skip_ws()
5919 if not self.skip_string(']'):
5920 self.fail('Expected "]" after "operator ' + op + '["')
5921 op += '[]'
5922 return ASTOperatorBuildIn(op)
5923  
5924 # user-defined literal?
5925 if self.skip_string('""'):
5926 self.skip_ws()
5927 if not self.match(identifier_re):
5928 self.fail("Expected user-defined literal suffix.")
5929 identifier = ASTIdentifier(self.matched_text)
5930 return ASTOperatorLiteral(identifier)
5931  
5932 # oh well, looks like a cast operator definition.
5933 # In that case, eat another type.
5934 type = self._parse_type(named=False, outer="operatorCast")
5935 return ASTOperatorType(type)
5936  
5937 def _parse_template_argument_list(self) -> ASTTemplateArgs:
5938 # template-argument-list: (but we include the < and > here
5939 # template-argument ...[opt]
5940 # template-argument-list, template-argument ...[opt]
5941 # template-argument:
5942 # constant-expression
5943 # type-id
5944 # id-expression
5945 self.skip_ws()
5946 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('<'):
5947 return None
5948 if self.skip_string('>'):
5949 return ASTTemplateArgs([], False)
5950 prevErrors = []
5951 templateArgs: list[ASTType | ASTTemplateArgConstant] = []
5952 packExpansion = False
5953 while 1:
5954 pos = self.pos
5955 parsedComma = False
5956 parsedEnd = False
5957 try:
5958 type = self._parse_type(named=False)
5959 self.skip_ws()
5960 if self.skip_string_and_ws('...'):
5961 packExpansion = True
5962 parsedEnd = True
5963 if not self.skip_string('>'):
5964 self.fail('Expected ">" after "..." in template argument list.')
5965 elif self.skip_string('>'):
5966 parsedEnd = True
5967 elif self.skip_string(','):
5968 parsedComma = True
5969 else:
5970 self.fail('Expected "...>", ">" or "," in template argument list.')
5971 templateArgs.append(type)
5972 except DefinitionError as e:
5973 prevErrors.append((e, "If type argument"))
5974 self.pos = pos
5975 try:
5976 value = self._parse_constant_expression(inTemplate=True)
5977 self.skip_ws()
5978 if self.skip_string_and_ws('...'):
5979 packExpansion = True
5980 parsedEnd = True
5981 if not self.skip_string('>'):
5982 self.fail('Expected ">" after "..." in template argument list.')
5983 elif self.skip_string('>'):
5984 parsedEnd = True
5985 elif self.skip_string(','):
5986 parsedComma = True
5987 else:
5988 self.fail('Expected "...>", ">" or "," in template argument list.')
5989 templateArgs.append(ASTTemplateArgConstant(value))
5990 except DefinitionError as e:
5991 self.pos = pos
5992 prevErrors.append((e, "If non-type argument"))
5993 header = "Error in parsing template argument list."
5994 raise self._make_multi_error(prevErrors, header) from e
5995 if parsedEnd:
5996 assert not parsedComma
5997 break
5998 assert not packExpansion
5999 return ASTTemplateArgs(templateArgs, packExpansion)
6000  
6001 def _parse_nested_name(self, memberPointer: bool = False) -> ASTNestedName:
6002 names: list[ASTNestedNameElement] = []
6003 templates: list[bool] = []
6004  
6005 self.skip_ws()
6006 rooted = False
6007 if self.skip_string('::'):
6008 rooted = True
6009 while 1:
6010 self.skip_ws()
6011 if len(names) > 0:
6012 template = self.skip_word_and_ws('template')
6013 else:
6014 template = False
6015 templates.append(template)
6016 identOrOp: ASTIdentifier | ASTOperator = None
6017 if self.skip_word_and_ws('operator'):
6018 identOrOp = self._parse_operator()
6019 else:
6020 if not self.match(identifier_re):
6021 if memberPointer and len(names) > 0:
6022 templates.pop()
6023 break
6024 self.fail("Expected identifier in nested name.")
6025 identifier = self.matched_text
6026 # make sure there isn't a keyword
6027 if identifier in _keywords:
6028 self.fail("Expected identifier in nested name, "
6029 "got keyword: %s" % identifier)
6030 identOrOp = ASTIdentifier(identifier)
6031 # try greedily to get template arguments,
6032 # but otherwise a < might be because we are in an expression
6033 pos = self.pos
6034 try:
6035 templateArgs = self._parse_template_argument_list()
6036 except DefinitionError as ex:
6037 self.pos = pos
6038 templateArgs = None
6039 self.otherErrors.append(ex)
6040 names.append(ASTNestedNameElement(identOrOp, templateArgs))
6041  
6042 self.skip_ws()
6043 if not self.skip_string('::'):
6044 if memberPointer:
6045 self.fail("Expected '::' in pointer to member (function).")
6046 break
6047 return ASTNestedName(names, templates, rooted)
6048  
6049 # ==========================================================================
6050  
6051 def _parse_simple_type_specifiers(self) -> ASTTrailingTypeSpecFundamental:
6052 modifier: str | None = None
6053 signedness: str | None = None
6054 width: list[str] = []
6055 typ: str | None = None
6056 names: list[str] = [] # the parsed sequence
6057  
6058 self.skip_ws()
6059 while self.match(_simple_type_specifiers_re):
6060 t = self.matched_text
6061 names.append(t)
6062 if t in ('auto', 'void', 'bool',
6063 'char', 'wchar_t', 'char8_t', 'char16_t', 'char32_t',
6064 'int', '__int64', '__int128',
6065 'float', 'double',
6066 '__float80', '_Float64x', '__float128', '_Float128'):
6067 if typ is not None:
6068 self.fail(f"Can not have both {t} and {typ}.")
6069 typ = t
6070 elif t in ('signed', 'unsigned'):
6071 if signedness is not None:
6072 self.fail(f"Can not have both {t} and {signedness}.")
6073 signedness = t
6074 elif t == 'short':
6075 if len(width) != 0:
6076 self.fail(f"Can not have both {t} and {width[0]}.")
6077 width.append(t)
6078 elif t == 'long':
6079 if len(width) != 0 and width[0] != 'long':
6080 self.fail(f"Can not have both {t} and {width[0]}.")
6081 width.append(t)
6082 elif t in ('_Imaginary', '_Complex'):
6083 if modifier is not None:
6084 self.fail(f"Can not have both {t} and {modifier}.")
6085 modifier = t
6086 self.skip_ws()
6087 if len(names) == 0:
6088 return None
6089  
6090 if typ in ('auto', 'void', 'bool',
6091 'wchar_t', 'char8_t', 'char16_t', 'char32_t',
6092 '__float80', '_Float64x', '__float128', '_Float128'):
6093 if modifier is not None:
6094 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {modifier}.")
6095 if signedness is not None:
6096 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {signedness}.")
6097 if len(width) != 0:
6098 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {' '.join(width)}.")
6099 elif typ == 'char':
6100 if modifier is not None:
6101 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {modifier}.")
6102 if len(width) != 0:
6103 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {' '.join(width)}.")
6104 elif typ == 'int':
6105 if modifier is not None:
6106 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {modifier}.")
6107 elif typ in ('__int64', '__int128'):
6108 if modifier is not None:
6109 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {modifier}.")
6110 if len(width) != 0:
6111 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {' '.join(width)}.")
6112 elif typ == 'float':
6113 if signedness is not None:
6114 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {signedness}.")
6115 if len(width) != 0:
6116 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {' '.join(width)}.")
6117 elif typ == 'double':
6118 if signedness is not None:
6119 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {signedness}.")
6120 if len(width) > 1:
6121 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {' '.join(width)}.")
6122 if len(width) == 1 and width[0] != 'long':
6123 self.fail(f"Can not have both {typ} and {' '.join(width)}.")
6124 elif typ is None:
6125 if modifier is not None:
6126 self.fail(f"Can not have {modifier} without a floating point type.")
6127 else:
6128 msg = f'Unhandled type {typ}'
6129 raise AssertionError(msg)
6130  
6131 canonNames: list[str] = []
6132 if modifier is not None:
6133 canonNames.append(modifier)
6134 if signedness is not None:
6135 canonNames.append(signedness)
6136 canonNames.extend(width)
6137 if typ is not None:
6138 canonNames.append(typ)
6139 return ASTTrailingTypeSpecFundamental(names, canonNames)
6140  
6141 def _parse_trailing_type_spec(self) -> ASTTrailingTypeSpec:
6142 # fundamental types, https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/type
6143 # and extensions
6144 self.skip_ws()
6145 res = self._parse_simple_type_specifiers()
6146 if res is not None:
6147 return res
6148  
6149 # decltype
6150 self.skip_ws()
6151 if self.skip_word_and_ws('decltype'):
6152 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
6153 self.fail("Expected '(' after 'decltype'.")
6154 if self.skip_word_and_ws('auto'):
6155 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6156 self.fail("Expected ')' after 'decltype(auto'.")
6157 return ASTTrailingTypeSpecDecltypeAuto()
6158 expr = self._parse_expression()
6159 self.skip_ws()
6160 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6161 self.fail("Expected ')' after 'decltype(<expr>'.")
6162 return ASTTrailingTypeSpecDecltype(expr)
6163  
6164 # prefixed
6165 prefix = None
6166 self.skip_ws()
6167 for k in ('class', 'struct', 'enum', 'union', 'typename'):
6168 if self.skip_word_and_ws(k):
6169 prefix = k
6170 break
6171 nestedName = self._parse_nested_name()
6172 self.skip_ws()
6173 placeholderType = None
6174 if self.skip_word('auto'):
6175 placeholderType = 'auto'
6176 elif self.skip_word_and_ws('decltype'):
6177 if not self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
6178 self.fail("Expected '(' after 'decltype' in placeholder type specifier.")
6179 if not self.skip_word_and_ws('auto'):
6180 self.fail("Expected 'auto' after 'decltype(' in placeholder type specifier.")
6181 if not self.skip_string_and_ws(')'):
6182 self.fail("Expected ')' after 'decltype(auto' in placeholder type specifier.")
6183 placeholderType = 'decltype(auto)'
6184 return ASTTrailingTypeSpecName(prefix, nestedName, placeholderType)
6185  
6186 def _parse_parameters_and_qualifiers(self, paramMode: str) -> ASTParametersQualifiers:
6187 if paramMode == 'new':
6188 return None
6189 self.skip_ws()
6190 if not self.skip_string('('):
6191 if paramMode == 'function':
6192 self.fail('Expecting "(" in parameters-and-qualifiers.')
6193 else:
6194 return None
6195 args = []
6196 self.skip_ws()
6197 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6198 while 1:
6199 self.skip_ws()
6200 if self.skip_string('...'):
6201 args.append(ASTFunctionParameter(None, True))
6202 self.skip_ws()
6203 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6204 self.fail('Expected ")" after "..." in '
6205 'parameters-and-qualifiers.')
6206 break
6207 # note: it seems that function arguments can always be named,
6208 # even in function pointers and similar.
6209 arg = self._parse_type_with_init(outer=None, named='single')
6210 # TODO: parse default parameters # TODO: didn't we just do that?
6211 args.append(ASTFunctionParameter(arg))
6212  
6213 self.skip_ws()
6214 if self.skip_string(','):
6215 continue
6216 if self.skip_string(')'):
6217 break
6218 self.fail('Expecting "," or ")" in parameters-and-qualifiers, '
6219 f'got "{self.current_char}".')
6220  
6221 self.skip_ws()
6222 const = self.skip_word_and_ws('const')
6223 volatile = self.skip_word_and_ws('volatile')
6224 if not const: # the can be permuted
6225 const = self.skip_word_and_ws('const')
6226  
6227 refQual = None
6228 if self.skip_string('&&'):
6229 refQual = '&&'
6230 if not refQual and self.skip_string('&'):
6231 refQual = '&'
6232  
6233 exceptionSpec = None
6234 self.skip_ws()
6235 if self.skip_string('noexcept'):
6236 if self.skip_string_and_ws('('):
6237 expr = self._parse_constant_expression(False)
6238 self.skip_ws()
6239 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6240 self.fail("Expecting ')' to end 'noexcept'.")
6241 exceptionSpec = ASTNoexceptSpec(expr)
6242 else:
6243 exceptionSpec = ASTNoexceptSpec(None)
6244  
6245 self.skip_ws()
6246 if self.skip_string('->'):
6247 trailingReturn = self._parse_type(named=False)
6248 else:
6249 trailingReturn = None
6250  
6251 self.skip_ws()
6252 override = self.skip_word_and_ws('override')
6253 final = self.skip_word_and_ws('final')
6254 if not override:
6255 override = self.skip_word_and_ws(
6256 'override') # they can be permuted
6257  
6258 attrs = self._parse_attribute_list()
6259  
6260 self.skip_ws()
6261 initializer = None
6262 # if this is a function pointer we should not swallow an initializer
6263 if paramMode == 'function' and self.skip_string('='):
6264 self.skip_ws()
6265 valid = ('0', 'delete', 'default')
6266 for w in valid:
6267 if self.skip_word_and_ws(w):
6268 initializer = w
6269 break
6270 if not initializer:
6271 self.fail(
6272 'Expected "%s" in initializer-specifier.'
6273 % '" or "'.join(valid))
6274  
6275 return ASTParametersQualifiers(
6276 args, volatile, const, refQual, exceptionSpec, trailingReturn,
6277 override, final, attrs, initializer)
6278  
6279 def _parse_decl_specs_simple(self, outer: str, typed: bool) -> ASTDeclSpecsSimple:
6280 """Just parse the simple ones."""
6281 storage = None
6282 threadLocal = None
6283 inline = None
6284 virtual = None
6285 explicitSpec = None
6286 consteval = None
6287 constexpr = None
6288 constinit = None
6289 volatile = None
6290 const = None
6291 friend = None
6292 attrs = []
6293 while 1: # accept any permutation of a subset of some decl-specs
6294 self.skip_ws()
6295 if not const and typed:
6296 const = self.skip_word('const')
6297 if const:
6298 continue
6299 if not volatile and typed:
6300 volatile = self.skip_word('volatile')
6301 if volatile:
6302 continue
6303 if not storage:
6304 if outer in ('member', 'function'):
6305 if self.skip_word('static'):
6306 storage = 'static'
6307 continue
6308 if self.skip_word('extern'):
6309 storage = 'extern'
6310 continue
6311 if outer == 'member':
6312 if self.skip_word('mutable'):
6313 storage = 'mutable'
6314 continue
6315 if self.skip_word('register'):
6316 storage = 'register'
6317 continue
6318 if not inline and outer in ('function', 'member'):
6319 inline = self.skip_word('inline')
6320 if inline:
6321 continue
6322 if not constexpr and outer in ('member', 'function'):
6323 constexpr = self.skip_word("constexpr")
6324 if constexpr:
6325 continue
6326  
6327 if outer == 'member':
6328 if not constinit:
6329 constinit = self.skip_word('constinit')
6330 if constinit:
6331 continue
6332 if not threadLocal:
6333 threadLocal = self.skip_word('thread_local')
6334 if threadLocal:
6335 continue
6336 if outer == 'function':
6337 if not consteval:
6338 consteval = self.skip_word('consteval')
6339 if consteval:
6340 continue
6341 if not friend:
6342 friend = self.skip_word('friend')
6343 if friend:
6344 continue
6345 if not virtual:
6346 virtual = self.skip_word('virtual')
6347 if virtual:
6348 continue
6349 if not explicitSpec:
6350 explicit = self.skip_word_and_ws('explicit')
6351 if explicit:
6352 expr: ASTExpression = None
6353 if self.skip_string('('):
6354 expr = self._parse_constant_expression(inTemplate=False)
6355 if not expr:
6356 self.fail("Expected constant expression after '('" +
6357 " in explicit specifier.")
6358 self.skip_ws()
6359 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6360 self.fail("Expected ')' to end explicit specifier.")
6361 explicitSpec = ASTExplicitSpec(expr)
6362 continue
6363 attr = self._parse_attribute()
6364 if attr:
6365 attrs.append(attr)
6366 continue
6367 break
6368 return ASTDeclSpecsSimple(storage, threadLocal, inline, virtual,
6369 explicitSpec, consteval, constexpr, constinit,
6370 volatile, const, friend, ASTAttributeList(attrs))
6371  
6372 def _parse_decl_specs(self, outer: str, typed: bool = True) -> ASTDeclSpecs:
6373 if outer:
6374 if outer not in ('type', 'member', 'function', 'templateParam'):
6375 raise Exception('Internal error, unknown outer "%s".' % outer)
6376 """
6377 storage-class-specifier function-specifier "constexpr"
6378 "volatile" "const" trailing-type-specifier
6379  
6380 storage-class-specifier ->
6381 "static" (only for member_object and function_object)
6382 | "register"
6383  
6384 function-specifier -> "inline" | "virtual" | "explicit" (only for
6385 function_object)
6386  
6387 "constexpr" (only for member_object and function_object)
6388 """
6389 leftSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs_simple(outer, typed)
6390 rightSpecs = None
6391  
6392 if typed:
6393 trailing = self._parse_trailing_type_spec()
6394 rightSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs_simple(outer, typed)
6395 else:
6396 trailing = None
6397 return ASTDeclSpecs(outer, leftSpecs, rightSpecs, trailing)
6398  
6399 def _parse_declarator_name_suffix(
6400 self, named: bool | str, paramMode: str, typed: bool,
6401 ) -> ASTDeclaratorNameParamQual | ASTDeclaratorNameBitField:
6402 # now we should parse the name, and then suffixes
6403 if named == 'maybe':
6404 pos = self.pos
6405 try:
6406 declId = self._parse_nested_name()
6407 except DefinitionError:
6408 self.pos = pos
6409 declId = None
6410 elif named == 'single':
6411 if self.match(identifier_re):
6412 identifier = ASTIdentifier(self.matched_text)
6413 nne = ASTNestedNameElement(identifier, None)
6414 declId = ASTNestedName([nne], [False], rooted=False)
6415 # if it's a member pointer, we may have '::', which should be an error
6416 self.skip_ws()
6417 if self.current_char == ':':
6418 self.fail("Unexpected ':' after identifier.")
6419 else:
6420 declId = None
6421 elif named:
6422 declId = self._parse_nested_name()
6423 else:
6424 declId = None
6425 arrayOps = []
6426 while 1:
6427 self.skip_ws()
6428 if typed and self.skip_string('['):
6429 self.skip_ws()
6430 if self.skip_string(']'):
6431 arrayOps.append(ASTArray(None))
6432 continue
6433  
6434 def parser() -> ASTExpression:
6435 return self._parse_expression()
6436 value = self._parse_expression_fallback([']'], parser)
6437 if not self.skip_string(']'):
6438 self.fail("Expected ']' in end of array operator.")
6439 arrayOps.append(ASTArray(value))
6440 continue
6441 break
6442 paramQual = self._parse_parameters_and_qualifiers(paramMode)
6443 if paramQual is None and len(arrayOps) == 0:
6444 # perhaps a bit-field
6445 if named and paramMode == 'type' and typed:
6446 self.skip_ws()
6447 if self.skip_string(':'):
6448 size = self._parse_constant_expression(inTemplate=False)
6449 return ASTDeclaratorNameBitField(declId=declId, size=size)
6450 return ASTDeclaratorNameParamQual(declId=declId, arrayOps=arrayOps,
6451 paramQual=paramQual)
6452  
6453 def _parse_declarator(self, named: bool | str, paramMode: str,
6454 typed: bool = True,
6455 ) -> ASTDeclarator:
6456 # 'typed' here means 'parse return type stuff'
6457 if paramMode not in ('type', 'function', 'operatorCast', 'new'):
6458 raise Exception(
6459 "Internal error, unknown paramMode '%s'." % paramMode)
6460 prevErrors = []
6461 self.skip_ws()
6462 if typed and self.skip_string('*'):
6463 self.skip_ws()
6464 volatile = False
6465 const = False
6466 attrList = []
6467 while 1:
6468 if not volatile:
6469 volatile = self.skip_word_and_ws('volatile')
6470 if volatile:
6471 continue
6472 if not const:
6473 const = self.skip_word_and_ws('const')
6474 if const:
6475 continue
6476 attr = self._parse_attribute()
6477 if attr is not None:
6478 attrList.append(attr)
6479 continue
6480 break
6481 next = self._parse_declarator(named, paramMode, typed)
6482 return ASTDeclaratorPtr(next=next, volatile=volatile, const=const,
6483 attrs=ASTAttributeList(attrList))
6484 # TODO: shouldn't we parse an R-value ref here first?
6485 if typed and self.skip_string("&"):
6486 attrs = self._parse_attribute_list()
6487 next = self._parse_declarator(named, paramMode, typed)
6488 return ASTDeclaratorRef(next=next, attrs=attrs)
6489 if typed and self.skip_string("..."):
6490 next = self._parse_declarator(named, paramMode, False)
6491 return ASTDeclaratorParamPack(next=next)
6492 if typed and self.current_char == '(': # note: peeking, not skipping
6493 if paramMode == "operatorCast":
6494 # TODO: we should be able to parse cast operators which return
6495 # function pointers. For now, just hax it and ignore.
6496 return ASTDeclaratorNameParamQual(declId=None, arrayOps=[],
6497 paramQual=None)
6498 # maybe this is the beginning of params and quals,try that first,
6499 # otherwise assume it's noptr->declarator > ( ptr-declarator )
6500 pos = self.pos
6501 try:
6502 # assume this is params and quals
6503 res = self._parse_declarator_name_suffix(named, paramMode,
6504 typed)
6505 return res
6506 except DefinitionError as exParamQual:
6507 prevErrors.append((exParamQual,
6508 "If declarator-id with parameters-and-qualifiers"))
6509 self.pos = pos
6510 try:
6511 assert self.current_char == '('
6512 self.skip_string('(')
6513 # TODO: hmm, if there is a name, it must be in inner, right?
6514 # TODO: hmm, if there must be parameters, they must be
6515 # inside, right?
6516 inner = self._parse_declarator(named, paramMode, typed)
6517 if not self.skip_string(')'):
6518 self.fail("Expected ')' in \"( ptr-declarator )\"")
6519 next = self._parse_declarator(named=False,
6520 paramMode="type",
6521 typed=typed)
6522 return ASTDeclaratorParen(inner=inner, next=next)
6523 except DefinitionError as exNoPtrParen:
6524 self.pos = pos
6525 prevErrors.append((exNoPtrParen, "If parenthesis in noptr-declarator"))
6526 header = "Error in declarator"
6527 raise self._make_multi_error(prevErrors, header) from exNoPtrParen
6528 if typed: # pointer to member
6529 pos = self.pos
6530 try:
6531 name = self._parse_nested_name(memberPointer=True)
6532 self.skip_ws()
6533 if not self.skip_string('*'):
6534 self.fail("Expected '*' in pointer to member declarator.")
6535 self.skip_ws()
6536 except DefinitionError as e:
6537 self.pos = pos
6538 prevErrors.append((e, "If pointer to member declarator"))
6539 else:
6540 volatile = False
6541 const = False
6542 while 1:
6543 if not volatile:
6544 volatile = self.skip_word_and_ws('volatile')
6545 if volatile:
6546 continue
6547 if not const:
6548 const = self.skip_word_and_ws('const')
6549 if const:
6550 continue
6551 break
6552 next = self._parse_declarator(named, paramMode, typed)
6553 return ASTDeclaratorMemPtr(name, const, volatile, next=next)
6554 pos = self.pos
6555 try:
6556 res = self._parse_declarator_name_suffix(named, paramMode, typed)
6557 # this is a heuristic for error messages, for when there is a < after a
6558 # nested name, but it was not a successful template argument list
6559 if self.current_char == '<':
6560 self.otherErrors.append(self._make_multi_error(prevErrors, ""))
6561 return res
6562 except DefinitionError as e:
6563 self.pos = pos
6564 prevErrors.append((e, "If declarator-id"))
6565 header = "Error in declarator or parameters-and-qualifiers"
6566 raise self._make_multi_error(prevErrors, header) from e
6567  
6568 def _parse_initializer(self, outer: str | None = None, allowFallback: bool = True,
6569 ) -> ASTInitializer:
6570 # initializer # global vars
6571 # -> brace-or-equal-initializer
6572 # | '(' expression-list ')'
6573 #
6574 # brace-or-equal-initializer # member vars
6575 # -> '=' initializer-clause
6576 # | braced-init-list
6577 #
6578 # initializer-clause # function params, non-type template params (with '=' in front)
6579 # -> assignment-expression
6580 # | braced-init-list
6581 #
6582 # we don't distinguish between global and member vars, so disallow paren:
6583 #
6584 # -> braced-init-list # var only
6585 # | '=' assignment-expression
6586 # | '=' braced-init-list
6587 self.skip_ws()
6588 if outer == 'member':
6589 bracedInit = self._parse_braced_init_list()
6590 if bracedInit is not None:
6591 return ASTInitializer(bracedInit, hasAssign=False)
6592  
6593 if not self.skip_string('='):
6594 return None
6595  
6596 bracedInit = self._parse_braced_init_list()
6597 if bracedInit is not None:
6598 return ASTInitializer(bracedInit)
6599  
6600 if outer == 'member':
6601 fallbackEnd: list[str] = []
6602 elif outer == 'templateParam':
6603 fallbackEnd = [',', '>']
6604 elif outer is None: # function parameter
6605 fallbackEnd = [',', ')']
6606 else:
6607 self.fail("Internal error, initializer for outer '%s' not "
6608 "implemented." % outer)
6609  
6610 inTemplate = outer == 'templateParam'
6611  
6612 def parser() -> ASTExpression:
6613 return self._parse_assignment_expression(inTemplate=inTemplate)
6614 value = self._parse_expression_fallback(fallbackEnd, parser, allow=allowFallback)
6615 return ASTInitializer(value)
6616  
6617 def _parse_type(self, named: bool | str, outer: str | None = None) -> ASTType:
6618 """
6619 named=False|'maybe'|True: 'maybe' is e.g., for function objects which
6620 doesn't need to name the arguments
6621  
6622 outer == operatorCast: annoying case, we should not take the params
6623 """
6624 if outer: # always named
6625 if outer not in ('type', 'member', 'function',
6626 'operatorCast', 'templateParam'):
6627 raise Exception('Internal error, unknown outer "%s".' % outer)
6628 if outer != 'operatorCast':
6629 assert named
6630 if outer in ('type', 'function'):
6631 # We allow type objects to just be a name.
6632 # Some functions don't have normal return types: constructors,
6633 # destructors, cast operators
6634 prevErrors = []
6635 startPos = self.pos
6636 # first try without the type
6637 try:
6638 declSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs(outer=outer, typed=False)
6639 decl = self._parse_declarator(named=True, paramMode=outer,
6640 typed=False)
6641 mustEnd = True
6642 if outer == 'function':
6643 # Allow trailing requires on functions.
6644 self.skip_ws()
6645 if re.compile(r'requires\b').match(self.definition, self.pos):
6646 mustEnd = False
6647 if mustEnd:
6648 self.assert_end(allowSemicolon=True)
6649 except DefinitionError as exUntyped:
6650 if outer == 'type':
6651 desc = "If just a name"
6652 elif outer == 'function':
6653 desc = "If the function has no return type"
6654 else:
6655 raise AssertionError from exUntyped
6656 prevErrors.append((exUntyped, desc))
6657 self.pos = startPos
6658 try:
6659 declSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs(outer=outer)
6660 decl = self._parse_declarator(named=True, paramMode=outer)
6661 except DefinitionError as exTyped:
6662 self.pos = startPos
6663 if outer == 'type':
6664 desc = "If typedef-like declaration"
6665 elif outer == 'function':
6666 desc = "If the function has a return type"
6667 else:
6668 raise AssertionError from exUntyped
6669 prevErrors.append((exTyped, desc))
6670 # Retain the else branch for easier debugging.
6671 # TODO: it would be nice to save the previous stacktrace
6672 # and output it here.
6673 if True:
6674 if outer == 'type':
6675 header = "Type must be either just a name or a "
6676 header += "typedef-like declaration."
6677 elif outer == 'function':
6678 header = "Error when parsing function declaration."
6679 else:
6680 raise AssertionError from exUntyped
6681 raise self._make_multi_error(prevErrors, header) from exTyped
6682 else: # NoQA: RET506
6683 # For testing purposes.
6684 # do it again to get the proper traceback (how do you
6685 # reliably save a traceback when an exception is
6686 # constructed?)
6687 self.pos = startPos
6688 typed = True
6689 declSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs(outer=outer, typed=typed)
6690 decl = self._parse_declarator(named=True, paramMode=outer,
6691 typed=typed)
6692 else:
6693 paramMode = 'type'
6694 if outer == 'member':
6695 named = True
6696 elif outer == 'operatorCast':
6697 paramMode = 'operatorCast'
6698 outer = None
6699 elif outer == 'templateParam':
6700 named = 'single'
6701 declSpecs = self._parse_decl_specs(outer=outer)
6702 decl = self._parse_declarator(named=named, paramMode=paramMode)
6703 return ASTType(declSpecs, decl)
6704  
6705 def _parse_type_with_init(
6706 self, named: bool | str,
6707 outer: str) -> ASTTypeWithInit | ASTTemplateParamConstrainedTypeWithInit:
6708 if outer:
6709 assert outer in ('type', 'member', 'function', 'templateParam')
6710 type = self._parse_type(outer=outer, named=named)
6711 if outer != 'templateParam':
6712 init = self._parse_initializer(outer=outer)
6713 return ASTTypeWithInit(type, init)
6714 # it could also be a constrained type parameter, e.g., C T = int&
6715 pos = self.pos
6716 eExpr = None
6717 try:
6718 init = self._parse_initializer(outer=outer, allowFallback=False)
6719 # note: init may be None if there is no =
6720 if init is None:
6721 return ASTTypeWithInit(type, None)
6722 # we parsed an expression, so we must have a , or a >,
6723 # otherwise the expression didn't get everything
6724 self.skip_ws()
6725 if self.current_char != ',' and self.current_char != '>':
6726 # pretend it didn't happen
6727 self.pos = pos
6728 init = None
6729 else:
6730 # we assume that it was indeed an expression
6731 return ASTTypeWithInit(type, init)
6732 except DefinitionError as e:
6733 self.pos = pos
6734 eExpr = e
6735 if not self.skip_string("="):
6736 return ASTTypeWithInit(type, None)
6737 try:
6738 typeInit = self._parse_type(named=False, outer=None)
6739 return ASTTemplateParamConstrainedTypeWithInit(type, typeInit)
6740 except DefinitionError as eType:
6741 if eExpr is None:
6742 raise
6743 errs = []
6744 errs.append((eExpr, "If default template argument is an expression"))
6745 errs.append((eType, "If default template argument is a type"))
6746 msg = "Error in non-type template parameter"
6747 msg += " or constrained template parameter."
6748 raise self._make_multi_error(errs, msg) from eType
6749  
6750 def _parse_type_using(self) -> ASTTypeUsing:
6751 name = self._parse_nested_name()
6752 self.skip_ws()
6753 if not self.skip_string('='):
6754 return ASTTypeUsing(name, None)
6755 type = self._parse_type(False, None)
6756 return ASTTypeUsing(name, type)

6758 def _parse_concept(self) -> ASTConcept:
6759 nestedName = self._parse_nested_name()
6760 self.skip_ws()
6761 initializer = self._parse_initializer('member')
6762 return ASTConcept(nestedName, initializer)

6764 def _parse_class(self) -> ASTClass:
6765 attrs = self._parse_attribute_list()
6766 name = self._parse_nested_name()
6767 self.skip_ws()
6768 final = self.skip_word_and_ws('final')
6769 bases = []
6770 self.skip_ws()
6771 if self.skip_string(':'):
6772 while 1:
6773 self.skip_ws()
6774 visibility = None
6775 virtual = False
6776 pack = False
6777 if self.skip_word_and_ws('virtual'):
6778 virtual = True
6779 if self.match(_visibility_re):
6780 visibility = self.matched_text
6781 self.skip_ws()
6782 if not virtual and self.skip_word_and_ws('virtual'):
6783 virtual = True
6784 baseName = self._parse_nested_name()
6785 self.skip_ws()
6786 pack = self.skip_string('...')
6787 bases.append(ASTBaseClass(baseName, visibility, virtual, pack))
6788 self.skip_ws()
6789 if self.skip_string(','):
6790 continue
6791 break
6792 return ASTClass(name, final, bases, attrs)

6794 def _parse_union(self) -> ASTUnion:
6795 attrs = self._parse_attribute_list()
6796 name = self._parse_nested_name()
6797 return ASTUnion(name, attrs)
6798  
6799 def _parse_enum(self) -> ASTEnum:
6800 scoped = None # is set by CPPEnumObject
6801 attrs = self._parse_attribute_list()
6802 name = self._parse_nested_name()
6803 self.skip_ws()
6804 underlyingType = None
6805 if self.skip_string(':'):
6806 underlyingType = self._parse_type(named=False)
6807 return ASTEnum(name, scoped, underlyingType, attrs)
6808  
6809 def _parse_enumerator(self) -> ASTEnumerator:
6810 name = self._parse_nested_name()
6811 attrs = self._parse_attribute_list()
6812 self.skip_ws()
6813 init = None
6814 if self.skip_string('='):
6815 self.skip_ws()
6816  
6817 def parser() -> ASTExpression:
6818 return self._parse_constant_expression(inTemplate=False)
6819 initVal = self._parse_expression_fallback([], parser)
6820 init = ASTInitializer(initVal)
6821 return ASTEnumerator(name, init, attrs)

6825 def _parse_template_parameter(self) -> ASTTemplateParam:
6826 self.skip_ws()
6827 if self.skip_word('template'):
6828 # declare a template template parameter
6829 nestedParams = self._parse_template_parameter_list()
6830 else:
6831 nestedParams = None
6832  
6833 pos = self.pos
6834 try:
6835 # Unconstrained type parameter or template type parameter
6836 key = None
6837 self.skip_ws()
6838 if self.skip_word_and_ws('typename'):
6839 key = 'typename'
6840 elif self.skip_word_and_ws('class'):
6841 key = 'class'
6842 elif nestedParams:
6843 self.fail("Expected 'typename' or 'class' after "
6844 "template template parameter list.")
6845 else:
6846 self.fail("Expected 'typename' or 'class' in the "
6847 "beginning of template type parameter.")
6848 self.skip_ws()
6849 parameterPack = self.skip_string('...')
6850 self.skip_ws()
6851 if self.match(identifier_re):
6852 identifier = ASTIdentifier(self.matched_text)
6853 else:
6854 identifier = None
6855 self.skip_ws()
6856 if not parameterPack and self.skip_string('='):
6857 default = self._parse_type(named=False, outer=None)
6858 else:
6859 default = None
6860 if self.current_char not in ',>':
6861 self.fail('Expected "," or ">" after (template) type parameter.')
6862 data = ASTTemplateKeyParamPackIdDefault(key, identifier,
6863 parameterPack, default)
6864 if nestedParams:
6865 return ASTTemplateParamTemplateType(nestedParams, data)
6866 else:
6867 return ASTTemplateParamType(data)
6868 except DefinitionError as eType:
6869 if nestedParams:
6870 raise
6871 try:
6872 # non-type parameter or constrained type parameter
6873 self.pos = pos
6874 param = self._parse_type_with_init('maybe', 'templateParam')
6875 self.skip_ws()
6876 parameterPack = self.skip_string('...')
6877 return ASTTemplateParamNonType(param, parameterPack)
6878 except DefinitionError as eNonType:
6879 self.pos = pos
6880 header = "Error when parsing template parameter."
6881 errs = []
6882 errs.append(
6883 (eType, "If unconstrained type parameter or template type parameter"))
6884 errs.append(
6885 (eNonType, "If constrained type parameter or non-type parameter"))
6886 raise self._make_multi_error(errs, header) from None
6887  
6888 def _parse_template_parameter_list(self) -> ASTTemplateParams:
6889 # only: '<' parameter-list '>'
6890 # we assume that 'template' has just been parsed
6891 templateParams: list[ASTTemplateParam] = []
6892 self.skip_ws()
6893 if not self.skip_string("<"):
6894 self.fail("Expected '<' after 'template'")
6895 while 1:
6896 pos = self.pos
6897 err = None
6898 try:
6899 param = self._parse_template_parameter()
6900 templateParams.append(param)
6901 except DefinitionError as eParam:
6902 self.pos = pos
6903 err = eParam
6904 self.skip_ws()
6905 if self.skip_string('>'):
6906 requiresClause = self._parse_requires_clause()
6907 return ASTTemplateParams(templateParams, requiresClause)
6908 elif self.skip_string(','):
6909 continue
6910 else:
6911 header = "Error in template parameter list."
6912 errs = []
6913 if err:
6914 errs.append((err, "If parameter"))
6915 try:
6916 self.fail('Expected "," or ">".')
6917 except DefinitionError as e:
6918 errs.append((e, "If no parameter"))
6919 logger.debug(errs)
6920 raise self._make_multi_error(errs, header)
6921  
6922 def _parse_template_introduction(self) -> ASTTemplateIntroduction:
6923 pos = self.pos
6924 try:
6925 concept = self._parse_nested_name()
6926 except Exception:
6927 self.pos = pos
6928 return None
6929 self.skip_ws()
6930 if not self.skip_string('{'):
6931 self.pos = pos
6932 return None
6933  
6934 # for sure it must be a template introduction now
6935 params = []
6936 while 1:
6937 self.skip_ws()
6938 parameterPack = self.skip_string('...')
6939 self.skip_ws()
6940 if not self.match(identifier_re):
6941 self.fail("Expected identifier in template introduction list.")
6942 txt_identifier = self.matched_text
6943 # make sure there isn't a keyword
6944 if txt_identifier in _keywords:
6945 self.fail("Expected identifier in template introduction list, "
6946 "got keyword: %s" % txt_identifier)
6947 identifier = ASTIdentifier(txt_identifier)
6948 params.append(ASTTemplateIntroductionParameter(identifier, parameterPack))
6949  
6950 self.skip_ws()
6951 if self.skip_string('}'):
6952 break
6953 if self.skip_string(','):
6954 continue
6955 self.fail('Error in template introduction list. Expected ",", or "}".')
6956 return ASTTemplateIntroduction(concept, params)
6957  
6958 def _parse_requires_clause(self) -> ASTRequiresClause | None:
6959 # requires-clause -> 'requires' constraint-logical-or-expression
6960 # constraint-logical-or-expression
6961 # -> constraint-logical-and-expression
6962 # | constraint-logical-or-expression '||' constraint-logical-and-expression
6963 # constraint-logical-and-expression
6964 # -> primary-expression
6965 # | constraint-logical-and-expression '&&' primary-expression
6966 self.skip_ws()
6967 if not self.skip_word('requires'):
6968 return None
6969  
6970 def parse_and_expr(self: DefinitionParser) -> ASTExpression:
6971 andExprs = []
6972 ops = []
6973 andExprs.append(self._parse_primary_expression())
6974 while True:
6975 self.skip_ws()
6976 oneMore = False
6977 if self.skip_string('&&'):
6978 oneMore = True
6979 ops.append('&&')
6980 elif self.skip_word('and'):
6981 oneMore = True
6982 ops.append('and')
6983 if not oneMore:
6984 break
6985 andExprs.append(self._parse_primary_expression())
6986 if len(andExprs) == 1:
6987 return andExprs[0]
6988 else:
6989 return ASTBinOpExpr(andExprs, ops)
6990  
6991 orExprs = []
6992 ops = []
6993 orExprs.append(parse_and_expr(self))
6994 while True:
6995 self.skip_ws()
6996 oneMore = False
6997 if self.skip_string('||'):
6998 oneMore = True
6999 ops.append('||')
7000 elif self.skip_word('or'):
7001 oneMore = True
7002 ops.append('or')
7003 if not oneMore:
7004 break
7005 orExprs.append(parse_and_expr(self))
7006 if len(orExprs) == 1:
7007 return ASTRequiresClause(orExprs[0])
7008 else:
7009 return ASTRequiresClause(ASTBinOpExpr(orExprs, ops))
7010  
7011 def _parse_template_declaration_prefix(self, objectType: str,
7012 ) -> ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix | None:
7013 templates: list[ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction] = []
7014 while 1:
7015 self.skip_ws()
7016 # the saved position is only used to provide a better error message
7017 params: ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction = None
7018 pos = self.pos
7019 if self.skip_word("template"):
7020 try:
7021 params = self._parse_template_parameter_list()
7022 except DefinitionError as e:
7023 if objectType == 'member' and len(templates) == 0:
7024 return ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix(None)
7025 else:
7026 raise e
7027 if objectType == 'concept' and params.requiresClause is not None:
7028 self.fail('requires-clause not allowed for concept')
7029 else:
7030 params = self._parse_template_introduction()
7031 if not params:
7032 break
7033 if objectType == 'concept' and len(templates) > 0:
7034 self.pos = pos
7035 self.fail("More than 1 template parameter list for concept.")
7036 templates.append(params)
7037 if len(templates) == 0 and objectType == 'concept':
7038 self.fail('Missing template parameter list for concept.')
7039 if len(templates) == 0:
7040 return None
7041 else:
7042 return ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix(templates)
7043  
7044 def _check_template_consistency(self, nestedName: ASTNestedName,
7045 templatePrefix: ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix,
7046 fullSpecShorthand: bool, isMember: bool = False,
7047 ) -> ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix:
7048 numArgs = nestedName.num_templates()
7049 isMemberInstantiation = False
7050 if not templatePrefix:
7051 numParams = 0
7052 else:
7053 if isMember and templatePrefix.templates is None:
7054 numParams = 0
7055 isMemberInstantiation = True
7056 else:
7057 numParams = len(templatePrefix.templates)
7058 if numArgs + 1 < numParams:
7059 self.fail("Too few template argument lists comapred to parameter"
7060 " lists. Argument lists: %d, Parameter lists: %d."
7061 % (numArgs, numParams))
7062 if numArgs > numParams:
7063 numExtra = numArgs - numParams
7064 if not fullSpecShorthand and not isMemberInstantiation:
7065 msg = "Too many template argument lists compared to parameter" \
7066 " lists. Argument lists: %d, Parameter lists: %d," \
7067 " Extra empty parameters lists prepended: %d." \
7068 % (numArgs, numParams, numExtra)
7069 msg += " Declaration:\n\t"
7070 if templatePrefix:
7071 msg += "%s\n\t" % templatePrefix
7072 msg += str(nestedName)
7073 self.warn(msg)
7074  
7075 newTemplates: list[ASTTemplateParams | ASTTemplateIntroduction] = []
7076 for _i in range(numExtra):
7077 newTemplates.append(ASTTemplateParams([], requiresClause=None))
7078 if templatePrefix and not isMemberInstantiation:
7079 newTemplates.extend(templatePrefix.templates)
7080 templatePrefix = ASTTemplateDeclarationPrefix(newTemplates)
7081 return templatePrefix
7082  
7083 def parse_declaration(self, objectType: str, directiveType: str) -> ASTDeclaration:
7084 if objectType not in ('class', 'union', 'function', 'member', 'type',
7085 'concept', 'enum', 'enumerator'):
7086 raise Exception('Internal error, unknown objectType "%s".' % objectType)
7087 if directiveType not in ('class', 'struct', 'union', 'function', 'member', 'var',
7088 'type', 'concept',
7089 'enum', 'enum-struct', 'enum-class', 'enumerator'):
7090 raise Exception('Internal error, unknown directiveType "%s".' % directiveType)
7091 visibility = None
7092 templatePrefix = None
7093 trailingRequiresClause = None
7094 declaration: Any = None
7095  
7096 self.skip_ws()
7097 if self.match(_visibility_re):
7098 visibility = self.matched_text
7099  
7100 if objectType in ('type', 'concept', 'member', 'function', 'class', 'union'):
7101 templatePrefix = self._parse_template_declaration_prefix(objectType)
7102  
7103 if objectType == 'type':
7104 prevErrors = []
7105 pos = self.pos
7106 try:
7107 if not templatePrefix:
7108 declaration = self._parse_type(named=True, outer='type')
7109 except DefinitionError as e:
7110 prevErrors.append((e, "If typedef-like declaration"))
7111 self.pos = pos
7112 pos = self.pos
7113 try:
7114 if not declaration:
7115 declaration = self._parse_type_using()
7116 except DefinitionError as e:
7117 self.pos = pos
7118 prevErrors.append((e, "If type alias or template alias"))
7119 header = "Error in type declaration."
7120 raise self._make_multi_error(prevErrors, header) from e
7121 elif objectType == 'concept':
7122 declaration = self._parse_concept()
7123 elif objectType == 'member':
7124 declaration = self._parse_type_with_init(named=True, outer='member')
7125 elif objectType == 'function':
7126 declaration = self._parse_type(named=True, outer='function')
7127 trailingRequiresClause = self._parse_requires_clause()
7128 elif objectType == 'class':
7129 declaration = self._parse_class()
7130 elif objectType == 'union':
7131 declaration = self._parse_union()
7132 elif objectType == 'enum':
7133 declaration = self._parse_enum()
7134 elif objectType == 'enumerator':
7135 declaration = self._parse_enumerator()
7136 else:
7137 raise AssertionError
7138 templatePrefix = self._check_template_consistency(declaration.name,
7139 templatePrefix,
7140 fullSpecShorthand=False,
7141 isMember=objectType == 'member')
7142 self.skip_ws()
7143 semicolon = self.skip_string(';')
7144 return ASTDeclaration(objectType, directiveType, visibility,
7145 templatePrefix, declaration,
7146 trailingRequiresClause, semicolon)
7147  
7148 def parse_namespace_object(self) -> ASTNamespace:
7149 templatePrefix = self._parse_template_declaration_prefix(objectType="namespace")
7150 name = self._parse_nested_name()
7151 templatePrefix = self._check_template_consistency(name, templatePrefix,
7152 fullSpecShorthand=False)
7153 res = ASTNamespace(name, templatePrefix)
7154 res.objectType = 'namespace' # type: ignore[attr-defined]
7155 return res
7156  
7157 def parse_xref_object(self) -> tuple[ASTNamespace | ASTDeclaration, bool]:
7158 pos = self.pos
7159 try:
7160 templatePrefix = self._parse_template_declaration_prefix(objectType="xref")
7161 name = self._parse_nested_name()
7162 # if there are '()' left, just skip them
7163 self.skip_ws()
7164 self.skip_string('()')
7165 self.assert_end()
7166 templatePrefix = self._check_template_consistency(name, templatePrefix,
7167 fullSpecShorthand=True)
7168 res1 = ASTNamespace(name, templatePrefix)
7169 res1.objectType = 'xref' # type: ignore[attr-defined]
7170 return res1, True
7171 except DefinitionError as e1:
7172 try:
7173 self.pos = pos
7174 res2 = self.parse_declaration('function', 'function')
7175 # if there are '()' left, just skip them
7176 self.skip_ws()
7177 self.skip_string('()')
7178 self.assert_end()
7179 return res2, False
7180 except DefinitionError as e2:
7181 errs = []
7182 errs.append((e1, "If shorthand ref"))
7183 errs.append((e2, "If full function ref"))
7184 msg = "Error in cross-reference."
7185 raise self._make_multi_error(errs, msg) from e2
7186  
7187 def parse_expression(self) -> ASTExpression | ASTType:
7188 pos = self.pos
7189 try:
7190 expr = self._parse_expression()
7191 self.skip_ws()
7192 self.assert_end()
7193 return expr
7194 except DefinitionError as exExpr:
7195 self.pos = pos
7196 try:
7197 typ = self._parse_type(False)
7198 self.skip_ws()
7199 self.assert_end()
7200 return typ
7201 except DefinitionError as exType:
7202 header = "Error when parsing (type) expression."
7203 errs = []
7204 errs.append((exExpr, "If expression"))
7205 errs.append((exType, "If type"))
7206 raise self._make_multi_error(errs, header) from exType
7207  
7208  
7209 def _make_phony_error_name() -> ASTNestedName:
7210 nne = ASTNestedNameElement(ASTIdentifier("PhonyNameDueToError"), None)
7211 return ASTNestedName([nne], [False], rooted=False)

7214 class CPPObject(ObjectDescription[ASTDeclaration]):
7215 """Description of a C++ language object."""
7216  
7217 doc_field_types: list[Field] = [
7218 GroupedField('template parameter', label=_('Template Parameters'),
7219 names=('tparam', 'template parameter'),
7220 can_collapse=True),
7221 ]
7222  
7223 option_spec: OptionSpec = {
7224 'no-index-entry': directives.flag,
7225 'no-contents-entry': directives.flag,
7226 'no-typesetting': directives.flag,
7227 'noindexentry': directives.flag,
7228 'nocontentsentry': directives.flag,
7229 'tparam-line-spec': directives.flag,
7230 'single-line-parameter-list': directives.flag,
7231 }
7232  
7233 def _add_enumerator_to_parent(self, ast: ASTDeclaration) -> None:
7234 assert ast.objectType == 'enumerator'
7235 # find the parent, if it exists && is an enum
7236 # && it's unscoped,
7237 # then add the name to the parent scope
7238 symbol = ast.symbol
7239 assert symbol
7240 assert symbol.identOrOp is not None
7241 assert symbol.templateParams is None
7242 assert symbol.templateArgs is None
7243 parentSymbol = symbol.parent
7244 assert parentSymbol
7245 if parentSymbol.parent is None:
7246 # TODO: we could warn, but it is somewhat equivalent to unscoped
7247 # enums, without the enum
7248 return # no parent
7249 parentDecl = parentSymbol.declaration
7250 if parentDecl is None:
7251 # the parent is not explicitly declared
7252 # TODO: we could warn, but it could be a style to just assume
7253 # enumerator parents to be scoped
7254 return
7255 if parentDecl.objectType != 'enum':
7256 # TODO: maybe issue a warning, enumerators in non-enums is weird,
7257 # but it is somewhat equivalent to unscoped enums, without the enum
7258 return
7259 if parentDecl.directiveType != 'enum':
7260 return
7261  
7262 targetSymbol = parentSymbol.parent
7263 s = targetSymbol.find_identifier(symbol.identOrOp, matchSelf=False, recurseInAnon=True,
7264 searchInSiblings=False)
7265 if s is not None:
7266 # something is already declared with that name
7267 return
7268 declClone = symbol.declaration.clone()
7269 declClone.enumeratorScopedSymbol = symbol
7270 Symbol(parent=targetSymbol, identOrOp=symbol.identOrOp,
7271 templateParams=None, templateArgs=None,
7272 declaration=declClone,
7273 docname=self.env.docname, line=self.get_source_info()[1])
7274  
7275 def add_target_and_index(self, ast: ASTDeclaration, sig: str,
7276 signode: TextElement) -> None:
7277 # general note: name must be lstrip(':')'ed, to remove "::"
7278 ids = []
7279 for i in range(1, _max_id + 1):
7280 try:
7281 id = ast.get_id(version=i)
7282 ids.append(id)
7283 except NoOldIdError:
7284 assert i < _max_id
7285 # let's keep the newest first
7286 ids = list(reversed(ids))
7287 newestId = ids[0]
7288 assert newestId # shouldn't be None
7289 if not re.compile(r'^[a-zA-Z0-9_]*$').match(newestId):
7290 logger.warning('Index id generation for C++ object "%s" failed, please '
7291 'report as bug (id=%s).', ast, newestId,
7292 location=self.get_location())
7293  
7294 name = ast.symbol.get_full_nested_name().get_display_string().lstrip(':')
7295 # Add index entry, but not if it's a declaration inside a concept
7296 isInConcept = False
7297 s = ast.symbol.parent
7298 while s is not None:
7299 decl = s.declaration
7300 s = s.parent
7301 if decl is None:
7302 continue
7303 if decl.objectType == 'concept':
7304 isInConcept = True
7305 break
7306 if not isInConcept and 'no-index-entry' not in self.options:
7307 strippedName = name
7308 for prefix in self.env.config.cpp_index_common_prefix:
7309 if name.startswith(prefix):
7310 strippedName = strippedName[len(prefix):]
7311 break
7312 indexText = self.get_index_text(strippedName)
7313 self.indexnode['entries'].append(('single', indexText, newestId, '', None))
7314  
7315 if newestId not in self.state.document.ids:
7316 # if the name is not unique, the first one will win
7317 names = self.env.domaindata['cpp']['names']
7318 if name not in names:
7319 names[name] = ast.symbol.docname
7320 # always add the newest id
7321 assert newestId
7322 signode['ids'].append(newestId)
7323 # only add compatibility ids when there are no conflicts
7324 for id in ids[1:]:
7325 if not id: # is None when the element didn't exist in that version
7326 continue
7327 if id not in self.state.document.ids:
7328 signode['ids'].append(id)
7329 self.state.document.note_explicit_target(signode)
7330  
7331 @property
7332 def object_type(self) -> str:
7333 raise NotImplementedError
7334  
7335 @property
7336 def display_object_type(self) -> str:
7337 return self.object_type
7338  
7339 def get_index_text(self, name: str) -> str:
7340 return _('%s (C++ %s)') % (name, self.display_object_type)
7341  
7342 def parse_definition(self, parser: DefinitionParser) -> ASTDeclaration:
7343 return parser.parse_declaration(self.object_type, self.objtype)
7344  
7345 def describe_signature(self, signode: desc_signature,
7346 ast: ASTDeclaration, options: dict) -> None:
7347 ast.describe_signature(signode, 'lastIsName', self.env, options)
7348  
7349 def run(self) -> list[Node]:
7350 env = self.state.document.settings.env # from ObjectDescription.run
7351 if 'cpp:parent_symbol' not in env.temp_data:
7352 root = env.domaindata['cpp']['root_symbol']
7353 env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = root
7354 env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = root.get_lookup_key()
7355  
7356 # The lookup keys assume that no nested scopes exists inside overloaded functions.
7357 # (see also #5191)
7358 # Example:
7359 # .. cpp:function:: void f(int)
7360 # .. cpp:function:: void f(double)
7361 #
7362 # .. cpp:function:: void g()
7363 #
7364 # :cpp:any:`boom`
7365 #
7366 # So we disallow any signatures inside functions.
7367 parentSymbol = env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol']
7368 parentDecl = parentSymbol.declaration
7369 if parentDecl is not None and parentDecl.objectType == 'function':
7370 msg = ("C++ declarations inside functions are not supported. "
7371 f"Parent function: {parentSymbol.get_full_nested_name()}\n"
7372 f"Directive name: {self.name}\nDirective arg: {self.arguments[0]}")
7373 logger.warning(msg, location=self.get_location())
7374 name = _make_phony_error_name()
7375 symbol = parentSymbol.add_name(name)
7376 env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol'] = symbol
7377 return []
7378 # When multiple declarations are made in the same directive
7379 # they need to know about each other to provide symbol lookup for function parameters.
7380 # We use last_symbol to store the latest added declaration in a directive.
7381 env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol'] = None
7382 return super().run()
7383  
7384 def handle_signature(self, sig: str, signode: desc_signature) -> ASTDeclaration:
7385 parentSymbol: Symbol = self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol']
7386  
7387 max_len = (self.env.config.cpp_maximum_signature_line_length
7388 or self.env.config.maximum_signature_line_length
7389 or 0)
7390 signode['multi_line_parameter_list'] = (
7391 'single-line-parameter-list' not in self.options
7392 and (len(sig) > max_len > 0)
7393 )
7394  
7395 parser = DefinitionParser(sig, location=signode, config=self.env.config)
7396 try:
7397 ast = self.parse_definition(parser)
7398 parser.assert_end()
7399 except DefinitionError as e:
7400 logger.warning(e, location=signode)
7401 # It is easier to assume some phony name than handling the error in
7402 # the possibly inner declarations.
7403 name = _make_phony_error_name()
7404 symbol = parentSymbol.add_name(name)
7405 self.env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol'] = symbol
7406 raise ValueError from e
7407  
7408 try:
7409 symbol = parentSymbol.add_declaration(
7410 ast, docname=self.env.docname, line=self.get_source_info()[1])
7411 # append the new declaration to the sibling list
7412 assert symbol.siblingAbove is None
7413 assert symbol.siblingBelow is None
7414 symbol.siblingAbove = self.env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol']
7415 if symbol.siblingAbove is not None:
7416 assert symbol.siblingAbove.siblingBelow is None
7417 symbol.siblingAbove.siblingBelow = symbol
7418 self.env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol'] = symbol
7419 except _DuplicateSymbolError as e:
7420 # Assume we are actually in the old symbol,
7421 # instead of the newly created duplicate.
7422 self.env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol'] = e.symbol
7423 msg = __("Duplicate C++ declaration, also defined at %s:%s.\n"
7424 "Declaration is '.. cpp:%s:: %s'.")
7425 msg = msg % (e.symbol.docname, e.symbol.line,
7426 self.display_object_type, sig)
7427 logger.warning(msg, location=signode)
7428  
7429 if ast.objectType == 'enumerator':
7430 self._add_enumerator_to_parent(ast)
7431  
7432 # note: handle_signature may be called multiple time per directive,
7433 # if it has multiple signatures, so don't mess with the original options.
7434 options = dict(self.options)
7435 options['tparam-line-spec'] = 'tparam-line-spec' in self.options
7436 self.describe_signature(signode, ast, options)
7437 return ast
7438  
7439 def before_content(self) -> None:
7440 lastSymbol: Symbol = self.env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol']
7441 assert lastSymbol
7442 self.oldParentSymbol = self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol']
7443 self.oldParentKey: LookupKey = self.env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key']
7444 self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = lastSymbol
7445 self.env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = lastSymbol.get_lookup_key()
7446 self.env.temp_data['cpp:domain_name'] = (
7447 *self.env.temp_data.get('cpp:domain_name', ()),
7448 lastSymbol.identOrOp._stringify(str),
7449 )
7450  
7451 def after_content(self) -> None:
7452 self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = self.oldParentSymbol
7453 self.env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = self.oldParentKey
7454 self.env.temp_data['cpp:domain_name'] = self.env.temp_data['cpp:domain_name'][:-1]
7455  
7456 def _object_hierarchy_parts(self, sig_node: desc_signature) -> tuple[str, ...]:
7457 return tuple(s.identOrOp._stringify(str) for s in
7458 self.env.temp_data['cpp:last_symbol'].get_full_nested_name().names)
7459  
7460 def _toc_entry_name(self, sig_node: desc_signature) -> str:
7461 if not sig_node.get('_toc_parts'):
7462 return ''
7463  
7464 config = self.env.app.config
7465 objtype = sig_node.parent.get('objtype')
7466 if config.add_function_parentheses and objtype in {'function', 'method'}:
7467 parens = '()'
7468 else:
7469 parens = ''
7470 *parents, name = sig_node['_toc_parts']
7471 if config.toc_object_entries_show_parents == 'domain':
7472 return '::'.join((*self.env.temp_data.get('cpp:domain_name', ()), name + parens))
7473 if config.toc_object_entries_show_parents == 'hide':
7474 return name + parens
7475 if config.toc_object_entries_show_parents == 'all':
7476 return '::'.join(parents + [name + parens])
7477 return ''
