7532 class CPPNamespaceObject(SphinxDirective):
7533 """
7534 This directive is just to tell Sphinx that we're documenting stuff in
7535 namespace foo.
7536 """
7537  
7538 has_content = False
7539 required_arguments = 1
7540 optional_arguments = 0
7541 final_argument_whitespace = True
7542 option_spec: OptionSpec = {}
7543  
7544 def run(self) -> list[Node]:
7545 rootSymbol = self.env.domaindata['cpp']['root_symbol']
7546 if self.arguments[0].strip() in ('NULL', '0', 'nullptr'):
7547 symbol = rootSymbol
7548 stack: list[Symbol] = []
7549 else:
7550 parser = DefinitionParser(self.arguments[0],
7551 location=self.get_location(),
7552 config=self.config)
7553 try:
7554 ast = parser.parse_namespace_object()
7555 parser.assert_end()
7556 except DefinitionError as e:
7557 logger.warning(e, location=self.get_location())
7558 name = _make_phony_error_name()
7559 ast = ASTNamespace(name, None)
7560 symbol = rootSymbol.add_name(ast.nestedName, ast.templatePrefix)
7561 stack = [symbol]
7562 self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = symbol
7563 self.env.temp_data['cpp:namespace_stack'] = stack
7564 self.env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = symbol.get_lookup_key()
7565 return []

7568 class CPPNamespacePushObject(SphinxDirective):
7569 has_content = False
7570 required_arguments = 1
7571 optional_arguments = 0
7572 final_argument_whitespace = True
7573 option_spec: OptionSpec = {}
7574  
7575 def run(self) -> list[Node]:
7576 if self.arguments[0].strip() in ('NULL', '0', 'nullptr'):
7577 return []
7578 parser = DefinitionParser(self.arguments[0],
7579 location=self.get_location(),
7580 config=self.config)
7581 try:
7582 ast = parser.parse_namespace_object()
7583 parser.assert_end()
7584 except DefinitionError as e:
7585 logger.warning(e, location=self.get_location())
7586 name = _make_phony_error_name()
7587 ast = ASTNamespace(name, None)
7588 oldParent = self.env.temp_data.get('cpp:parent_symbol', None)
7589 if not oldParent:
7590 oldParent = self.env.domaindata['cpp']['root_symbol']
7591 symbol = oldParent.add_name(ast.nestedName, ast.templatePrefix)
7592 stack = self.env.temp_data.get('cpp:namespace_stack', [])
7593 stack.append(symbol)
7594 self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = symbol
7595 self.env.temp_data['cpp:namespace_stack'] = stack
7596 self.env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = symbol.get_lookup_key()
7597 return []

7600 class CPPNamespacePopObject(SphinxDirective):
7601 has_content = False
7602 required_arguments = 0
7603 optional_arguments = 0
7604 final_argument_whitespace = True
7605 option_spec: OptionSpec = {}
7606  
7607 def run(self) -> list[Node]:
7608 stack = self.env.temp_data.get('cpp:namespace_stack', None)
7609 if not stack or len(stack) == 0:
7610 logger.warning("C++ namespace pop on empty stack. Defaulting to global scope.",
7611 location=self.get_location())
7612 stack = []
7613 else:
7614 stack.pop()
7615 if len(stack) > 0:
7616 symbol = stack[-1]
7617 else:
7618 symbol = self.env.domaindata['cpp']['root_symbol']
7619 self.env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = symbol
7620 self.env.temp_data['cpp:namespace_stack'] = stack
7621 self.env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = symbol.get_lookup_key()
7622 return []

7625 class AliasNode(nodes.Element):
7626 def __init__(self, sig: str, aliasOptions: dict,
7627 env: BuildEnvironment | None = None,
7628 parentKey: LookupKey | None = None) -> None:
7629 super().__init__()
7630 self.sig = sig
7631 self.aliasOptions = aliasOptions
7632 if env is not None:
7633 if 'cpp:parent_symbol' not in env.temp_data:
7634 root = env.domaindata['cpp']['root_symbol']
7635 env.temp_data['cpp:parent_symbol'] = root
7636 env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key'] = root.get_lookup_key()
7637 self.parentKey = env.ref_context['cpp:parent_key']
7638 else:
7639 assert parentKey is not None
7640 self.parentKey = parentKey
7641  
7642 def copy(self) -> AliasNode:
7643 return self.__class__(self.sig, self.aliasOptions,
7644 env=None, parentKey=self.parentKey)
7645  
7646  
7647 class AliasTransform(SphinxTransform):
7648 default_priority = ReferencesResolver.default_priority - 1
7649  
7650 def _render_symbol(self, s: Symbol, maxdepth: int, skipThis: bool,
7651 aliasOptions: dict, renderOptions: dict,
7652 document: Any) -> list[Node]:
7653 if maxdepth == 0:
7654 recurse = True
7655 elif maxdepth == 1:
7656 recurse = False
7657 else:
7658 maxdepth -= 1
7659 recurse = True
7660  
7661 nodes: list[Node] = []
7662 if not skipThis:
7663 signode = addnodes.desc_signature('', '')
7664 nodes.append(signode)
7665 s.declaration.describe_signature(signode, 'markName', self.env, renderOptions)
7666  
7667 if recurse:
7668 if skipThis:
7669 childContainer: list[Node] | addnodes.desc = nodes
7670 else:
7671 content = addnodes.desc_content()
7672 desc = addnodes.desc()
7673 content.append(desc)
7674 desc.document = document
7675 desc['domain'] = 'cpp'
7676 # 'desctype' is a backwards compatible attribute
7677 desc['objtype'] = desc['desctype'] = 'alias'
7678 desc['no-index'] = True
7679 childContainer = desc
7680  
7681 for sChild in s._children:
7682 if sChild.declaration is None:
7683 continue
7684 if sChild.declaration.objectType in ("templateParam", "functionParam"):
7685 continue
7686 childNodes = self._render_symbol(
7687 sChild, maxdepth=maxdepth, skipThis=False,
7688 aliasOptions=aliasOptions, renderOptions=renderOptions,
7689 document=document)
7690 childContainer.extend(childNodes)
7691  
7692 if not skipThis and len(desc.children) != 0:
7693 nodes.append(content)
7694 return nodes
7695  
7696 def apply(self, **kwargs: Any) -> None:
7697 for node in self.document.findall(AliasNode):
7698 sig = node.sig
7699 parentKey = node.parentKey
7700 try:
7701 parser = DefinitionParser(sig, location=node,
7702 config=self.env.config)
7703 ast, isShorthand = parser.parse_xref_object()
7704 parser.assert_end()
7705 except DefinitionError as e:
7706 logger.warning(e, location=node)
7707 ast, isShorthand = None, None
7708  
7709 if ast is None:
7710 # could not be parsed, so stop here
7711 signode = addnodes.desc_signature(sig, '')
7712 signode.clear()
7713 signode += addnodes.desc_name(sig, sig)
7714 node.replace_self(signode)
7715 continue
7716  
7717 rootSymbol: Symbol = self.env.domains['cpp'].data['root_symbol']
7718 parentSymbol: Symbol = rootSymbol.direct_lookup(parentKey)
7719 if not parentSymbol:
7720 logger.debug("Target: %s", sig)
7721 logger.debug("ParentKey: %s", parentKey)
7722 logger.debug(rootSymbol.dump(1))
7723 assert parentSymbol # should be there
7724  
7725 symbols: list[Symbol] = []
7726 if isShorthand:
7727 assert isinstance(ast, ASTNamespace)
7728 ns = ast
7729 name = ns.nestedName
7730 if ns.templatePrefix:
7731 templateDecls = ns.templatePrefix.templates
7732 else:
7733 templateDecls = []
7734 symbols, failReason = parentSymbol.find_name(
7735 nestedName=name,
7736 templateDecls=templateDecls,
7737 typ='any',
7738 templateShorthand=True,
7739 matchSelf=True, recurseInAnon=True,
7740 searchInSiblings=False)
7741 if symbols is None:
7742 symbols = []
7743 else:
7744 assert isinstance(ast, ASTDeclaration)
7745 decl = ast
7746 name = decl.name
7747 s = parentSymbol.find_declaration(decl, 'any',
7748 templateShorthand=True,
7749 matchSelf=True, recurseInAnon=True)
7750 if s is not None:
7751 symbols.append(s)
7752  
7753 symbols = [s for s in symbols if s.declaration is not None]
7754  
7755 if len(symbols) == 0:
7756 signode = addnodes.desc_signature(sig, '')
7757 node.append(signode)
7758 signode.clear()
7759 signode += addnodes.desc_name(sig, sig)
7760  
7761 logger.warning("Can not find C++ declaration for alias '%s'." % ast,
7762 location=node)
7763 node.replace_self(signode)
7764 else:
7765 nodes = []
7766 renderOptions = {
7767 'tparam-line-spec': False,
7768 }
7769 for s in symbols:
7770 assert s.declaration is not None
7771 res = self._render_symbol(
7772 s, maxdepth=node.aliasOptions['maxdepth'],
7773 skipThis=node.aliasOptions['noroot'],
7774 aliasOptions=node.aliasOptions,
7775 renderOptions=renderOptions,
7776 document=node.document)
7777 nodes.extend(res)
7778 node.replace_self(nodes)
7779  
7780  
7781 class CPPAliasObject(ObjectDescription):
7782 option_spec: OptionSpec = {
7783 'maxdepth': directives.nonnegative_int,
7784 'noroot': directives.flag,
7785 }
7786  
7787 def run(self) -> list[Node]:
7788 """
7789 On purpose this doesn't call the ObjectDescription version, but is based on it.
7790 Each alias signature may expand into multiple real signatures (an overload set).
7791 The code is therefore based on the ObjectDescription version.
7792 """
7793 if ':' in self.name:
7794 self.domain, self.objtype = self.name.split(':', 1)
7795 else:
7796 self.domain, self.objtype = '', self.name
7797  
7798 node = addnodes.desc()
7799 node.document = self.state.document
7800 node['domain'] = self.domain
7801 # 'desctype' is a backwards compatible attribute
7802 node['objtype'] = node['desctype'] = self.objtype
7803  
7804 self.names: list[str] = []
7805 aliasOptions = {
7806 'maxdepth': self.options.get('maxdepth', 1),
7807 'noroot': 'noroot' in self.options,
7808 }
7809 if aliasOptions['noroot'] and aliasOptions['maxdepth'] == 1:
7810 logger.warning("Error in C++ alias declaration."
7811 " Requested 'noroot' but 'maxdepth' 1."
7812 " When skipping the root declaration,"
7813 " need 'maxdepth' 0 for infinite or at least 2.",
7814 location=self.get_location())
7815 signatures = self.get_signatures()
7816 for sig in signatures:
7817 node.append(AliasNode(sig, aliasOptions, env=self.env))
7818  
7819 contentnode = addnodes.desc_content()
7820 node.append(contentnode)
7821 self.before_content()
7822 self.state.nested_parse(self.content, self.content_offset, contentnode)
7823 self.env.temp_data['object'] = None
7824 self.after_content()
7825 return [node]
7826  
7827  
7828 class CPPXRefRole(XRefRole):
7829 def process_link(self, env: BuildEnvironment, refnode: Element, has_explicit_title: bool,
7830 title: str, target: str) -> tuple[str, str]:
7831 refnode.attributes.update(env.ref_context)
7832  
7833 if not has_explicit_title:
7834 # major hax: replace anon names via simple string manipulation.
7835 # Can this actually fail?
7836 title = anon_identifier_re.sub("[anonymous]", str(title))
7837  
7838 if refnode['reftype'] == 'any':
7839 # Assume the removal part of fix_parens for :any: refs.
7840 # The addition part is done with the reference is resolved.
7841 if not has_explicit_title and title.endswith('()'):
7842 title = title[:-2]
7843 if target.endswith('()'):
7844 target = target[:-2]
7845 # TODO: should this really be here?
7846 if not has_explicit_title:
7847 target = target.lstrip('~') # only has a meaning for the title
7848 # if the first character is a tilde, don't display the module/class
7849 # parts of the contents
7850 if title[:1] == '~':
7851 title = title[1:]
7852 dcolon = title.rfind('::')
7853 if dcolon != -1:
7854 title = title[dcolon + 2:]
7855 return title, target
7856  
7857  
7858 class CPPExprRole(SphinxRole):
7859 def __init__(self, asCode: bool) -> None:
7860 super().__init__()
7861 if asCode:
7862 # render the expression as inline code
7863 self.class_type = 'cpp-expr'
7864 else:
7865 # render the expression as inline text
7866 self.class_type = 'cpp-texpr'
7867  
7868 def run(self) -> tuple[list[Node], list[system_message]]:
7869 text = self.text.replace('\n', ' ')
7870 parser = DefinitionParser(text,
7871 location=self.get_location(),
7872 config=self.config)
7873 # attempt to mimic XRefRole classes, except that...
7874 try:
7875 ast = parser.parse_expression()
7876 except DefinitionError as ex:
7877 logger.warning('Unparseable C++ expression: %r\n%s', text, ex,
7878 location=self.get_location())
7879 # see below
7880 return [addnodes.desc_inline('cpp', text, text, classes=[self.class_type])], []
7881 parentSymbol = self.env.temp_data.get('cpp:parent_symbol', None)
7882 if parentSymbol is None:
7883 parentSymbol = self.env.domaindata['cpp']['root_symbol']
7884 # ...most if not all of these classes should really apply to the individual references,
7885 # not the container node
7886 signode = addnodes.desc_inline('cpp', classes=[self.class_type])
7887 ast.describe_signature(signode, 'markType', self.env, parentSymbol)
7888 return [signode], []

7890  
7891 class CPPDomain(Domain):
7892 """C++ language domain.
7893  
7894 There are two 'object type' attributes being used::
7895  
7896 - Each object created from directives gets an assigned .objtype from ObjectDescription.run.
7897 This is simply the directive name.
7898 - Each declaration (see the distinction in the directives dict below) has a nested .ast of
7899 type ASTDeclaration. That object has .objectType which corresponds to the keys in the
7900 object_types dict below. They are the core different types of declarations in C++ that
7901 one can document.
7902 """
7903 name = 'cpp'
7904 label = 'C++'
7905 object_types = {
7906 'class': ObjType(_('class'), 'class', 'struct', 'identifier', 'type'),
7907 'union': ObjType(_('union'), 'union', 'identifier', 'type'),
7908 'function': ObjType(_('function'), 'func', 'identifier', 'type'),
7909 'member': ObjType(_('member'), 'member', 'var', 'identifier'),
7910 'type': ObjType(_('type'), 'identifier', 'type'),
7911 'concept': ObjType(_('concept'), 'concept', 'identifier'),
7912 'enum': ObjType(_('enum'), 'enum', 'identifier', 'type'),
7913 'enumerator': ObjType(_('enumerator'), 'enumerator', 'identifier'),
7914 # generated object types
7915 'functionParam': ObjType(_('function parameter'), 'identifier', 'member', 'var'), # noqa: E501
7916 'templateParam': ObjType(_('template parameter'),
7917 'identifier', 'class', 'struct', 'union', 'member', 'var', 'type'), # noqa: E501
7918 }
7919  
7920 directives = {
7921 # declarations
7922 'class': CPPClassObject,
7923 'struct': CPPClassObject,
7924 'union': CPPUnionObject,
7925 'function': CPPFunctionObject,
7926 'member': CPPMemberObject,
7927 'var': CPPMemberObject,
7928 'type': CPPTypeObject,
7929 'concept': CPPConceptObject,
7930 'enum': CPPEnumObject,
7931 'enum-struct': CPPEnumObject,
7932 'enum-class': CPPEnumObject,
7933 'enumerator': CPPEnumeratorObject,
7934 # scope control
7935 'namespace': CPPNamespaceObject,
7936 'namespace-push': CPPNamespacePushObject,
7937 'namespace-pop': CPPNamespacePopObject,
7938 # other
7939 'alias': CPPAliasObject,
7940 }
7941 roles = {
7942 'any': CPPXRefRole(),
7943 'class': CPPXRefRole(),
7944 'struct': CPPXRefRole(),
7945 'union': CPPXRefRole(),
7946 'func': CPPXRefRole(fix_parens=True),
7947 'member': CPPXRefRole(),
7948 'var': CPPXRefRole(),
7949 'type': CPPXRefRole(),
7950 'concept': CPPXRefRole(),
7951 'enum': CPPXRefRole(),
7952 'enumerator': CPPXRefRole(),
7953 'expr': CPPExprRole(asCode=True),
7954 'texpr': CPPExprRole(asCode=False),
7955 }
7956 initial_data = {
7957 'root_symbol': Symbol(None, None, None, None, None, None, None),
7958 'names': {}, # full name for indexing -> docname
7959 }
7960  
7961 def clear_doc(self, docname: str) -> None:
7962 if Symbol.debug_show_tree:
7963 logger.debug("clear_doc: %s", docname)
7964 logger.debug("\tbefore:")
7965 logger.debug(self.data['root_symbol'].dump(1))
7966 logger.debug("\tbefore end")
7967  
7968 rootSymbol = self.data['root_symbol']
7969 rootSymbol.clear_doc(docname)
7970  
7971 if Symbol.debug_show_tree:
7972 logger.debug("\tafter:")
7973 logger.debug(self.data['root_symbol'].dump(1))
7974 logger.debug("\tafter end")
7975 logger.debug("clear_doc end: %s", docname)
7976 for name, nDocname in list(self.data['names'].items()):
7977 if nDocname == docname:
7978 del self.data['names'][name]
7979  
7980 def process_doc(self, env: BuildEnvironment, docname: str,
7981 document: nodes.document) -> None:
7982 if Symbol.debug_show_tree:
7983 logger.debug("process_doc: %s", docname)
7984 logger.debug(self.data['root_symbol'].dump(0))
7985 logger.debug("process_doc end: %s", docname)
7986  
7987 def process_field_xref(self, pnode: pending_xref) -> None:
7988 pnode.attributes.update(self.env.ref_context)
7989  
7990 def merge_domaindata(self, docnames: list[str], otherdata: dict) -> None:
7991 if Symbol.debug_show_tree:
7992 logger.debug("merge_domaindata:")
7993 logger.debug("\tself:")
7994 logger.debug(self.data['root_symbol'].dump(1))
7995 logger.debug("\tself end")
7996 logger.debug("\tother:")
7997 logger.debug(otherdata['root_symbol'].dump(1))
7998 logger.debug("\tother end")
7999  
8000 self.data['root_symbol'].merge_with(otherdata['root_symbol'],
8001 docnames, self.env)
8002 ourNames = self.data['names']
8003 for name, docname in otherdata['names'].items():
8004 if docname in docnames:
8005 if name not in ourNames:
8006 ourNames[name] = docname
8007 # no need to warn on duplicates, the symbol merge already does that
8008 if Symbol.debug_show_tree:
8009 logger.debug("\tresult:")
8010 logger.debug(self.data['root_symbol'].dump(1))
8011 logger.debug("\tresult end")
8012 logger.debug("merge_domaindata end")
8013  
8014 def _resolve_xref_inner(self, env: BuildEnvironment, fromdocname: str, builder: Builder,
8015 typ: str, target: str, node: pending_xref,
8016 contnode: Element) -> tuple[Element | None, str | None]:
8017 # add parens again for those that could be functions
8018 if typ in ('any', 'func'):
8019 target += '()'
8020 parser = DefinitionParser(target, location=node, config=env.config)
8021 try:
8022 ast, isShorthand = parser.parse_xref_object()
8023 except DefinitionError as e:
8024 # as arg to stop flake8 from complaining
8025 def findWarning(e: Exception) -> tuple[str, Exception]:
8026 if typ != 'any' and typ != 'func':
8027 return target, e
8028 # hax on top of the paren hax to try to get correct errors
8029 parser2 = DefinitionParser(target[:-2],
8030 location=node,
8031 config=env.config)
8032 try:
8033 parser2.parse_xref_object()
8034 except DefinitionError as e2:
8035 return target[:-2], e2
8036 # strange, that we don't get the error now, use the original
8037 return target, e
8038 t, ex = findWarning(e)
8039 logger.warning('Unparseable C++ cross-reference: %r\n%s', t, ex,
8040 location=node)
8041 return None, None
8042 parentKey: LookupKey = node.get("cpp:parent_key", None)
8043 rootSymbol = self.data['root_symbol']
8044 if parentKey:
8045 parentSymbol: Symbol = rootSymbol.direct_lookup(parentKey)
8046 if not parentSymbol:
8047 logger.debug("Target: %s", target)
8048 logger.debug("ParentKey: %s", parentKey.data)
8049 logger.debug(rootSymbol.dump(1))
8050 assert parentSymbol # should be there
8051 else:
8052 parentSymbol = rootSymbol
8053  
8054 if isShorthand:
8055 assert isinstance(ast, ASTNamespace)
8056 ns = ast
8057 name = ns.nestedName
8058 if ns.templatePrefix:
8059 templateDecls = ns.templatePrefix.templates
8060 else:
8061 templateDecls = []
8062 # let's be conservative with the sibling lookup for now
8063 searchInSiblings = (not name.rooted) and len(name.names) == 1
8064 symbols, failReason = parentSymbol.find_name(
8065 name, templateDecls, typ,
8066 templateShorthand=True,
8067 matchSelf=True, recurseInAnon=True,
8068 searchInSiblings=searchInSiblings)
8069 if symbols is None:
8070 if typ == 'identifier':
8071 if failReason == 'templateParamInQualified':
8072 # this is an xref we created as part of a signature,
8073 # so don't warn for names nested in template parameters
8074 raise NoUri(str(name), typ)
8075 s = None
8076 else:
8077 # just refer to the arbitrarily first symbol
8078 s = symbols[0]
8079 else:
8080 assert isinstance(ast, ASTDeclaration)
8081 decl = ast
8082 name = decl.name
8083 s = parentSymbol.find_declaration(decl, typ,
8084 templateShorthand=True,
8085 matchSelf=True, recurseInAnon=True)
8086 if s is None or s.declaration is None:
8087 txtName = str(name)
8088 if txtName.startswith('std::') or txtName == 'std':
8089 raise NoUri(txtName, typ)
8090 return None, None
8091  
8092 if typ.startswith('cpp:'):
8093 typ = typ[4:]
8094 declTyp = s.declaration.objectType
8095  
8096 def checkType() -> bool:
8097 if typ == 'any':
8098 return True
8099 objtypes = self.objtypes_for_role(typ)
8100 if objtypes:
8101 return declTyp in objtypes
8102 logger.debug(f"Type is {typ}, declaration type is {declTyp}") # NoQA: G004
8103 raise AssertionError
8104 if not checkType():
8105 logger.warning("cpp:%s targets a %s (%s).",
8106 typ, s.declaration.objectType,
8107 s.get_full_nested_name(),
8108 location=node)
8109  
8110 declaration = s.declaration
8111 if isShorthand:
8112 fullNestedName = s.get_full_nested_name()
8113 displayName = fullNestedName.get_display_string().lstrip(':')
8114 else:
8115 displayName = decl.get_display_string()
8116 docname = s.docname
8117 assert docname
8118  
8119 # the non-identifier refs are cross-references, which should be processed:
8120 # - fix parenthesis due to operator() and add_function_parentheses
8121 if typ != "identifier":
8122 title = contnode.pop(0).astext()
8123 # If it's operator(), we need to add '()' if explicit function parens
8124 # are requested. Then the Sphinx machinery will add another pair.
8125 # Also, if it's an 'any' ref that resolves to a function, we need to add
8126 # parens as well.
8127 # However, if it's a non-shorthand function ref, for a function that
8128 # takes no arguments, then we may need to add parens again as well.
8129 addParen = 0
8130 if not node.get('refexplicit', False) and declaration.objectType == 'function':
8131 if isShorthand:
8132 # this is just the normal haxing for 'any' roles
8133 if env.config.add_function_parentheses and typ == 'any':
8134 addParen += 1
8135 # and now this stuff for operator()
8136 if (env.config.add_function_parentheses and typ == 'func' and
8137 title.endswith('operator()')):
8138 addParen += 1
8139 if (typ in ('any', 'func') and
8140 title.endswith('operator') and
8141 displayName.endswith('operator()')):
8142 addParen += 1
8143 else:
8144 # our job here is to essentially nullify add_function_parentheses
8145 if env.config.add_function_parentheses:
8146 if typ == 'any' and displayName.endswith('()'):
8147 addParen += 1
8148 elif typ == 'func':
8149 if title.endswith('()') and not displayName.endswith('()'):
8150 title = title[:-2]
8151 else:
8152 if displayName.endswith('()'):
8153 addParen += 1
8154 if addParen > 0:
8155 title += '()' * addParen
8156 # and reconstruct the title again
8157 contnode += nodes.Text(title)
8158 res = make_refnode(builder, fromdocname, docname,
8159 declaration.get_newest_id(), contnode, displayName,
8160 ), declaration.objectType
8161 return res
8162  
8163 def resolve_xref(self, env: BuildEnvironment, fromdocname: str, builder: Builder,
8164 typ: str, target: str, node: pending_xref, contnode: Element,
8165 ) -> Element | None:
8166 return self._resolve_xref_inner(env, fromdocname, builder, typ,
8167 target, node, contnode)[0]
8168  
8169 def resolve_any_xref(self, env: BuildEnvironment, fromdocname: str, builder: Builder,
8170 target: str, node: pending_xref, contnode: Element,
8171 ) -> list[tuple[str, Element]]:
8172 with logging.suppress_logging():
8173 retnode, objtype = self._resolve_xref_inner(env, fromdocname, builder,
8174 'any', target, node, contnode)
8175 if retnode:
8176 if objtype == 'templateParam':
8177 return [('cpp:templateParam', retnode)]
8178 else:
8179 return [('cpp:' + self.role_for_objtype(objtype), retnode)]
8180 return []
8181  
8182 def get_objects(self) -> Iterator[tuple[str, str, str, str, str, int]]:
8183 rootSymbol = self.data['root_symbol']
8184 for symbol in rootSymbol.get_all_symbols():
8185 if symbol.declaration is None:
8186 continue
8187 assert symbol.docname
8188 fullNestedName = symbol.get_full_nested_name()
8189 name = str(fullNestedName).lstrip(':')
8190 dispname = fullNestedName.get_display_string().lstrip(':')
8191 objectType = symbol.declaration.objectType
8192 docname = symbol.docname
8193 newestId = symbol.declaration.get_newest_id()
8194 yield (name, dispname, objectType, docname, newestId, 1)
8195  
8196 def get_full_qualified_name(self, node: Element) -> str:
8197 target = node.get('reftarget', None)
8198 if target is None:
8199 return None
8200 parentKey: LookupKey = node.get("cpp:parent_key", None)
8201 if parentKey is None or len(parentKey.data) <= 0:
8202 return None
8203  
8204 rootSymbol = self.data['root_symbol']
8205 parentSymbol = rootSymbol.direct_lookup(parentKey)
8206 parentName = parentSymbol.get_full_nested_name()
8207 return '::'.join([str(parentName), target])
8208  
8209  
8210 def setup(app: Sphinx) -> dict[str, Any]:
8211 app.add_domain(CPPDomain)
8212 app.add_config_value("cpp_index_common_prefix", [], 'env')
8213 app.add_config_value("cpp_id_attributes", [], 'env')
8214 app.add_config_value("cpp_paren_attributes", [], 'env')
8215 app.add_config_value("cpp_maximum_signature_line_length", None, 'env', types={int, None})
8216 app.add_post_transform(AliasTransform)
8217  
8218 # debug stuff
8219 app.add_config_value("cpp_debug_lookup", False, '')
8220 app.add_config_value("cpp_debug_show_tree", False, '')
8221  
8222 def initStuff(app):
8223 Symbol.debug_lookup = app.config.cpp_debug_lookup
8224 Symbol.debug_show_tree = app.config.cpp_debug_show_tree
8225 app.config.cpp_index_common_prefix.sort(reverse=True)
8226 app.connect("builder-inited", initStuff)
8227  
8228 return {
8229 'version': 'builtin',
8230 'env_version': 9,
8231 'parallel_read_safe': True,
8232 'parallel_write_safe': True,
8233 }
